%TITLE An introduction to %@%n Official Rules
The official rules are a detailed set of guidelines for %c%lALL%x users and administrators of %@%n, implemented and intended to maintain order amongst both its users and administrators.

These rules help keep %@%m a friendly and enjoyable environment for all of its users by helping keep it free from abusive and malicious people, and users who misuse privileges with which they have been entrusted (This includes Builders and administrators.)

As a user of %@%m, you are expected to thoroughly read, understand and abide by these rules at all times.  If you fail to do so, and break rules intentionally or unintentionally, you will receive appropriate punishment.  This will initially be in the form of a verbal warning and possible removal of abused privileges, but if you continue to ignore and break rules, you could be banned from %@%m completely.

%PAGE
Each rule may be preceeded by a rating (E.g:  '%m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>%x'.)  The number (On a scale of %y%l1%x (%g%lNot too serious%x) to %y%l5%x (%r%l%fVery serious%x)) indicates how serious breaking that particular rule will be treated.  The ratings are intended as a guideline, and will be used to help decide on suitable punishment when a rule is broken.

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xIf a rule has a low rating, this does not mean that it is acceptable to purposely break it or ignore the fact that it has been broken.  If a rule is broken, suitable punishment must be issued promptly.

              %9%6These rules apply to the date at the top of the help page for '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.  The administrators of %@%m reserve the right to change, amend or add to these rules at any time without prior notice.  Any significant additions or amendments will be announced on %@%n BBS in the %y%lNEWS%x topic (See '%g%l%<bbs%>%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
