%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC safety
%TOPIC safetyguidelines
%TITLE Safety Guidelines for %w%l%u%fALL%x users of %@%m...
All users of %@%m should be aware that things that occur in real life, either if they are directly or indirectly linked to occurances on %@%m, that the administrators %r%l%ucannot%x be held responsible, nor can they punish or ban users without proof that abuse has actually occurred on %@%m.  We advise that all users of %@%m, in common with all other forms of anonymous Internet communication, should follow some basic safety guidelines:

%y%l%4*  %c%l%uNEVER%x give out your real life personal details (Home address, telephone number, etc) to anyone you do not know in real life  -  Even if you've known them 'virtually' for a long time, they may not be who you think they are.

%r%l%4*  %c%l%uNEVER%x forget that others may adopt 'Internet Personas' which may, or may not, correspond to their real life personas.  In other words, don't believe all you read!

%y%l%4*  %c%l%uREMEMBER%x, if it sounds too good to be true, it probably is.

%PAGE
If something is happening in real life as a result of the occurances of not following the above guidelines, please note, we can only advise the following:

   %m%l%4Get in touch with the Police, or whatever other Authorities you can (Offender's Internet Provider(s), etc.) and pass on the information you know.  We can only act upon punishable offenses we see and have proof of on %@%m.

%9%4%r%lIMPORTANT:  %xThe administrators of %@%m will %y%l%u*NOT*%x see fit to punish possible users who use %c%l*NON* %@%m related incidents%x in order to cause or inflict spite or punishment of other possible users.  To punish a user requires solid proof that the user did do something wrong, and that proof needs to be visible to other administrators on %@%m's server.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<behaviour guidelines%>%x', '%g%l%<general rules%>%x', '%g%l%<terms%>%x', '%g%l%<disclaimer%>%x' and '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC behaviour
%TOPIC acceptablebehaviour
%TOPIC behaviourguidelines
%TITLE Guidelines for Acceptable Behaviour
The Administrators of %@%m must take a conservative view towards certain forms of language and behaviour in public locations such as %y%l%@%n BBS%x and the %y%lSwan Pub%x, regardless of their personal opinions about such things.

The %y%l%(CENSOR%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<censor flag%>%x') was incorporated into %@%m to protect both younger users and %@%m itself from any complaints made to its host (%c%l%@%l%x) and/or server administrators.

However, not all forms of slang/vulgarity are caught by the automatic bad language censor which is active in public locations, and the following guidelines are a companion to the auto-censor and guide for the user for acceptable language and behaviour in the public areas of %@%m.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Public Rooms
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xPublic discussions of a sexual nature must use proper, clinical terminology, in its correct context.  If you use vulgarities/slang at all in public areas (This includes attempts to get around the auto-censor by using different spellings or ASCII characters), you will be asked to stop or take it to a private room or chat channel.

Failure to comply with the Administrator's request will result in an Official Warning and/or further punishment.

%PAGE

%c%l%$The BBS (Bulletin Board System)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xDue to the nature of some BBS topics, sexual discussions take place.  Their purpose is to inform and help users with sexual problems or questions.  This does not give license to use improper, vulgar terminology in these discussions.  You must use the proper, clinical terms in their correct context.

Any malicious BBS post done merely to provoke a slagging match, 'spam' (Excessive posting), or to attack another user, will be censored or removed depending on the content and the user will be warned to stop.

Any BBS post found to contain vulgar words and/or phrases (This also includes attempts to get around the auto-censor by using different spellings or ASCII characters) will be censored or removed by the Administrators, and if necessary an Official Warning will be given.

%PAGE
Failure to comply with this may result in the loss of your %y%l%(^flag BBS%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<bbs flag%>%x') and an entry on your rapsheet.


%c%l%$Final Words
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~
%xThe Admin have no wish to inhibit the users of %@%m.  Certain forms of discussions are not being prohibited, we merely ask that if you are going to be in a public location, such as %y%lThe Swan Pub%x, you exercise caution when using terminology that might be considered offensive.

What you do or say in private rooms is your business and no Admin will ever interfere with that.  However, public areas such as the %y%lBBS%x or %y%lThe Swan Pub%x %r%l%uMUST BE KEPT CLEAN%x to protect younger users.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<general rules%>%x', '%g%l%<safety guidelines%>%x', '%g%l%<terms%>%x', '%g%l%<disclaimer%>%x' and '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC userrules
%TOPIC mortalrules
%TOPIC normalrules
%TOPIC generalrules
%TITLE Rules for %w%lGeneral Users%x (%w%lMortals%x)
%4%r%l*  %xAs a general (%(Mortal%)) user of %@%n, you are free to do and say whatever you like %y%lwithin reason%x, providing it is not %r%lprohibited%x by the %c%l%(rules%)%x or %c%l%(disclaimer%)%x of %@%m (See '%g%l%<rules%>%x' and '%g%l%<disclaimer%>%x'.)

%4%y%l*  %xIf any complaints are received from other users about you, they will be %c%lfully investigated%x and %c%lappropriate action%x will be taken if you refuse to stop (Depending on the severity, this could involve imposing a %y%lban%x on your site and/or sending a complaint to your system Adminstrator(s) (Which could result in you losing your access to the Internet.))

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xYou must not '%c%lspam%x' (Send large quantities of output), %c%labuse%x, %c%lharass%x, %c%loffend%x or %c%linvade the privacy%x of other users.

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xThe distribution/sharing of %c%lillegal%x or %c%lpornographic material%x is %r%l%f%uSTRICTLY%x prohibited.  This includes the use of %@%m's World Wide Web Interface (See '%g%l%<html%>%x') to provide links to or display %c%lmaterial%x, %c%lresources%x or %c%larchives%x which contain %y%lillegal%x, %y%loffensive%x or %y%lpornographic%x material.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xYou must not create more than %y%l%f%uONE%x character for your own use  -  If we discover that you are using more than one character, the additional character(s) will be %r%ldestroyed%x and the Internet site you connect from could receive a %y%lban%x on creating new characters.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xDo not advertise any other MUD which can be accessed via the Internet, on a public channel, via %@%m internal mail or in a title/description.  This includes saying the address in a room.  You can give out the address of another MUD over a private channel to another user (Providing they have asked you for it), e.g:  Via '%g%l%(page%)%x', '%g%l%(tell%)%x' or '%g%l%(mail%)%x' (See '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x' and '%g%l%<mail%>%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<builder rules%>%x', '%g%l%<safety guidelines%>%x', '%g%l%<behaviour guidelines%>%x', '%g%l%<terms%>%x' and '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC builderrules
%TOPIC buildersrules
%TOPIC buildingrules
%TITLE Rules for %w%lBuilders%x
As a Builder, the rules for General Users (See '%g%l%<general rules%>%x') apply as well as the following...

%4%r%l*  %xBefore you can be given building privileges, you must at least set your %c%lPRIVATE%x E-mail address to your %r%l%fREAL%x E-mail address, by typing '%g%l%(@email%) private <EMAIL ADDRESS>%x' (See '%g%l%<@email%>%x'.)  An anonymous or forwarding E-mail address can't be accepted.  Your private E-mail address is only visible to yourself and the administrators of %@%m, and will be kept %m%lSTRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL%x.

%4%y%l*  %xAs a Builder, you may have up to a maximum of %y%lONE%x permanent puppet, providing you can fully justify the need for it.  Temporary puppets can be obtained by Builders for the purpose of testing building work from the point of view of another user (Please ask Admin for details of the %c%lPuppet Bank%x.)

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xYou must not use your building privileges to purposely annoy, spam (Send large quantities of output), abuse, offend or invade the privacy of other users.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xYou must not use your building privileges to hack or purposely 'lag' %@%m.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xYou must not create compound commands which will inconvenience, confuse or attempt to use the privileges of another user.  This also includes making compound commands which shadow built-in commands (E.g:  '%g%l%(@command%) %(say%);%(emote%);%(page%);%(tell%)%x', etc.)

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xYou must not use your building privileges to try and obtain %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above powers, or commands which allow you to execute commands under the ID or privileges of another character.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<assistant rules%>%x', '%g%l%<terms%>%x', '%g%l%<builder%>%x', '%g%l%<safety guidelines%>%x', '%g%l%<behaviour guidelines%>%x' and '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC xrules
%TOPIC exprules
%TOPIC assistantrules
%TOPIC assistantsrules
%TOPIC experiencedrules
%TOPIC experiencedbuilderrules
%TITLE Rules for %w%lAssistants%x and %w%lExperienced Builders%x
As an %rAssistant%x or %r%lExperienced Builder%x, the rules for both General Users (See '%g%l%<general rules%>%x') and Builders (See '%g%l%<builder rules%>%x') apply as well as the following...

%4%r%l*  %xThe %rAssistant%x and %r%lExperienced Builder%x ranks are %c%lNOT%x part of the administration team, and do not have any administrative rights or privileges (With the exception of the use of the '%g%l%(assist%)%x' and '%g%l%(welcome%)%x' commands (See '%g%l%<assist%>%x' and '%g%l%<welcome%>%x') when there are few or no Admin connected.)

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xAs an %rAssistant%x, you must be prepared to help any users who ask you for it.  If you are unable to help them, you should direct them to either a member of Admin or another %rAssistant/%r%lExperienced Builder%x who can.

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %xProviding help and assistance is a requirement of the %rAssistant%x rank, but optional for %r%lExperienced Builders%x, who are given the rank as recognition for their building skills and to help them to improve and extend their skills further.  However, %r%lExperienced Builders%x must not outrightly refuse to give help and assistance  -  If you do not wish to help the user, you must redirect them to another %rAssistant%x, %r%lExperienced Builder%x or member of Admin who can.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xIf there are only a few members of Admin connected, or no Admin connected at all, you should use the '%g%l%(assist%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<assist%>%x') to check for and provide assistance to users who require it, and welcome new users.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %r%lExperienced Builders%x must not use their extra privileges to hack or obtain privileges to which they are not entitled.  %r%lExperienced Builder%x privileges are entrusted to the users to whom they are given.  Any abuse of these extra privileges will result in removal of %r%lExperienced Builder%x status.

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xAs an %r%lExperienced Builder%x or %rAssistant%x, you must behave reasonably and responsibly at all times.  This is because you will be looked up to and approached for help by both existing and new users.  Although giving help and assistance is not a requirement of the %r%lExperienced Builder%x status (It is a requirement of the %rAssistant%x status, however), you must not outrightly refuse or be offensive to the user asking.  If you do not wish to help them or are unable to, please refer them to another %rAssistant%x, %r%lExperienced Builder%x or administrator.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xIf an %r%lExperienced Builder%x has their %y%lHELP%x flag set, all rules which apply to %rAssistants%x also apply to them (In addition to %r%lExperienced Builder%x rules.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<admin rules%>%x', '%g%l%<terms%>%x', '%g%l%<assistant%>%x', '%g%l%<experienced builder%>%x', '%g%l%<safety guidelines%>%x', '%g%l%<behaviour guidelines%>%x' and '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC adminrules
%TOPIC administratorrules
%TOPIC administrationrules
%TITLE Rules for %w%ladministrators%x
As an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above, it's important that you act responsibly and fairly at all times, and give help and assistance to users as and when they need it to the best of your ability.  It's important that you bear in mind that anything you do or say in public reflects not only on yourself, but the entire Admin team and %@%m as a whole, both of which you are a part of and representing.

These rules are designed as basic guidelines to what you should and shouldn't do as an administrator, and must be followed at all times.  Violating the rules will result in appropriate punishment and official warnings being issued.  Failure to comply with the rules after official warnings have been issued could ultimately result in your demotion.

%PAGE

%c%l%$General rules for administators...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xDo not do anything which could degrade the credibility of %@%m, its Admin team, or the provider of its Internet connection (%y%l%@%l%x.)

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xDo not harass any user, or do anything which may cause users to leave %@%m, and use another MUD instead.  If there are personal problems with a certain user, then avoid contact with them.  If necessary, use the friend flags to block all messages from them.  Type '%g%l%(fadd%) <NAME>%x' and '%g%l%(fset%) <NAME> = enemy !fchat !link !mail !pagetell !pagetellfriends%x' (See '%g%l%<fadd%>%x' and '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.)

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xDo not connect to %@%m if you are depressed, drunk, or otherwise likely to act irresponsibly and abuse your powers.

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xDo not advertise any other MUD which can be accessed via the Internet, on a public channel, via %@%m internal mail or in a title/description.  This includes saying the address in a room.  You can give out the address of another MUD over a private channel to another user (Providing they have asked you for it), e.g:  Via '%g%l%(page%)%x', '%g%l%(tell%)%x' or '%g%l%(mail%)%x' (See '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x' and '%g%l%<mail%>%x'.)

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xDo not act irresponsibly elsewhere on the Internet, where you can be recognised as a member of the %@%m Admin team.  This means do not go to other MUD's and be abusive, or advertise %@%m on them.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xDo not 'hack' to obtain privileges higher than your level.  If you need a certain privilege, ask someone of a higher level than you to help you with it.

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xDo not boot a dead connection unless it's absolutely necessary  -  The '%g%l%(@bootdead%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@bootdead%>%x') can be used by a user to boot any dead connections they might have.  Connections that are 'stuck' can also be revived by logging in again and taking them over.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xMortal users are only allowed a maximum of %c%lONE%x puppet, providing the need for it can be fully justified.  Temporary puppets can be obtained by Mortals from the %c%lPuppet Bank%x (This can be reached by typing '%g%lpuppet%x'.)  The use of a permanent puppet in a building project as a shopkeeper (For example) is not a suitable use.  A suitably named object would give the desired effect.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Rules for dealing with other users...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xAnswer all assists and welcomes when you can (See '%g%l%<assist%>%x' and '%g%l%<welcome%>%x'), especially if there are few Admin connected, or you are the only member of Admin connected.  If there is a sufficient number of Admin connected, try to take it in turns to do them.  New Admin have priority over assists and welcomes.  Remember that higher ranking members of Admin may not see assist/welcome messages if a sufficient number of lower ranking Admin are connected.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xIf a user asks you for help, help them to the best of your ability  -  This is a priority over building or chatting to your friends.  If you are not able to help them, ask someone who can.  It's important to stay and see what the answer to the problem is, and to try and learn from it.  If no other administrators are available to help, then %@%m mail someone who you know is able to solve the problem, or direct them to an %r%lExperienced Builder%x (If one is connected.)

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xDo not summon users or teleport (See '%g%l%<summon%>%x' and '%g%l%<@teleport%>%x') them around against their will.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l2%m%l>>>  %xFeel free to teleport to other users locations to examine them and their contents, but if the owner or other characters are connected and in the location, then ask permission to visit first.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xIf you find a room or thing that acts as a jail (Holds you there), ask the user to remove it or disable it.  If they do not comply, use an appropriate punishment.  If all else fails, remove their %y%l%(BUILDER%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<builder flag%>%x'.)  (If you find yourself stuck in a jail, use the '%g%l%(escape%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<escape%>%x') to get out.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Rules for dealing with abusive/problem users...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xIf a user is abusive to you or other users  -  Deal with them appropriately.  The order of punishment is as follows:

%9%9%8   %y%lAn official warning:  %x'%g%l%(warn%) <NAME> = <REASON>%x'.
%9%9%8                         (See '%g%l%<warn%>%x.)  Official warnings are logged to the '%c%lWarn%x' log file (See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.)

%9%9%8   %y%lThe Punishment Zone:  %x'%g%lpunish <NAME> = <REASON>%x'.
%9%9%8                         They will be broken off from all contact with other users, and have to type out some of %@%m's rules, before getting out.  (Use '%g%lunpunish <NAME> = <REASON>%x' to let them out prematurely.)

%PAGE
%9%9%8   %y%lJail:                 %x'%g%ljail <NAME> = <REASON>%x'.
%9%9%8                         They will be unable to leave the jail.  Admin can get out by typing '%g%ldoor%x' or '%g%l%(escape%)%x'.  (Use '%g%lfree <NAME> = <REASON>%x' to let them out.)

%9%9%8   %y%lMoron:                %x'%g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = moron = <REASON>%x'.
%9%9%8                         (See '%g%l%<moron flag%>%x.)  They will then have negative privileges.  They will be unable to page people (Except Admin), use %@%m mail, or whisper secretly.  (Use '%g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = !moron = <REASON>%x' to reset the moron flag.)

%PAGE
%9%9%8   %y%lBoot:                 %x'%g%l%(@boot%) *<NAME> = <REASON> [= <BAN TIME>]%x'.
%9%9%8                         (See '%g%l%<@boot%>%x'.)  They will be booted (Forcefully disconnected) from %@%m, and a public message will be displayed showing the boot and the reason.  It's also logged to the '%c%lBoot%x' log file (See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.)  %y%l<BAN TIME>%x is an optional time in minutes (Up to %c%l60 minutes%x) to ban the user, so that they can't reconnect again almost immediately.

%9%9%8   %y%lBan:                  %x'%g%l%(@ban%) *<NAME> = <TIME>|permanently = <REASON>%x'.
%9%9%8                         (See '%g%l%<@ban%>%x'.)  Bans the user for the time specified or permanently.  Users can only be banned by %c%lWizard/%cDruids%x and above.  If you're an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x and can't set a necessary ban, ask a higher level character to do so for you.  (Use '%g%l%(@ban%) *<NAME> = lift = <REASON>%x' to lift a ban.)  Be sure to send E-mail to the banned user explaining why they have been banned.

%PAGE
%9%9%y%l*  %c%lSite bans%x  -  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xIf a user keeps creating new duplicate characters and/or Guest characters, then a site ban may be necessary.

%9%9%3                 %y%l*  %xTo ban a site from creating characters, use:
%9%9%3                    '%g%l%(@site set%) <ADDRESS> = !create = <REASON>%x' (See '%g%l%<@site set%>%x'.)
%9%9%3                 %r%l*  %xLikewise, to stop Guest character being created from a site, use:
%9%9%3                    '%g%l%(@site set%) <ADDRESS> = !guest = <REASON>%x'.
%9%9%3                 %y%l*  %xThe flags can be combined:
%9%9%3                    '%g%l%(@site set%) <ADDRESS> = !create !guest = <REASON>%x'.

%9%9                 If you set a site to be create or guest banned, you should re-describe it to reflect that  -  Use '%g%l%(@site desc%) <IP ADDRESS> = <DESCRIPTION>%x' (See '%g%l%<@site desc%>%x'.)  Add '%y%l(Create Banned)%x', '%y%l(Guest Banned)%x', or '%y%l(Create and Guest Banned)%x' to the end of the site's description.

%PAGE
%9%9%1%r%l*  %c%lMail abuse%x  -  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xIf a user is abusing the internal mail system, reset their %y%l%(MAIL%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<mail flag%>%x') using '%g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = !mail = <REASON>%x'.  This prevents them from sending or receiving any mail whatsoever.  If they're just harassing one particular user, get that user to add them as a friend (Or enemy), and type '%g%l%(fset%) <NAME> = !mail%x' (See '%g%l%<fadd%>%x' and '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.)  This prevents them sending mail to that one person.

%9%9%1%y%l*  %c%lBBS abuse%x   -  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xIf someone continually abuses the BBS by posting rude, offensive or degrading messages, then reset their %y%l%(BBS%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<bbs flag%>%x') using '%g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = !bbs = <REASON>%x'.

%9%9%1%r%l*  %c%lRap sheets%x  -  %m%l<<<%y%l2%m%l>>>  %xLog any abuse onto a user's rapsheet with the '%g%laddrap%x' command.  The usage is '%g%laddrap <NAME> = <ABUSE>%x'.  To see what they've done in the past, use '%g%lcheckrap <NAME>%x'.  This helps to identify consistent problem users.

%PAGE
%9%9%7%y%l*  %c%lMonitoring users%x  -  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xIf a user is suspected of hacking or abuse, and needs to be watched, use the '%g%l%(@monitor%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@monitor%>%x'.)  The basic use is '%g%l%(@monitor%) <NAME> = commands = <REASON>%x'.  Do not use '%g%l%(@monitor%)%x' unless it's strictly necessary, as it breaches on the user's privacy.  Use '%g%l%(@monitor%) <NAME> = off%x' to stop monitoring.


%c%l%$Rules for administrative privileges...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xUse the '%g%l%(shout%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<shout%>%x') only for important messages which %c%lALL%x users connected need to see.  '%g%l%(@with%) connected ...%x' (See '%g%l%<@with%>%x') in conjunction with '%g%l%(page%)%x', '%g%l%(tell%)%x' or '%g%l%(@notify%)%x' is treated as a '%g%l%(shout%)%x' (See '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x' and '%g%l%<@notify%>%x'.)  Please remember that you are representing the Admin team as a whole, and every connected user will see your message.

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xDo not use '%g%l%(page%)%x', '%g%l%(tell%)%x' or '%g%l%(@notify%)%x' in conjunction with '%g%l%(@with%) friends%x' or '%g%l%(@with%) connected%x' (See '%g%l%<@with%>%x') as an alternative or substitute for the '%g%l%(page%) friends%x', '%g%l%(tell%) friends%x' or '%g%l%(shout%)%x' command ('%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x' and '%g%l%<shout%>%x'.)  This rule is for two simple reasons...

   %9%g%l(1)  %xIt causes extra and unnecessary work for the server, especially if you have a large friends list or there are a good number of users connected.  '%g%l%(page%) friends%x', '%g%l%(tell%) friends%x' or '%g%l%(shout%)%x' will only take a few milliseconds to execute, whereas '%g%l%(@with%) friends%x' or '%g%l%(@with%) connected%x' can take up to several seconds, causing unnecessary 'lag'.

%PAGE
   %9%g%l(2)  %xIf '%g%l%(@notify%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@notify%>%x') is used with these commands, the recipients have no easy means of selectively blocking the messages if they do not wish to receive them.  With '%g%l%(page%) friends%x' and '%g%l%(tell%) friends%x' they can simply reset the %y%l%(^friend PAGETELLFRIENDS%)%x friend flag (See '%g%l%<pagetellfriends%>%x') on you if they do not wish to receive the messages.  If '%g%l%(page%)%x'/'%g%l%(tell%)%x' is used (I.e:  '%g%l%(@with%) friends me do %g%l%(tell%) $6 = hello%x'), this can be extremely confusing for the recipients, as to them it appears as though you have specifically and individually sent the message to them, rather than your entire list of friends.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xDo not give out your privileges to other characters, by giving out your password or giving them a compound command with your '%g%l%(@chpid%)%x' in it (See '%g%l%<@chpid%>%x'.)

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xDo not use your privileges for your own personal gain, benefit or pleasure.

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xDo not use '%g%l%(@force%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@force%>%x') to force another character (Excluding your own puppets) to execute a command or say something against their will.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xDo not use fuses (See '%g%l%<@fuse%>%x') to monitor rooms or characters.  This is a serious breach of privacy.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xDo not destroy a character on user request under any circumstances.  If a character is left unused they will eventually be destroyed by the automatic maintainence system.

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xDo destroy characters when they are found to be duplicates, but only if you are certain that they're duplicates.  Remember that some users will connect from the same account and might have the same E-mail address.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xBe very judicious in creating alarms, for your own or any other character's use.  Several alarms going off at the same time, or on a regular basis (I.e:  More than once every %c%l5 minutes%x) can cause unnecessary 'lag'.  The same effect can often be achieved using a fuse and the '%g%l{%(@?time%)}%x' query command (See '%g%l%<@?time%>%x'), and should always be done as an alternative, if possible.

   %4The ownership of an alarm should never be changed to a Mortal character.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xDo not use the '%g%l%(@areawrite%)%x', '%g%l%(@oecho%)%x' or '%g%l%(@write%)%x' commands (See '%g%l%<;%>%x', '%g%l%<@oecho%>%x' and '%g%l%<@write%>%x') in %y%l#2%x, %y%l#4%x, or a public area.  Likewise do not use these (And similar) commands (I.e:  '%g%l%(@notify%)%x'  -  See '%g%l%<@notify%>%x') to fake messages, or fake another user's actions or speech.

%PAGE
%COMMENT %4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xWhen adding Internet sites, use the rules for site adding as stated in the %y%lAPPRENTICES%x topic on %c%l%@%n BBS%x (See '%g%l%<bbs%>%x') or in the file '%y%ltczadmin.siteguidelines.txt%x', available from the FTP archive (See '%g%l%<ftp%>%x'.)
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xWhen adding Internet sites, use the rules for site adding as stated in the %y%lAPPRENTICES%x topic on %c%l%@%n BBS%x (See '%g%l%<bbs%>%x'.)

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xDo not set an execution time limit greater than %c%l3 seconds%x, unless it's absolutely necessary for the compound command to function.  In most cases (If not all), it will usually be possible to re-write the compound command more efficiently, so that it doesn't need an execution time limit greater than %c%l3 seconds%x.  An execution time limit greater than %c%l5 seconds%x should never be used, as this will cause noticable lag.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xDo not teleport a Mortal owned command to a module in %y%l#4%x (Or to %y%l#4%x itself), if it's not set %y%l%(READONLY%)%x (See '%g%l%<readonly flag%>%x'.)  If the %y%l%(READONLY%)%x flag stops the compound command working correctly, then it either needs to be re-written or Admin owned instead (A Mortal's compound command should never be changed to Admin ownership without first extensive checking for hacks, 'backdoors' or flaws which could be taken advantage of by Mortals.)

%PAGE
%4   An easy way to teleport commands into %y%l#4%x is to use the '%g%ltelglobal%x' command, which takes those rules into account.  Type '%g%ltelglobal <COMMAND>%x' to use it.  The '%g%lcheckmodule%x' command can be used to examine the modules in %y%l#4%x for any commands which breach the rules.  Any global commands also need to be coded efficiently, and use good grammar, spelling, and presentation.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xDo not disclose any information which is only readable/accessible by Admin to non-Admin users.  This includes the '%g%l%(natter%)%x' channel (See '%g%l%<natter%>%x'), restricted BBS topics (Such as the Admin only topics), contents of log files (See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'), rap sheets, and any other information/commands which a lower level user couldn't access themselves.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xDo not destroy or modify objects which belong to other users (Both Mortal and Admin owned), unless you have the permission from the owner to do so (An exeception to this rule is if the object is being used to 'spam' users/areas, is abusive/offensive in some way, or is being used to lag/hack %@%m.)

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l3%m%l>>>  %xDo not adjust the bank account or credit in pocket of a user without good reason (I.e:  The user has obtained credit by unfair means or is in severe debt.)  This is important, because improper use of the '%g%l%(@credit%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@credit%>%x') command (I.e:  Injecting excessive money into the system or taking it out) could ruin the entire monetary system and make it worthless.


%c%l%$Rules for building and Building Quota limits...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l1%m%l>>>  %xTo obtain a %y%l%(BUILDER%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<builder flag%>%x'), a character must have a valid and unique E-mail address.  This ensures that they are not duplicates.  To see if anyone else on %@%m has the same E-mail address, use the '%g%lcheckb%x' command.  If so, enquire as to why their address is not unique.  To see if the address is valid and not fake, the easiest way is to send an E-mail to it, and get them to reply.  Do not set a %y%l%(BUILDER%)%x flag until you are sure that the E-mail address is valid and the character isn't a duplicate.

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l2%m%l>>> %xDo not raise a characters Building Quota limit above %c%l500%x, unless they really need it, and they are building something of good quality that is beneficial to users of %@%m other than themselves and just a few friends.  This is %r%lIMPORTANT%x  -  'Good quality' means good, well written descriptions, fields of exits are set ('%g%l%(@osucc%)%x', '%g%l%(@odrop%)%x' and '%g%l%(@drop%)%x'  -  See '%g%l%<@osucc%>%x', '%g%l%<@odrop%>%x' and '%g%l%<@drop%>%x'), compound commands are well used and written, no objects are used that could be placed in a description instead.  Be very stringent about giving out Building Quota limits greater than %c%l500%x.  It's irrelevant that many other users may already have more than 500  -  That's the limit for Builders unless they are building something exceptional.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Rules for promotions and demotions...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xDo not promote a character to %rAssistant%x, %r%lExperienced Builder%x or %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or higher.  Promotions are carried out when there is an Admin review (Or for %r%lExperienced Builders%x and %rAssistants%x, as the result of a vote in favour between all administrators on %@%n BBS.)  The exception to this is promoting your puppet to %r%lExperienced Builder%x or %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x, if you are able.  If you're an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x yourself, you can still have your puppet promoted to the same level  -  Just ask someone of a higher level to do it for you.

   %4%rAssistants%x and %r%lExperienced Builders%x may be promoted after a votable message on %@%n BBS gives them a %c%l60%%%x or more majority in favour.  The message must be on the BBS for at least a week before a promotion is given, and the voting must use the majority factor ('%g%lvote <NUMBER> = majority%x'  -  See '%g%l%<majority factor%>%x'.)

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xOnly users who are of %c%l16%x years of age or over may be promoted to the rank of %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above.  This is because material Admin may be subject to and situations they may need to deal with are unsuitable for users below this age.  If a member of Admin is discovered at a later date to be under the age of 16, they will be immediately demoted.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xAdministrators on %@%m may not be administrators on any other MUD.  The main reason for this rule is that someone who is Admin on more than one MUD will not be able to be fully dedicated to administrating %@%m, to which they should be fully dedicated.  It's also unfair on other people who are not administrators on any MUD, who's chances are reduced by people who are administrators on more than one MUD.

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xAdministrators must be able to connect on a regular basis, as one of their primary tasks is giving help and assistance to both existing and new users and dealing with abusive/problem users.  Of course, allowances are made for holidays and other periods where a member of Admin will be away for a short period of time.  If you are going to be away for a period of time, you must announce when and how long you will be away in the %y%lADMIN/ABSENCES%x topic of %@%n BBS.  If you fail to do this, your demotion may occur.

   %4A member of Admin should ideally connect for %c%l24 hours%x or more each month.  If a member's connect time is considered insufficient in a period of %c%l3%x consecutive months, their status will be subject to review.

%PAGE
%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l4%m%l>>>  %xThe returning of a flag (%r%lExperienced Builder/%rAssistant%x and above) should first go to an Admin vote, unless predefined by a time period elapsing (I.e:  Their flag was taken away for %c%lone week%x and %c%lone week%x has elapsed since its removal.)  The vote should be held in the BBS '%y%lAdmin/Voting%x' topic, where %c%lALL%x Admin may vote.

%4%r%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l2%m%l>>>  %xIf a member of Admin wishes to resign, then demote them, but be sure to remind them that they have a period of %c%l2 weeks%x in which to change their mind.  After this period has passed, they will need to go through the review process again to re-join the Admin team.  If an %r%lExperienced Builder%x or Builder abuses their building privileges, take their flag away.  If you are not sure about doing this, discuss it on the '%g%l%(natter%)%x' channel and have a vote if necessary.

%4%y%l*  %m%l<<<%y%l5%m%l>>>  %xIf a member of Admin starts maliciously abusing their power/privileges, and refuses to stop, everything within the power of the administrators connected at the time should be done to stop them, including demotion, if necessary.
