%4%r%l*  %xSetting name prefixes ('%g%l%(@prefix%) <NAME> = <NAME PREFIX>%x') and name suffixes ('%g%l%(@suffix%) <NAME> = <NAME SUFFIX>%x'.)  Please make sure they are not abusive, offensive or use censored words.  See '%g%l%<@prefix%>%x' and '%g%l%<@suffix%>%x'.

%4%y%l*  %xChanging a forgotten password for a character ('%g%l%(@newpassword%) <NAME> = <NEW PASSWORD>%x'  -  See '%g%l%<@newpassword%>%x')  -  Please ensure that they are authentic, and not somebody else, trying to hack into another person's character.  (One way to do this is to check their E-mail address, and send their new password to the E-mail address they have set on %@%m.)

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %xSetting %y%l%(BUILDER%)%x flags ('%g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = builder%x'  -  See '%g%l%<@set%>%x' and '%g%l%<builder flag%>%x'), after checking that the potential Builder has set their E-Mail address, and is not a duplicate character (Use '%g%l%(checkb%) <NAME>%x' to check  -  See '%g%l%<checkb%>%x'.)

%4%y%l*  %xTeleporting Builders' Top Areas to '%c%lThe Top Area For Builders(#646)%x' ('%g%l%(@tel%) #<ID> = #646%x' or '%g%l%(toptel%) #<ID>%x'.)  See '%g%l%<toptel%>%x' and '%g%l%<@tel%>%x'.

%4%r%l*  %xAssessing Building Quota rises for Builders ('%g%l%(@quotalimit%)%x'  -  See '%g%l%<@quotalimit%>%x'), having checked the quality of what they have built so far.  Please see '%g%l%<quota%>%x' for further details regarding Building Quota increases.

%4%y%l*  %xSetting %r%lExperienced Builder%x ('%g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = experienced%x') or %rAssistant%x ('%g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = assistant%x') flags on users, as a result of a vote in favour on %@%n BBS between all administrators of %@%m.  See '%g%l%<@set%>%x', '%g%l%<experienced%>%x' and '%g%l%<assistant%>%x'.

%PAGE
%4%r%l*  %xAdding and checking Internet site descriptions ('%g%l%(@site add%) <ADDRESS> [=] <DESCRIPTION>%x' and '%g%l%(@site desc%) <ADDRESS> [=] <DESCRIPTION>%x'  -  You may also wish to investigate the use of the '%g%lsitereport%x' commands for this purpose.  See '%g%l%<@site%>%x', '%g%l%<@site add%>%x' and '%g%l%<@site desc%>%x'.
