%TOPIC residency
%TITLE Help on gaining %w%lresidency%x on %@%n
On many Talker/MUD systems, you need to obtain permanent residency in order to keep your character after you log out.

On %@%n, you %c%ldo not%x need to obtain residency  -  Your character will be kept after you log out (With the exception of Guest Characters, who are temporary (Please ask a member of Admin to create a character for you if you are logged in as a Guest Character.))  All we ask is that you use your character regularly, and you do not have more than %c%lONE%x character for your own personal use.

%@%n automatically checks for unused characters on a regular basis, and deletes any who have not been used for a significant period of time (See '%g%l%<timeout%>%x' for more details.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<timeout%>%x' and '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.

