%TOPIC groupbuilders
%TOPIC groupbuilding
%TOPIC groupbuildingprojects
%TITLE Help on %w%lgroup building projects%x
If you and your proposed group are starting a building project from scratch, you may like to ask a member of Admin to create a character for the purpose with an appropriate Building Quota limit, with all members of the group being given full '%c%lread%x' and '%c%lwrite%x' permissions to this character (I.e:  '%g%l%(fset%) <NAME> = read write create destroy !sharable%x'.)

All work on the building project should then be done under the ownership of this character (Using the '%g%l@chuid%x' (See '%g%l%<@chuid%>%x') command when working on the project.)  This will prevent problems arising if a member of the group suddenly decides to pull out or a new member joins the group, and will keep all of the building project together in one place, owned by a single character.  The password of this character should only be disclosed to the founder (Or user in charge) of the group, allowing them to remain in full control of the group and building project.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<fset%>%x', '%g%l%<sharable flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<@chuid%>%x'.

