%TITLE Help on '%w%lauthors%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lauthor <NAME> [= <PAGE NO>]
        authors [<PAGE NO>]%]%x

The '%g%lauthors%x' command displays a complete list of source code module authors.

Typing '%g%lauthors%x' without a name of a module author will display a complete list of all authors.  The first page of authors will be displayed.  You can display the other pages using '%g%lauthors <PAGE NO>%x', e.g:  '%g%lauthors 2%x'.

If you are interested in a particular author, you can type '%g%lauthor <NAME>%x' to view full information (Including modules they have worked on) about a source code module author.  For example, '%g%lauthor jpb%x' will display full information about the module author with the initials %y%lJPB%x.  You can specify the %c%linitials%x, %c%lfull name%x or %c%lnickname%x of an author.

%PAGE
The '%g%lauthors%x' command ensures that authors of TCZ source code (See '%g%l%<tcz%>%x' and '%g%l%<gpl%>%x') modules are given credit and acknowledgement where due.  It also allows users to find out who was responsible for their favourite parts of TCZ.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<modules%>%x', '%g%l%<version info%>%x', '%g%l%<bug fixes%>%x', '%g%l%<acknowledgements%>%x', '%g%l%<tcz%>%x' and '%g%l%<version%>%x'.

