%TITLE Help on %w%lThe Bank of %@%m%x
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lstatement [<NAME>]
        withdraw <AMOUNT>
        restrict <AMOUNT>
        deposit <AMOUNT>
        bank%]%x

Every user on %@%m has a bank account, where they can deposit and withdraw credit (Money) which they've earned.

Every user on %@%m starts off with %c%l500%x credits in their bank account and %c%l50%x credits in their 'pocket'.  If you run out of credits in your pocket, you can easily withdraw more from your bank account (%c%lNOTE:  %xNew users cannot withdraw credit from their bank account until they have %c%l1 hour%x of total connect time.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Your 'wage'
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~
%xFor every hour you spend connected to %@%m, you will be paid %c%l25 credits%x into your bank account.  This figure doubles if you stay connected for %c%l8 or more hours%x within a single login session (Giving you '%y%l*SPOD*%x' status in the user list ('%g%l%(who%)%x'  -  See '%g%l%<who%>%x'.))

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xIdling (Not typing any commands) for over %c%l5 minutes%x does not count towards your next payment.

       %8Two or more active connections with the same character %r%lwill not%x count towards your next payment, unless all of the connections except one are idle for more than %c%l5 minutes%x.

       %8Puppets %r%ldo not%x receive hourly payments.

%PAGE

%c%l%$How to get to the bank
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lbank%]%x

Typing '%g%lbank%x' will take you to %y%lThe Bank of %@%m%x, where you can withdraw from or deposit credit into your bank account or view your bank statement.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Viewing your bank statement
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lstatement%]%x

Typing '%g%lstatement%x' in the bank will show you a statement of your account, telling you how much you have in your account, pocket and a summary of your income and expenditure over the current quarter.


%c%l%$Withdrawing credit from your bank account
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lwithdraw <AMOUNT>%]%x

You can withdraw credit from your account by typing '%g%lwithdraw%x' followed by the amount you would like to withdraw, e.g:  '%g%lwithdraw 10%x' will withdraw %y%l10 credits%x from your bank account.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Depositing credit into your bank account
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%ldeposit <AMOUNT>%]%x

To deposit credit into your account, simply type 'deposit' followed by the amount you would like to deposit, e.g:  '%g%ldeposit 100%x' will deposit %y%l100 credits%x from your pocket into your bank account.


%c%l%$Guarding against unwanted payments
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lrestrict <AMOUNT>%]%x

You can use the '%g%l%(@pay%)%x' command to build compound commands which charge for their usage.  See '%g%l%<@pay%>%x' for further details.

%PAGE
To guard against malicious users charging too much for using commands, etc. in their areas, you can set a restriction on the maximum amount you can pay to another user from within a compound command.

The default restriction is %c%l10 credits%x.  To change this restriction, simply type '%g%lrestrict%x' follwed by your preferred restriction, e.g:  '%g%lrestrict 5%x' will restrict the maximum amount you can pay from within a compound command to %y%l5 credits%x.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xThe above restriction does not apply to payments to other users performed on the command-line or payments made within compound commands which have been set %y%l%(APPRENTICE%)%x (See '%g%l%<apprentice flag%>%x') by administrators of %@%m.

       %8The restriction also does not apply to the owner of the compound command (I.e:  When they are using '%g%l%(@force%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@force%>%x') to pay out credits to other users.)

%PAGE

%r%l%$***  %y%l%f%$IMPORTANT%r%l%$  ***
%~%r~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xPlease don't ask administrators to give you credit.  They %m%lwill not%x be able to do so, except in exceptional circumstances.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<pay%>%x', '%g%l%<transfer%>%x', '%g%l%<bankcmds%>%x', '%g%l%<@credit%>%x', '%g%l%<@?credit%>%x', '%g%l%<@?balance%>%x', '%g%l%<@?income%>%x', '%g%l%<@?expenditure%>%x', '%g%l%<@?profit%>%x', '%g%l%<@?quarter%>%x', '%g%l%<@?restriction%>%x', '%g%l%<@?bank%>%x' and '%g%l%<@admin%>%x'.

