%TITLE Help on '%w%ladd%x' and '%w%laddanon%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] add[anon] <SUBJECT> [= <MESSAGE>]%]%x

The '%g%ladd%x' BBS command posts a new message with the subject %y%l<SUBJECT>%x to the topic/sub-topic you're currently browsing on the BBS.

If %y%l<MESSAGE>%x (Your message) is specified, the message will be posted to the BBS immediately.  Otherwise, %@%n Editor (See '%g%l%<editor%>%x') will be started, so you can write your message (Type it in a line at a time, and then type '%g%l%(.save%)%x' on a line by itself to exit the editor and post your message to the BBS.)

You can use '%g%laddanon%x' instead of '%g%ladd%x' to anonymously post a message to the BBS.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<editor%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs reply%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs anon%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs topic%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs allowadd%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

