%TOPIC bbsanon
%TOPIC bbsanonymous
%TITLE Help on '%w%lanon%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] anon <NUMBER>%]%x

The '%g%lanon%x' BBS command makes the message number %y%l<NUMBER>%x in the topic/sub-topic you're currently browsing on the BBS anonymous.  You can also use this BBS command to make a message of yours no-longer anonymous.

When a message is made anonymous, other users will not be able to see the identity of the user who posted the message.  To prevent abuse, Admin are able to use the '%g%l%(^bbs readanon%)%x' BBS command (See '%g%l%<bbs readanon%>%x') to read an anonymous message and reveal the identity of who posted it.

You can use the '%g%l%(^bbs addanon%)%x', '%g%l%(^bbs replyanon%)%x' and '%g%l%(^bbs appendanon%)%x' BBS commands to anonymously post, reply and append to messages respectively.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs addanon%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs replyanon%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs appendanon%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs readanon%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs topic%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs allowanon%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

