%TOPIC bbscatchup
%TITLE Help on '%w%lignore%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] ignore [<TOPIC>[/<SUBTOPIC>]]
        [bbs] ignore all%]%x

You will probably find that there are several topics/sub-topics on the BBS which you are not interested in reading the messages within.  However, if you don't read the messages, they will still appear as unread messages in '%g%l%(^bbs summary%)%x', '%g%l%(^bbs topics%)%x', etc.

You can use the '%g%lignore%x' BBS command to ignore the unread messages currently within a topic or sub-topic, or ignore every single unread message currently on the entire BBS.

When a message has been ignored, it will be marked as '%m%l(Ignored)%x' and will no-longer appear as '%m%l(*UNREAD*)%x', or in '%g%l%(^bbs summary%)%x', '%g%l%(^bbs topics%)%x', etc.

To ignore all remaining unread messages within the topic/sub-topic you're currently browsing, simply type '%g%l[bbs] ignore%x'.

%PAGE
To ignore the unread messages currently within a selected topic/sub-topic, type '%g%l[bbs] ignore <TOPIC>[/<SUBTOPIC>]%x', where %y%l<TOPIC>%x is the name of the topic, and (Optionally) %y%l<SUBTOPIC>%x is the name of the sub-topic, i.e:

%g%l%[   bbs ignore discussion/politics
   bbs ignore discussion
   bbs ignore general%]%x

To ignore all unread messages currently on the entire BBS, simply type '%g%l[bbs] ignore all%x'.

You can read messages which you have ignored by typing '%g%l%(^bbs read%) ignored%x' (This is similar to how you can read unread messages, using '%g%l%(^bbs read%) unread%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs topics%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs read%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs summary%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs latest%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

