%TOPIC latest
%TOPIC bbslatest
%TITLE Help on '%w%llatest%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] latest <TOPIC>[/<SUBTOPIC>] [= <COUNT>]
        [bbs] latest *<NAME> [= <COUNT>]
        [bbs] latest me [= <COUNT>]
        [bbs] latest%]%x

The '%g%llatest%x' BBS command lists the most recent messages posted to the BBS, along with the topic/sub-topic they're located in.

By default, the 12 most recent messages are shown, but any number up to a maximum of 60 can be shown by specifying %y%l<COUNT>%x, e.g:  '%g%llatest = 30%x' will show the 30 most recent messages posted to the BBS.

You can list the most recent messages posted in a particular topic/sub-topic by typing '%g%llatest <TOPIC>[/<SUBTOPIC>]%x', where %y%l<TOPIC>%x is the name of the topic and (Optionally) %y%l<SUBTOPIC>%x is the name of a sub-topic within that topic, e.g:  '%g%llatest news%x', '%g%llatest code updates/building%x', etc.

%PAGE
You can list the most recent messages you've posted to the BBS by typing '%g%llatest me%x'.  This is useful if you wish to review the messages you've posted recently.

You can also list the most recent messages posted by a particular character by typing '%g%llatest *<NAME>%x', where %y%l<NAME>%x is the name of the character (The '%y%l*%x' %c%lIS%x important.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<summary%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs topics%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs ignore%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

