%TOPIC bbscat
%TOPIC bbsread
%TOPIC bbsview
%TOPIC bbsmessages
%TOPIC bbsreadmessage
%TOPIC bbsviewmessage
%TITLE Help on '%w%lread%x', '%w%lview%x' and '%w%lmessages%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] read [page] <NUMBER>   [bbs] view [page] <NUMBER>
        [bbs] read unread|ignored    [bbs] view unread|ignored
        [bbs] read next|prev         [bbs] view next|prev

        [bbs] messages [page] <NUMBER>
        [bbs] messages unread|ignored
        [bbs] messages next|prev%]%x

The '%g%lread%x' (Or '%g%lview%x') BBS command is used to both list messages in your current selected topic/sub-topic and read individual messages.

To see a list of messages in your current selected topic/sub-topic, simply type '%g%lread%x' (Or '%g%lview%x'.)  If there are a lot of messages in a topic, you'll see the last full page of messages by default.  You can view the other pages of messages by typing '%g%lread page <NUMBER>%x' (Or '%g%lview page <NUMBER>%x'), where %y%l<NUMBER>%x is the number of the page you'd like to view, e.g:  '%g%lread page 1%x' will show you the first page of messages in the topic/sub-topic.

%PAGE
To read a message, simply type '%g%lread <NUMBER>%x' (Or '%g%lview <NUMBER>%x'), where %y%l<NUMBER>%x is the number of the message, e.g:  '%g%lread 43%x' will read message number %c%l43%x in your current selected topic/sub-topic.  Once you've read a message, you can type '%g%lread next%x' to read the next message in the topic/sub-topic and '%g%lread prev%x' to read the previous message.

The '%g%lread unread%x' BBS command reads the next message on the BBS which you haven't read yet (If the next unread message is in another topic/sub-topic, your current selected topic/sub-topic will be changed automatically for you.)  You can effectively use this command to read every single unread message on the BBS.

%PAGE
The '%g%lread ignored%x' BBS command reads the next unread message on the BBS which you have ignored using the 'ignore' BBS command (If the next unread message is in another topic/sub-topic, your current selected topic/sub-topic will be changed automatically for you.)

The '%g%lmessages%x' BBS command is identical to the '%g%lread%x'/'%g%lview%x' BBS commands, except that it omits (Ignores) replies to messages.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs topic%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs topics%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs ignore%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs summary%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs latest%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC bbsreplies
%TITLE Help on '%w%lreplies%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] replies <NUMBER>%]%x

The '%g%lreplies%x' BBS command lists all replies to the message %y%l<NUMBER>%x in your current selected topic/sub-topic (Including the original message, if it still exists.)

This allows you to easily find the replies to a given message, all the way back to the original message which invoked response from other users (If it still exists.)  This allows you to follow the thread right from its start, and read/find all of the replies which it generated.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs reply%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs messages%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

