%TOPIC bbsreply
%TOPIC bbsreplymessage
%TITLE Help on '%w%lreply%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] reply[anon] <NUMBER> [= <MESSAGE>]%]%x

The '%g%lreply%x' BBS command posts a reply to the message number %y%l<NUMBER>%x in the topic/sub-topic you're currently browsing on the BBS.

If %y%l<MESSAGE>%x (Your message) is specified, the reply will be posted to the BBS immediately.  Otherwise, %@%n Editor (See '%g%l%<editor%>%x') will be started, so you can write your reply to the message (Type it in a line at a time, and then type '%g%l%(.save%)%x' on a line by itself to exit the editor and add your reply to the message to the BBS.)

You can use '%g%lreplyanon%x' instead of '%g%lreply%x' to anonymously reply to a message on the BBS.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<editor%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs replies%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs add%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs messages%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs topic%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

