%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] ownertopic <TOPIC> = <OWNER>%]%x

The '%g%lownertopic%x' BBS command can be used to change the owner of topic or sub-topic on the BBS to another character (Including Mortal characters), e.g:  '%g%lownertopic clubs/new club = fred bloggs%x' will change the owner of the sub-topic '%y%lNew Club%x' in the topic '%y%lClubs%x' to the character '%y%lFred Bloggs%x'.

One use of this command is to give a Mortal user ownership of their own topic or sub-topic, which they can then be responsible for maintaining.  For example, a Mortal user may have set up a club/social group with other users, and wishes to have a sub-topic in the topic '%y%lClubs%x' for members to post messages to.

%PAGE
The owner of a topic/sub-topic has the authority to append to, delete, etc. messages left by other users (Including users of a higher rank), even if they are a Mortal user.

When giving a topic to a Mortal user, the sub-topic limit (See '%g%l%<bbs subtopiclimit%>%x') of the topic should be reduced (Or even zeroed.)  This can be done using the '%g%l%(^bbs subtopiclimit%)%x' BBS command, i.e:  '%g%l%(^bbs subtopiclimit%) <TOPIC> = 0%x' will prevent the owner of the topic from creating any sub-topics within it.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs settings%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs deletetopic%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs messagelimit%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs subtopiclimit%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

