%TITLE Help on '%w%lsubtopiclimit%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] subtopiclimit <TOPIC> = <LIMIT>%]%x

The '%g%lsubtopiclimit%x' BBS command can be used to restrict the number of sub-topics that can be created under a topic.  The default sub-topic limit is %y%l16%x, however this can be decreased or increased using the '%g%lsubtopiclimit%x' BBS command.

For example, you can increase the sub-topic limit of the topic '%y%lClubs%x' to %y%l20%x by typing '%g%lsubtopiclimit clubs = 20%x', and decrease the sub-topic limit of the topic '%y%lNews%x' to %y%l5%x by typing '%g%lsubtopiclimit news = 5%x'.

When giving a topic to a Mortal user, the sub-topic limit of the topic should be reduced (Or even zeroed.)  This can be done using the '%g%lsubtopiclimit%x' BBS command, i.e:  '%g%lsubtopiclimit <TOPIC> = 0%x' will prevent the owner of the topic from creating any sub-topics within it.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs subtopic%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs subtopics%>%x', '%g%l%<subtopics%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs settings%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

