%TOPIC bbstimelimit
%TOPIC bbsexpirytime
%TITLE Help on '%w%ltimelimit%x' (BBS)
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[bbs] timelimit <TOPIC> = <LIMIT>
        [bbs] timelimit <TOPIC> = off%]%x

The '%g%ltimelimit%x' BBS command can be used to set a time limit (Expiry time) on messages within a topic/sub-topic on the BBS.

%y%l<LIMIT>%x is the time limit (In days) of messages within the topic/sub-topic, e.g:  '%g%ltimelimit general = 30%x' will impose a time limit of %c%l30 days%x on messages in the topic '%y%lGeneral%x'.

When a time limit is set, any messages which have not been read for that number of days or greater will be automatically deleted.  Deletion takes place automatically on a daily basis.

%PAGE
This BBS command is most useful for topics/sub-topics which don't see too much activity (I.e:  Messages could remain in the topic/sub-topic for months, without being read by any further users.)  A time limit of a month or so (%y%l30 days%x) will help ensure messages in these topics/sub-topics are deleted when interest in them ceases, freeing up the memory used by the messages.

Popular topics/sub-topics don't really need a time limit, as older messages will be deleted as a result of cyclic deletion (See '%g%l%<bbs cyclic%>%x') after sufficient new messages have been posted.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs delete%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs cyclic%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs messagelimit%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs subtopiclimit%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs settings%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

