Lists the current administrators, retired administrators, %r%lExperienced Builders%x and %rAssistants%x of %@%n.

Administrators (%y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above) are there to help you with any problem or query you may have and also deal with abusive users.

%r%lExperienced Builders%x are ordinary users with exceptional building and compound command writing skills, who are a good choice if you have any building questions (Especially related to advanced building) and no %c%lWizard%x administrators are available.

%PAGE
%rAssistants%x are also ordinary users, who are prepared to give help to any user who needs it (Especially new users), however they may not necessarily have exceptional building skills (They are a good choice if you have any general questions or basic building questions and no %cDruid%x administrators are available.)

Retired administrators are past administrators who have retired from administrative duties.  Most will have good knowledge of %@%m, and will be more than willing to help you, if you ask.


%c%l%$Listing currently connected administrators/Experienced Builders/Assistants...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xTyping '%g%ladmin%x' will list all administrators, retired administrators, retired administrators, %r%lExperienced Builders%x and %rAssistants%x who are currently connected, along with their %c%lrank%x, %c%lidle time%x (If this is more than a few minutes, they may be busy or currently away from their terminal/computer) and whether they are %y%l%(HAVEN%)%x (See '%g%l%<haven flag%>%x') and/or %y%l%(QUIET%)%x (Either of these can indicate that they are currently busy and do not wish to be disturbed.)

%PAGE
Optionally, a page number can also be given, which will split the list up into pages and display the given page number (I.e:  '%g%ladmin 1%x' to display %c%lpage 1%x, '%g%ladmin 2%x' to display %c%lpage 2%x, etc.)


%c%l%$Listing every administrator/Experienced Builder/Assistant...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xTyping '%g%ladmin list%x' or '%g%ladmin all%x' will display a list of all current administrators, retired administrators, %r%lExperienced Builders%x and %rAssistants%x, regardless of whether they are currently connected or not, organised by rank.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Listing administrators/Experienced Builders/Assistants by rank...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xYou can also list every administrator, retired administrators, %r%lExperienced Builder%x or %rAssistant%x by their rank (Regardless of whether they are connected or not), by typing '%g%ladmin <RANK>%x', where %y%l<RANK>%x is their rank, which can be one of the following:

   %4%rAssistants%x, %r%lExperienced Builders%x, %rRetired Druids%x, %r%lRetired Wizards%x, %yApprentice Druids%x, %y%lApprentice Wizards%x, %cDruids%x, %c%lWizards%x, %gElder Druids%x, %g%lElder Wizards%x, %m%lDeities%x.

Optionally, a page number can also be given, which will split the list up into pages and display the given page number (I.e:  '%g%ladmin assistants 1%x' to display %c%lpage 1%x of current %rAssistants%x, '%g%ladmin assistants 2%x' to display %c%lpage 2%x, etc.)

%8%c%lNOTE:  %x%(Puppets%) (See '%g%l%<@controller%>%x') and %(Beings%) (See '%g%l%<being flag%>%x') are omitted from the administrators, retired administrators, %r%lExperienced Builders%x and %rAssistants%x listed by '%g%ladmin list%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<assist%>%x', '%g%l%<assistants%>%x', '%g%l%<experienced builders%>%x', '%g%l%<apprentices%>%x', '%g%l%<druids%>%x', '%g%l%<wizards%>%x', '%g%l%<elders%>%x', '%g%l%<deities%>%x' and '%g%l%<being flag%>%x'.

