        %g%l{@?isupper "<STRING>"}    %c-  %m%lUppercase %m(%y%lA%m-%y%lZ%m)%]%x

The above queries test the text character class of a string as indicated above.  For example, '%g%l{@?alpha}%x' or '%g%l{@?isalpha}%x' tests %y%l<STRING>%x to see if it contains alphabetical (%g%la%x-%g%lz%x, %g%lA%x-%g%lZ%x) characters only.  If it does, %c%lsuccess%x and %y%l<STRING>%x is returned, otherwise %c%lfailure%x and '%y%lError%x' is returned.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xThe '%y%lis%x' is optional on all of the above query commands except for '%g%l{@?islower}%x' and '%g%l{@?isupper}%x'.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Example:
