%TOPIC @?averagelogins
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@?averagelogins%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?averagelogins [<NAME>]}%]%x

Returns the average time in seconds between the character %y%l<NAME>%x's logins to %@%m, e.g:  '%g%l%(@echo%) {%(@?interval%) {@?averagelogins me}}%x' will display the average time between your logins.

Average time between logins is worked out by dividing the time between now and when a character was created by their total number of logins.

Fails and returns '%c%lError%x' if the character %y%l<NAME>%x can't be found.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@?totallogins%>%x', '%g%l%<@?interval%>%x', '%g%l%<@?time%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?created%>%x'.

