Average active time is worked out by dividing total active time (See '%g%l%<@?totalactive%>%x') by total number of logins (See '%g%l%<@?totallogins%>%x'.)

Fails and returns '%c%lError%x' if the character %y%l<NAME>%x can't be found.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@?averageidle%>%x', '%g%l%<@?averagetime%>%x', '%g%l%<@?totalactive%>%x', '%g%l%<@?totalidle%>%x', '%g%l%<@?totaltime%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?interval%>%x'.

