%TOPIC @?peak
%TITLE Help on '%w%l{@?peak}%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?peak [current|today|average|record]}%]%x

If no parameters or '%y%ltoday%x' is specified, the highest number of users connected simultaneously today will be returned.

If '%y%lcurrent%x' is specified, the current number of connected users will be returned.

If '%y%laverage%x' is specified, the average daily peak (Over the last two weeks) will be returned.

If '%y%lrecord%x' is specified, the record number of users connected simultaneously will be returned.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Example:
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@echo%) There are currently {@?peak current} users connected.
%(@echo%) The highest peak today is {@?peak today} users.
%(@echo%) The average daily peak is {@?peak average} users.
%(@echo%) The record peak is {@?peak record} users.%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@?uptime%>%x'.

