%TOPIC datestamps
%TOPIC timestamps
%TOPIC creationtimes
%TOPIC creationdates
%TOPIC lastusedtimes
%TOPIC lastuseddates
%TOPIC lastusagetimes
%TOPIC lastusagedates
%TITLE Help on object creation and last usage times/dates
Every object in %@%n has a date stamp, which records the date and time when the object was created and the time and date when it was last used.

You can view the date stamps of an object by examining it using either the '%g%l%(examine%)%x' (See '%g%l%<examine%>%x') or '%g%l%(settings%)%x' (See '%g%l%<settings%>%x') commands.

The '%g%l%(@list%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@list%>%x') and '%g%l%(@find%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@find%>%x') commands can be used to list/search for objects based on their creation and/or last usage date.

The last usage time/date of an object is updated everytime its text fields (I.e:  '%g%l%(@desc%)%x', '%g%l%(@succ%)%x', '%g%l%(@fail%)%x', etc.) or its lock are accessed/modified (%c%lNOTE:  %xExamining an object or scanning a character does not update the last usage time/date.)

%PAGE
%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xAny objects/characters in the database created before TCZ v4.1 will have the same creation and last usage time/date as when TCZ was upgraded to version 4.1, because versions of TCZ prior to v4.1 did not record the time and date when objects were created/last used.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<examine%>%x', '%g%l%<settings%>%x', '%g%l%<@list%>%x', '%g%l%<@find%>%x', '%g%l%<@?created%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?lastused%>%x'.

