%COMMENT -------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC colormaps
%TOPIC @?colormap
%TOPIC colourmaps
%TOPIC @?colourmap
%TITLE Help on '%w%l{@?colourmap}%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?colourmap "<MAP>" "<TEXT>"}%]%x

Applies a string of colour codes (Similar to %c%l%(substitutions%)%x (See '%g%l%<substitutions%>%x')) to a string of text.  This is especially useful for ASCII art or complex colour sequences which can make the text to which they add colour too difficult to edit.  The same code used for '%g%l{@?colourmap}%x' is used to add colour to %@%m's map (See '%g%l%<map%>%x'.)

%y%l<MAP>%x is the list of colour map codes, which will be applied to their respective characters in the string %y%l<TEXT>%x in order.  If %y%l<MAP>%x is shorter than %y%l<TEXT>%x, the sequence in %y%l<MAP>%x will be repeated from the start as many times as necessary.  To prevent repetition, include a '%g%l!%x' in %y%l<MAP>%x.

%y%l<TEXT>%x is the string which the colour map codes in %y%l<MAP>%x will be applied to, in order.

%PAGE

%c%l%$The following colour map codes can be used:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%g%lz  %wDark %z%i%wBlack%x     %g%lZ  %w%lLight %z%lBlack     %g%l0  %x%i%zBlack%w Background     %g%ld  %wDark%x
%g%lr  %wDark %rRed       %g%lR  %w%lLight %r%lRed       %g%l1  %x%i%rRed%w Background       %g%ll  %w%lLight%x
%g%lg  %wDark %gGreen     %g%lG  %w%lLight %g%lGreen     %g%l2  %x%i%gGreen%w Background     %g%lf  %w%fFlashing%x
%g%ly  %wDark %yYellow    %g%lY  %w%lLight %y%lYellow    %g%l3  %x%i%yYellow%w Background    %g%lu  %w%uUnderline%x
%g%lb  %wDark %bBlue      %g%lB  %w%lLight %b%lBlue      %g%l4  %x%i%bBlue%w Background      %g%lx  %xDefault
%g%lm  %wDark %mMagenta   %g%lM  %w%lLight %m%lMagenta   %g%l5  %x%i%mMagenta%w Background%x
%g%lc  %wDark %cCyan      %g%lC  %w%lLight %c%lCyan      %g%l6  %x%i%cCyan%w Background      %g%l#  %y%lComment%x
%g%lw  %wDark %wWhite     %g%lW  %w%lLight %w%lWhite     %g%l7  %x%i%wWhite%w Background     %g%l!  %r%lNo repeat%]%x

%PAGE
%c%l%8NOTE:  %xColour codes are %c%lcase sensitive%x.

       %8'%g%l#%x' is used for comments in %y%l<TEXT>%x, replacing the corresponding characters with a space (' '.)

       %8'%g%l!%x' prevents repetition if %y%l<MAP>%x is shorter than %y%l<TEXT>%x.


%c%l%$Examples:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~
%g%l%(@echo%) {@?colourmap "RGYBMC" "Some very colourful text."}
%g%l%(@echo%) {@?colourmap "RrYy x!" "Only the first word will be coloured."}
%4%g%l%(@echo%) {@?colourmap "zrgybmcwZRGYBMCW01234567xldfu" "zrgybmcwZRGYBMCW01234567xldfu"}
%g%l%(@echo%) {@?colourmap "RRRR ####### GGGG" "Some Comment Text"}
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<ansi%>%x', '%g%l%<substitutions%>%x', '%g%l%<map%>%x' and '%g%l%<advanced queries%>%x'.

