%TOPIC @?desc
%TOPIC @?describe
%TOPIC @?description
%TITLE Help on '%w%l{@?desc}%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?desc <ARRAY>[<ELEMENT>]}
        {@?desc <OBJECT>}%]%x

Returns the description of %y%l<OBJECT>%x.

'%g%l{@?desc}%x' can also be used to return the description (Or contents if you like) of a dynamic array element (Or a range of elements), e.g:  '%g%l{@?desc myarray[2]}%x' returns the description of the %c%l2nd%x element of the dynamic array '%y%lmyarray%x' and '%g%l{@?desc myarray[test]}%x' returns the description of the element with the index name '%y%ltest%x' of '%y%lmyarray%x'.

If a range of elements is specified, the descriptions of these elements will be returned, separated by %c%lNEWLINE%x's, e.g:  '%g%l{@?desc myarray[4..7]}%x' will return the descriptions of elements %c%l4%x, %c%l5%x, %c%l6%x and %c%l7%x of the dynamic array '%y%lmyarray%x'.

Fails and returns '%c%lError%x' if %y%l<OBJECT>%x or %y%l<ARRAY>%x can't be found.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@desc%>%x', '%g%l%<@odesc%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?odesc%>%x'.

