%TOPIC @?destination
%TITLE Help on '%w%l{@?destination}%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?destination [<OBJECT>]}%]%x

If %y%l<OBJECT>%x is a character or a thing, %g%l{@?destination}%x returns the name (Or ID if you control %y%l<OBJECT>%x) of the character's/thing's home location.

If %y%l<OBJECT>%x is an exit, %g%l{@?destination}%x returns the name/ID of the room where you'll end up if you go through the exit.

If %y%l<OBJECT>%x is a room, %g%l{@?destination}%x returns the name/ID of its dropto room.

Fails and returns '%c%lError%x' if %y%l<OBJECT>%x can't be found.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@link%>%x'.

