%TOPIC @damage
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@damage%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@damage <NAME> = <ACCURACY> <MIN DAMAGE> <MAX DAMAGE> <DELAY> <SCORE>%]%x


This command can only be used from within a compound command with its %y%l%(COMBAT%)%x flag set (See '%g%l%<combat flag%>%x'), in a location which also has its %y%l%(COMBAT%)%x flag set.  Both must be owned by the same character.

'%g%l@damage%x' attempts to damage the character %y%l<NAME>%x.  Whether it succeeds or not is determined by %y%l<ACCURACY>%x, which is a percentage (Out of %c%l100%x.)  The lower this percentage, the more likely '%g%l@damage%x' will fail and return '%c%lMISS%x'.

If '%g%l@damage%x' succeeds, the victim will lose a random amount of health between %y%l<MIN DAMAGE>%x and %y%l<MAX DAMAGE>%x.  If the victim survives, '%g%l@damage%x' will succeed and return '%c%lHIT%x', otherwise the attacker will be awarded %y%l<SCORE>%x points, the victim will lose 2/3rds of %y%l<SCORE>%x from their current score and '%g%l@damage%x' will succeed and return '%c%lKILL%x'.

%PAGE
Whether '%g%l@damage%x' is successful or not, the attacker will not be able to fight again (I.e:  Use '%g%l@damage%x') for %y%l<DELAY>%x seconds.  When a character is still subject to a combat delay, '%g%l@damage%x' returns '%c%lDELAY%x'.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %x'%g%l@damage%x' cannot be used on yourself if you own the compound command or location in which it is used, or the character %y%l<NAME>%x is not in the same location as you.  These restrictions can be removed by setting %y%l%(WIZARD%)%x or %y%l%(ELDER%)%x flags on the combat commands respectively (See '%g%l%<wizard flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<elder flag%>%x'.)

       %8Score is not awarded unless an %y%l%(APPRENTICE%)%x, %y%l%(WIZARD%)%x or %y%l%(ELDER%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<apprentice flag%>%x', '%g%l%<wizard flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<elder flag%>%x') is set on the compound command containing the '%g%l@damage%x' command.

       %8Battles won, lost and score %c%lare not%x updated if you are the owner of the compound command containing the '%g%l@damage%x' command.  This is to prevent the owner of a combat area from cheating to improve their performance or score.

%PAGE
       %8Combat can only take place in locations which have their %y%l%(COMBAT%)%x flag set and do not have their %y%l%(HAVEN%)%x flag set (See '%g%l%<combat flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<haven flag%>%x'.)

Some of the parameters of '%g%l@damage%x' may be subject to restrictions, depending on flags set on the compound command(s):


%[               %r%lCOMBAT   %y%lAPPRENTICE   %c%lWIZARD   %g%lELDER
%c%lParameter:     %r%lflag:    %y%lflag:        %c%lflag:    %g%lflag:
%c===================================================
%w%l<ACCURACY>     %r%l60       %y%l80           %c%l100      %g%l100
%w%l<MIN DAMAGE>   %r%l50       %y%l75           %c%l100      %g%l1000
%w%l<MAX DAMAGE>   %r%l50       %y%l75           %c%l100      %g%l1000
%w%l<DELAY>        %r%l30       %y%l45           %c%l60       %g%l60
%w%l<SCORE>        %r%l100      %y%l500          %c%l1000     %g%l10000
%c===================================================%]
%c
%PAGE

%[%c%lReturn string:   Description:
%c=======================================================================
%y%lMISS             %xAttacker missed.
%y%lHIT              %xAttacker hit victim, but victim didn't die.
%y%lKILL             %xAttacker hit victim and killed them.
%y%lDELAY            %xAttacker is still subject to combat delay.
%y%lError            %xCharacter %y%l<NAME>%x doesn't exist, isn't connected, isn't
                 in the same room, or no/invalid parameters given to
                 '%g%l@damage%x'.
%c=======================================================================
%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %y%l$0%x holds the return result of the last command executed.%]
%c
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@heal%>%x', '%g%l%<@delay%>%x', '%g%l%<substitutions%>%x', '%g%l%<combat flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<combat%>%x'.

