%TOPIC @?match
%TITLE Help on '%w%l{@?match}%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?match[error] <OBJECT NAME> [= <PREFERRED TYPES>]}%]%x

'%g%l{@?match}%x' calls %@%m's standard hierarchical object matching routines to match for the object %y%l<OBJECT NAME>%x.  If found, the object's name (Or #ID if you have read or write permission) is returned.  Otherwise, '%y%lError%x' is returned.

'%g%l{@?match}%x' will display appropriate error messages if the match is unsuccessful.  '%g%l{@?matcherror}%x' does not display appropriate error messages (The usage of '%g%l{@?match}%x' and '%g%l{@?matcherror}%x' are identical.)

With the exception of internal commands which can be used to refer to characters only, all internal commands which refer to objects use the hierarchical object matching routines in one way or another.

%PAGE
For details on specifying %y%l<OBJECT NAME>%x, see '%g%l%<matching%>%x'.

%y%l<PREFERRED TYPES>%x specifies one or more optional preferred object types to match against.  Preferred object types are matched first, followed by any remaining non-preferred types.  By default, the preferred object type is '%y%lthings%x' (This is the case for many internal %@%m commands which use matching.)  For example, '%g%l{@?match <OBJECT NAME> = characters}%x' will match against all object types, giving %c%lcharacters%x priority.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, '%g%l%<matching%>%x' and '%g%l%<matching order%>%x'.

%COMMENT -------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @?mass
%TITLE Help on '%w%l{@?mass}%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?mass <OBJECT>}%]%x

Returns the mass of %y%l<OBJECT>%x in kilograms.

Fails and returns '%c%lError%x' if %y%l<OBJECT>%x can't be found.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@mass%>%x', '%g%l%<@volume%>%x', '%g%l%<@?volume%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?weight%>%x'.

