%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?messages <TOPIC>}%]%x

Returns the total number of messages in the topic %y%l<TOPIC>%x on %@%n BBS.

Fails and returns '%c%lError%x' if the topic %y%l<TOPIC>%x doesn't exist, or you can't access it.


%c%l%$Example:
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@echo%) There are {%(@?messages%) news} items of news on the BBS.%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs%>%x', '%g%l%<@?newmessages%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?latest%>%x'.

