If the character %y%l<NAME>%x isn't specified, your payment restriction is returned, otherwise the payment restriction of the character %y%l<NAME>%x is returned.

For more information about restricting payments, please see '%g%l%<bank%>%x' (%c%lThe Bank of %@%m%x.)

Fails and returns '%c%lError%x' if the character %y%l<NAME>%x can't be found.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bank%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------

%TOPIC @?result
%TITLE Help on '%w%l{@?result}%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?result <VALUE> = "<TRUE>" "<FALSE>"}%]%x

Depending on the result %y%l<VALUE>%x, '%g%l{@?result}%x' returns either the text specified for %y%l<TRUE>%x or %y%l<FALSE>%x.

If %y%l<VALUE>%x is '%y%l0%x' or '%y%lError%x', the text %y%l<FALSE>%x will be returned, otherwise the text %y%l<TRUE>%x will be returned.


%c%l%$Examples:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~
%g%l%[%(@echo%) This room is{@?result {%(@?set%) here = %(abode%)} = "" " not"} set %(ABODE%).
%(@echo%) There {@?result {%(@eval%) {%(@?totalitems%) things here} = 1} = "is" "are"}
      {%(@?totalitems%) things here} thing{@?result {%(@eval%) {%(@?totalitems%) things
      here} = 1} = "" "s"} in your current location.%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@eval%>%x', '%g%l%<@?set%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?totalitems%>%x'.

