%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?realtime [<DATE>] [= [epoch|longdate] [full|date|long|short|time]}
        {@?realtime [<DATE>] [= [epoch|longdate] = <FORMAT>}%]%x

Converts the date/time (Stored in either the %c%lEPOCH%x (See '%g%l%<epoch%>%x') or %c%lLONGDATE%x (See '%g%l%<longdate%>%x') date/time format) into a readable format such as '%y%l%{@?realtime}%x' (Based on your preferred format, which can be set using the '%g%l%(@dateformat%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@dateformat%>%x'.))

If %y%l<DATE>%x is omitted, the current system date/time will be returned, taking your time difference into account.  Otherwise, the %c%lEXACT%x date/time %y%l<DATE>%x is returned, %c%lWITHOUT%x your time difference being taken into account.

By default, the %c%lEPOCH%x date/time format is assumed.  If '%y%llongdate%x' is specified, %y%l<DATE>%x will be treated as a date stored in the %c%lLONGDATE%x date format.  Please see '%g%l%<epoch%>%x' and '%g%l%<longdate%>%x' for more information on the %c%lEPOCH%x and %c%lLONGDATE%x date/time formats.

%PAGE
If '%y%ldate%x' or '%y%llong%x' is specified, %y%l<DATE>%x will be converted as a %c%llong format date%x only, otherwise if '%y%lshort%x' is specified, %y%l<DATE>%x will be converted as a %c%lshort format date%x only.

If '%y%ltime%x' is specified, %y%l<DATE>%x will be converted as a %c%ltime%x only.  If none of these are specified, or if '%y%lfull%x' is specified, %y%l<DATE>%x will be converted as %c%lfull date and time%x.

For more information on the %c%lEPOCH%x and %c%lLONGDATE%x date/time formats, please see '%g%l%<epoch%>%x' and '%g%l%<longdate%>%x'.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xTCZ is %y%lYear 2000%x complient (Y2K) because all dates stored internally use either the %c%lEPOCH%x or %c%lLONGDATE%x format.

%PAGE
Alternatively, a custom %y%l<FORMAT>%x may be specified, overriding the default preferred date format (See '%g%l%<@dateformat%>%x') of the character calling '%g%l{@?realtime}%x'.  For this reason, %y%l<FORMAT>%x should only be used in special cases, where you do not wish to display a full date and/or time (It is used within the '%g%l%(@dateformat%)%x' help pages to display an example for each formatting code, based on the current time/date.)

You should not force a specific date format, because other users from other countries may not use or understand the same date format as you.  '%g%l{@?realtime}%x' used without %y%l<FORMAT>%x will display the date/time in the preferred format choosen by the user.

For information on how to set your preferred time and date formats, please see '%g%l%<@dateformat%>%x'.  The same format codes can also be specified for %y%l<FORMAT>%x.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Examples:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@echo%) {@?realtime}
%(@echo%) {@?realtime {%(@?created%) me}}
%(@echo%) {@?realtime {%(@?profile%) me = birthday} = %(longdate%)}
%(@echo%) {@?realtime {%(@?datetime%) 01/01/00}}
%(@echo%) {@?realtime {%(@?time%)} = %(epoch%) = WW MM}%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@dateformat%>%x', '%g%l%<@?datetime%>%x', '%g%l%<@?interval%>%x', '%g%l%<@?time%>%x', '%g%l%<@?timediff%>%x', '%g%l%<epoch%>%x', '%g%l%<longdate%>%x', '%g%l%<@profile%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?created%>%x'.

