%TITLE Help on the %w%lLONGDATE%x date format
The %c%lLONGDATE%x format is a flexible date format used by %@%m to represent any date between %y%l1st January 0001%x and %y%l31st December 9999%x.  Unlike the %c%lEPOCH%x (See '%g%l%<epoch%>%x') format, the %c%lLONGDATE%x format cannot represent time, however it can support a considerably greater range of dates than the %c%lEPOCH%x format (For example, it's used internally to represent each character's date of birth (See '%g%l%<@profile%>%x'.))

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xTCZ is %y%lYear 2000%x complient (Y2K) because all dates stored internally use either the %c%lEPOCH%x or %c%lLONGDATE%x format.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<epoch%>%x', '%g%l%<@?realtime%>%x', '%g%l%<@?interval%>%x', '%g%l%<@?datetime%>%x', '%g%l%<@?time%>%x', '%g%l%<@?timediff%>%x' and '%g%l%<@profile%>%x'.

