The %c%lEPOCH%x format is a standard date/time format used on UNIX systems, which can represent any date and time between %y%lFriday 13th December 1901, 8:45.52 pm%x and %y%l19th January 2038, 3:14.07%x.  The %c%lEPOCH%x format is used internally throughout %@%m to represent dates and times (E.g:  Object creation/last usage dates/times (See '%g%l%<date stamps%>%x'), character total connect time, etc.)

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xTCZ is %y%lYear 2000%x complient (Y2K) because all dates stored internally use either the %c%lEPOCH%x or %c%lLONGDATE%x format.
