%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l{@?replace "<SEARCHSTR>" "<REPLACESTR>" [+]<OCCURENCE> "<STRING>"}%]%x

'%g%l{@?replace}%x' replaces the specified %y%l<OCCURENCE>%x of %y%l<SEARCHSTR>%x with %y%l<REPLACESTR>%x within the string of text %y%l<STRING>%x.

For %y%l<OCCURENCE>%x, an occurence number can be given (I.e:  '%y%l2%x' for the %c%lsecond%x occurence, '%y%l3%x' for the %c%lthird%x, etc.), or one of the keywords '%y%lFIRST%x', '%y%lLAST%x' or '%y%lALL%x' (Replace %c%lALL%x occurences within %y%l<STRING>%x.)  If %y%l<OCCURENCE>%x is prefixed with a '%y%l+%x', the given %y%l<OCCURENCE>%x will be replaced on %c%lEVERY%x line of %y%l<STRING>%x.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.replace%>%x' and '%g%l%<advanced queries%>%x'.

