%TOPIC limits
%TOPIC @admin
%TOPIC restrictions
%TOPIC @administration
%TOPIC @administrativeoptions
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@admin%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin [<OPTION> [=] <SETTING>]
        @admin options [<OPTION> [[=] <SETTING>]]%]%x

The '%g%l@admin%x' command (Which may only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above) is used to view/adjust various parameters of %@%m.  Typing '%g%l@admin%x' without any parameters displays all '%g%l@admin%x' options and their current settings.

'%g%l@admin options%x' displays the current server options given to %@%m at start-up either on the command-line or from within a configuration file.  Some of these can be %c%ltemporarily changed%x while %@%m is running by %m%lDeities%x and the %m%lSupreme Being%x (Using '%g%l@admin option <OPTION> [[=] <SETTING>]%x'.)  (%c%lNOTE:  %r%lDO NOT %xchange these options unless you know %y%l%u*exactly*%x what you are doing.)


%c%l%$Database dumping status%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~%x
When the database is being dumped to disk, this field will show you its progress so far, e.g:  '%g%lDatabase dumping status:  %w%l9032/40142 objects dumped.%x'

%PAGE

%c%l%$Database dumping duration%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~%x
This field is a summary of the time taken to dump the database to disk  -  The minimum, average and maximum times are shown (In that order) in hours, minutes and seconds.


%c%l%$Time until next dump%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~%x
When the database isn't being dumped to disk, this field will show the amount of time remaining before the next database dump starts.


%c%l%$Server shutdown%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~%x
If server shutdown has been started (Using the '%g%l%(@shutdown%)%x' command), this field will show the amount of time remaining before %@%m will shutdown.

%c%lNOTE:  %xServer shutdown can be cancelled by typing '%g%l%(@shutdown%) cancel%x'.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Database dumping interval%g%l               (Elder Wizards/%gDruids %g%land above only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin dumping [=] <TIME IN MINUTES>%]%x

This option is the amount of time (In minutes) between database dumps to disk.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xThe database can be forcefully dumped to disk using the '%g%l%(@dump%)%x' command (However, this should only ever be done in an emergency.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Data dumped per cycle%m%l                    (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin data [=] <SIZE IN KILOBYTES>%]%x

This option is the amount of database data (In kilobytes) which will be dumped to disk in a single dump cycle.

The higher this setting, the faster database dumps will be completed.  However, setting this value too high will result in the operating system's disk cache getting swamped, and %@%n lagging while it tries to catch up.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xThis option does not affect the forked database dump.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Dump cycle interval%m%l                      (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin cycle [=] <TIME IN SECONDS>%]%x

This option is the amount of time (In seconds) between each database dump cycle (Once the database dump has started.)

The lower this setting, the faster database dumps will be completed.  However, setting this value too low will result in the operating system's disk cache getting swamped, and the game lagging while it tries to catch up.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xThis option does not affect the forked database dump.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Limit maximum connections%g%l               (Elder Wizards/%gDruids %g%land above only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin limit [=] yes|no%]%x

When set to '%y%lyes%x', the maximum number of users simultaneously connected to %@%n at any one time will be limited to the number set with the '%y%lConnections %g%lallowed%x' option.

If the maximum number of users is reached or exceeded (When this option is set to '%y%lyes%x'), only %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above will be able to connect until the number of connected users drops below the limit again.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Connections allowed%g%l                     (Elder Wizards/%gDruids %g%land above only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin allowed [=] <LIMIT>%]%x

This option is the maximum number of users which can be simultaneously connected at any one time.  For this restriction to take any effect, '%y%lLimit %g%lmaximum connections%x' must be set to '%y%lyes%x'.


%c%l%$Home rooms container%m%l                     (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin homes [=] #<ID>%]%x

This option is the #ID of the room which the %c%lhome rooms%x (See '%g%l%<home%>%x' and '%g%l%<@homeroom%>%x') of users will be stored in.  It can not be accessed publicly (However, administrators can teleport (See '%g%l%<@teleport%>%x' and '%g%l%<to%>%x') there of course, if necessary.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Allow user creations%g%l                    (Elder Wizards/%gDruids%g%l and above only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin creations [=] yes|guests|no%]%x

This option determines whether new users may be created (This excludes new users created by administrators using the '%g%l%(@character%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@character%>%x'.))

If this restriction is set '%y%lno%x', no new users can be created, and no Guest characters may be connected.  If it's set to '%y%lguests%x', only Guest characters may be connected.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Allow user connections%m%l                   (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin connections [=] yes|no%]%x

This option determines whether non-administators will be able to connect to %@%m.  If this restriction is set to '%y%lno%x', only %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above will be able to connect.


%c%l%$Bank access room%m%l                         (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin bank [=] #<ID>%]%x

This option is the #ID of the room from which %c%lThe Bank of %@%m%x (See '%g%l%<bank%>%x') can be accessed, where users will be able to withdraw from and deposit credit into their bank account.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Mail access room%m%l                         (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin mail [=] #<ID>%]%x

This option is the #ID of the room from which the %c%linternal mail system%x (See '%g%l%<mail%>%x') can be accessed.


%c%l%$BBS access room%m%l                          (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin bbs [=] #<ID>%]%x

This option is the #ID of the room from which %c%l%@%n BBS%x (See '%g%l%<bbs%>%x') can be accessed.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Time adjustment%y%l                         (Apprentice Wizards/%yDruids %y%land above)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin time [=] [+/-] <TIME ADJUSTMENT>%]%x

This option is the time adjustment from the system time of the server machine %@%n is running on.  It allows adjustments to be made to the server time (Time on %@%n, %c%lNOT%x the server machine) to be made (If the system time is incorrect) without affecting %@%n up-time, idle and login times of connected users, database dumping timings, etc.

For example, if the server time was 4 minutes behind, you could type '%g%l@admin time = +4 minutes%x' to correct it, and if it was 23 minutes fast, you could type '%g%l@admin time = -23 minutes%x'.  You can also use any other interval of time if you like (E.g:  '%y%lseconds%x', '%y%lhours%x', etc.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Global Aliases%m%l                                           (Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin global [= <NAME>]%]%x

This option allows the %m%lSupreme Being%x to set the owner of global aliases (See '%g%l%<@alias%>%x' for information about aliases.)  Once set, all aliases of the global aliases owner will be global to every user of %@%m (Even from within compound commands.)

Global aliases are matched after user-defined aliases, so a user can override a global alias if they wish to do so by defining an alias with the same name.

Global aliases are a %r%lhigh security risk%x, so only the %m%lSupreme Being%x may set this option.  The global aliases owner should ideally be a Deity, and only the %m%lSupreme Being%x should know their password.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Maintenance%m%l                              (Deities and the Supreme Being only)
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin maintenance [=] on|off%]%x

When set to '%y%lyes%x', unused characters and objects will be destroyed on a weekly basis.  Maintenance helps keep the database free of redundant characters and objects which will probably never be used again.

Any character or object which couldn't be destroyed by maintenance (E.g:  A Builder who has objects locked to them, an object used in the lock of another object, etc.) will have its %y%l%(ASHCAN%)%x flag set (You can use '%g%l%(@list%) all = ashcanned characters%x' or '%g%l%(@list%) all = ashcanned%x' to list them.)

%8%c%lNOTE:  %m%lDeities%x and the %m%lSupreme Being%x may use the '%g%l%(@maintenance%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@maintenance%>%x') command to manually start %y%lcharacter%x, %y%lobject%x, %y%lmail%x or %y%lBBS%x maintenance.

%PAGE
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin owner [=] <OWNER>%]%x

This option is the character who will take over the ownership of objects which were owned by characters destroyed by maintenance.  This character will also take over the ownership of any objects owned by characters destroyed using the '%g%l%(@destroy%)%x' command.

%PAGE
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@admin builders [=] <UNUSED TIME>|off
        @admin newbies [=] <UNUSED TIME>|off
        @admin mortals [=] <UNUSED TIME>|off
        @admin objects [=] <UNUSED TIME>|off
        @admin morons [=] <UNUSED TIME>|off
        @admin junk [=] <UNUSED TIME>|off%]%x

These options are the times (In days) after which unused Mortal characters of each type (%b%lMorons%x, newbies (Characters who have less than %c%l1 day%x's total connect time), Mortals and Builders) and unused/junked objects/objects with their %y%l%(ASHCAN%)%x flag set will be destroyed.  Maintenance on each of the above character types and objects may be optionally turned off, if the parameter '%y%loff%x' is given instead of a time (In days.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<character expiry%>%x', '%g%l%<junked objects%>%x', '%g%l%<ashcan flag%>%x', '%g%l%<date stamps%>%x' and '%g%l%<@maintenance%>%x'.

