%TOPIC @censor
%TOPIC @censored
%TOPIC @censorship
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@censor%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@censor%]%x

This command can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above from within a compound command.

%@%m remembers the last command typed by every user who is currently logged on.  This allows you to recall (Execute) the last command you typed (By typing '%g%l%(!!%)%x'  -  See '%g%l%<!!%>%x') and Admin to list the last command typed by every user (Or a particular user), using the '%g%l%(last%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<last%>%x'.)  This facility enables Admin to help new users (By being able to see what they are doing wrong.)

To prevent invasion of privacy, all built-in communication commands (I.e:  '%g%l%(say%)%x', '%g%l%(page%)%x', '%g%l%(tell%)%x', etc.) are censored, so that Admin %c%lCAN'T%x 'snoop' on the private conversations of users.

%PAGE
However, user-created custom communications commands (I.e:  Constructed with compound commands) are not subject to censorship by default, and will appear in the '%g%l%(last%)%x' commands listing.

If '%g%l@censor%x' is placed at the beginning of a compound command (Or linked sequence of compound commands), use of the compound command will be censored in the '%g%l%(last%)%x' commands listing, allowing complete guaranteed privacy for its users.

If the editor (See '%g%leditor%x') is started from a compound command, and '%g%l@censor%x' is executed before the compound command finishes, the edit session will be censored (With the exception of executing a command, using '%g%l%(.execute%)%x' or '%g%l%(.x%)%x', unless it's normally censored on the command-line.)

'%g%l@censor%x' may be used from within a Mortal owned compound command, providing it either has its %y%l%(APPRENTICE%)%x or %y%l%(WIZARD%)%x flag set.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<!!%>%x', '%g%l%<last%>%x', '%g%l%<edit%>%x', '%g%l%<@?lastcommand%>%x', '%g%l%<apprentice flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<wizard flag%>%x'.

