%TOPIC @character
%TOPIC creatingplayers
%TOPIC creatingcharacters
%TOPIC creatingnewplayers
%TOPIC creatingnewcharacters
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@character%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@character <NAME> = <PASSWORD>%]%x

This command can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

'%g%l@character%x' creates a new character with the name %y%l<NAME>%x and password %y%l<PASSWORD>%x.  The main use of this command is to allow %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above to create a character for new users who can't create one themselves at the login screen (Due to their site being prevented from creating characters, due to abuse, etc.)

'%g%l@character%x' can't be used from within a compound command.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@request%>%x' and '%g%l%<@site%>%x'.

