%TOPIC @output
%TOPIC suppressoutput
%TOPIC suppressingoutput
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@output%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@output on|off%]%x

This command can only be used from within a compound command.

'%g%l@output%x' is used to turn output on or off within a compound command.  When output is turned off, the output from any command executed will not be displayed on the user's screen.


%c%l%$Example:
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l@output off
%(scan%) me
@output on
%(@echo%) I just scanned myself.%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@command%>%x', '%g%l%<scan%>%x' and '%g%l%<@echo%>%x'.

