%TOPIC @owner
%TOPIC @chown
%TOPIC ownership
%TOPIC changingownership
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@owner%x' (Or '%w%l@chown%x')
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@owner <OBJECT> = me|*<NAME>
        @owner *<NAME> = *<NAME>%]%x

The '%g%l@owner%x' (Or '%g%l@chown%x') command is used to change the ownership of an object to yourself ('%g%l@owner <OBJECT> = me%x') or another character ('%g%l@owner <OBJECT> = *<NAME>%x'  -  You must be a %c%lWizard/%cDruid%x or above to do this.)

%y%l<OBJECT>%x must have its %y%l%(TRANSFERABLE%)%x flag set for you to be able to take over its ownership (Unless you're a %c%lWizard/%cDruid%x or above.)  You must also have sufficient Building Quota, as the Building Quota used by the object will be transfered to you.

The second form ('%g%l@owner *<NAME> = *<NAME>%x') can be used by %c%lWizards/%cDruids%x and above to transfer all of a character's objects, mail and BBS messages/topics to another character.  As a safe-guard, the character must be set %y%l%(ASHCAN%)%x before this can be done.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<transferable flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<ashcan flag%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @chpid
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@chpid%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@chpid%]%x

This command can only be used within a compound command.

When used in a compound command, '%g%l@chpid%x' gives the person who executed the compound command the privileges of the owner of the compound command.

Privileges picked up through '%g%l@chpid%x' remain in effect until the compound command finishes executing or when another compound command is called (Either via the '%g%l%(@csucc%)%x'/'%g%l%(@cfail%)%x' links (See '%g%l%<@csucc%>%x' and '%g%l%<@cfail%>%x') or from within the compound command itself.)  Privileges picked up through '%g%l@chpid%x' can also be cancelled out by using the '%g%l%(@unchpid%)%x' command.

You'll find you need to use an '%g%l@chpid%x' at the beginning of any compound command that modifies objects you own, references objects you own by ID number or gets the contents of various fields via query commands (E.g:  '%g%l{%(@?drop%) <OBJECT>}%x'.

%PAGE
%8%c%lNOTE:  %xWhen a character executes a compound command that is not owned by themselves, write permission from within the compound command will be denied to both the character and their objects unless the %y%l%(APPRENTICE%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<apprentice flag%>%x') is set on the compound command, or it is owned by an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above.  This safe-guards users against malicious 'trojan' compound commands created by %(Builders%), which otherwise could alter their character and/or objects without their permission.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xUnless it has its %y%l%(WIZARD%)%x flag set (See '%g%l%<wizard flag%>%x'), a compound command will automatically '%g%l@chpid%x' (Even if omitted) to its owner if the compound command is an %c%l%(area command%)%x (E.g:  '%g%l%(.enter%)%x', see '%g%l%<areacmds%>%x'), triggered via a %c%l%(fuse%)%x (See '%g%l%<fuse%>%x'), or the character executing the compound command is an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@unchpid%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @uid
%TOPIC @chuid
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@chuid%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@chuid [<NAME>]%]%x

The '%g%l@chuid%x' (Stands for CHange User ID) command changes who you are currently building as.  If another character has given you '%c%lwrite%x' permissions to their objects via the %y%lWRITE%x friend flag (Or some of their objects via the %y%lSHARABLE%x friend flag) and permission to create objects under their ownership (Using their Building Quota) via the %y%lCREATE%x friend flag, you can use the '%g%l@chuid%x' command to set them as the character who you are building as.

Once you have used '%g%l@chuid%x' to set who you are building as, all further objects you create will be created under that character's ID, using their Building Quota.  You can return to building objects under your own ID (Using your own Building Quota) by typing '%g%l@chuid%x' without any parameters.

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xThe effects of '%g%l@chuid%x' are only effective on the command line (I.e:  You can only build as another character on the command line, %c%lNOT%x from within a compound command.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<fset%>%x', '%g%l%<group building%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?uid%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC converse
%TOPIC conversing
%TOPIC conversemode
%TOPIC conversationmode
%TITLE Help on '%w%lconverse%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lconverse%]%x

Puts you into 'converse' mode or takes you out of it.

Once in 'converse' mode, %c%lEVERYTHING%x you type will be spoken (Just as if you typed '%g%l%(say%)%x'), even if you don't put a %g%l%("%)%x or %g%l%('%)%x in front.  You can leave 'converse' mode at any time by typing '%g%lconverse%x' again.  Emoting (%g%l%(:%)%x) and thinking (%g%l%(+%)%x) can still be done in the usual way while in 'converse' mode.

You can execute any %@%m command while in 'converse' mode by typing '%g%l.<COMMAND>%x', e.g:  If you wanted to tell a message to another character, you'd type '%g%l.%(tell%) <NAME> [=] <MESSAGE>%x'.

You can still obtain help in '%g%lconverse%x' mode by typing '%g%l%(help%)%x' as normal.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<chatting%>%x'.

