%TOPIC articles
%TOPIC articlesupport
%TITLE Help on %w%larticles%x...
Article support in %@%n allows you to set an appropriate article ('%y%lA%x', '%y%lAn%x' or '%y%lSome%x') on an object, which will then be used in all messages relating to that object (E.g:  'Fred Bloggs %g%ldrops some %xSweets.' instead of 'Fred Bloggs %g%ldrops %xSweets.')

The flags %y%l%(CONSONANT%)%x (%c%lA%x), %y%l%(VOWEL%)%x (%c%lAn%x) and %y%l%(PLURAL%)%x (%c%lSome%x) determine the article of an object, and may be set on %c%l%(things%)%x, %c%l%(rooms%)%x, %c%l%(exits%)%x and %c%l%(characters%)%x (E.g:  '%g%l%(@set%) sweets = %(PLURAL%)%x'.)

Article support can be taken advantage of within compound commands by specifying '%y%ldefinite%x' or '%y%lindefinite%x' as the second parameter to the following query commands:  '%g%l{%(@?name%)}%x', '%g%l{%(@?article%)}%x', '%g%l{%(@?namec%)}%x' and '%g%l{%(@?fullname%)}%x', e.g:  '%g%l%(@echo%) {%(@?name%) sweets = INDEFINITE}%x' would give '%c%lSome Sweets%x'.
%PAGE

%[%c%lArticle flag:   %g%lindefinite  INDEFINITE  definite  DEFINITE
%c==========================================================
%y%l%(CONSONANT%)       %xa           A           the       The
%y%l%(VOWEL%)           %xan          An          the       The
%y%l%(PLURAL%)          %xsome        Some        the       The
%c==========================================================%]


%c%l%$Examples:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~%x
%[%g%l%(@set%) television = %(CONSONANT%)          %x(Gives '%y%lA Television%x'.)
%g%l%(@set%) orange = %(VOWEL%)                  %x(Gives '%y%lAn Orange%x'.)
%g%l%(@set%) sweets = %(PLURAL%)                 %x(Gives '%y%lSome Sweets%x'.)%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@?name%>%x', '%g%l%<@?article%>%x', '%g%l%<@?namec%>%x', '%g%l%<@?fullname%>%x', '%g%l%<consonant flag%>%x', '%g%l%<vowel flag%>%x', '%g%l%<plural flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<advanced%>%x'.

