%TOPIC @pending
%TOPIC fuselists
%TOPIC fuseslists
%TOPIC alarmlists
%TOPIC eventlists
%TOPIC alarmslists
%TOPIC eventslists
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@pending%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@pending [<PAGE NO>] [<NAME>] [= <OBJECT TYPE>]%]%x

Lists current pending events (In order of execution time.)  Pending events include %c%l%(alarms%)%x and triggered %y%l%(STICKY%)%x %c%l%(fuses%)%x.

By default, only alarms will be listed.  If %y%l<OBJECT TYPE>%x is specified, events of the specified object type will be listed (I.e:  '%g%l@pending = fuses%x' will list current pending %y%l%(STICKY%)%x fuses.)  '%y%lall%x' can also be specified to list all current pending events.

If %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, that page of events will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%l@pending 1%x', '%g%l@pending 2%x', etc.

If %y%l<NAME>%x is specified, only events matching %y%l<NAME>%x will be listed (I.e:  '%g%l@pending myevent%x' will list events with the text '%y%lmyevent%x' in their name.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@alarm%>%x', '%g%l%<@fuse%>%x', '%g%l%<sticky flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?pending%>%x'.

