%TITLE Help on '%w%l@thing%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@thing <NAME> [= <DESCRIPTION>]
        @create <NAME> [= <DESCRIPTION>]%]%x

Creates a thing with the name %y%l<NAME>%x (Building Quota used:  %c%l10%x.)  If %y%l<DESCRIPTION>%x is specified, it's description is set to %y%l<DESCRIPTION>%x.  You can change its description at any time of course by using '%g%l%(@desc%)%x'.

A thing is a flexible type of object that can be virtually anything you want  -  Be it a %c%lsofa%x, %c%lbed%x, %c%lcomputer%x, %c%lcar%x, %c%ldustbin%x, you name it, it can be it.  A thing can also be made into a container, into which you can put other objects providing it has enough volume (A thing's volume is set using the '%g%l%(@volume%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@volume%>%x') command.)  If the container is big enough, other characters can even climb into it (Using the '%g%l%(enter%)%x' (See '%g%l%<enter%>%x') command.)

%PAGE
By default, any other user will be able to pick up the thing and carry it off to another location.  If you do not want this to happen, you will need to set the %y%l%(IMMOVABLE%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<immovable flag%>%x') on the thing by typing '%g%l%(@set%) <THING> = immovable%x' (See '%g%l%<@set%>%x'), e.g:  '%g%l%(@set%) sofa = immovable%x'.  This will prevent %c%lANYONE%x from moving it, including yourself.

You can selectively prevent users from moving an object by locking it (Using the '%g%l%(@lock%)%x' command  -  See '%g%l%<@lock%>%x') instead of setting its %y%l%(IMMOVABLE%)%x flag.  For example, '%g%l%(@lock%) <THING> = me%x' will prevent anyone other than yourself moving the object.  See '%g%l%<@lock%>%x' for further details on locks and locking objects.

If you want to turn the thing into a container, this can be done by setting its %y%l%(OPEN%)%x/%y%l%(OPENABLE%)%x flag(s).  See section on '%g%l%(@set%)%x' for more details.

%PAGE
When you turn a thing into a container, remember to set its mass and volume (Using '%g%l%(@mass%)%x' and '%g%l%(@volume%)%x'), otherwise it wont be big enough to hold anything.

You can remotely reference things by using '%g%l#<ID>:<THING>%x', e.g:  You could reference the thing '%y%lcomputer%x' inside room %y%l#12345%x by using '%g%l#12345:computer%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@desc%>%x', '%g%l%<@name%>%x', '%g%l%<@mass%>%x', '%g%l%<@volume%>%x', '%g%l%<inheritance%>%x' and '%g%l%<building%>%x'.

