%TOPIC adjustingcredits
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@credit%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@credit <NAME> = <AMOUNT> = account|pocket = <REASON>%]%x

This command can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

The '%g%l@credit%x' command adjusts the bank account ('%y%laccount%x') or the credit in pocket ('%y%lpocket%x') of the character %y%l<NAME>%x to %y%l<AMOUNT>%x credits.  It's main use is to deal with users who have obtained credit by unfair means or users who have managed their money badly and got themselves into severe debt.

Only %c%lWizards/%cDruids%x and above may reduce the bank account or credit in pocket of a user.  %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above may raise the total credit of a user who has less than %c%l100 credits%x to a maximum of %c%l1000 credits%x.

%PAGE
%g%lElder Wizards/%gDruids%x and above may set the bank account or credit in pocket of a user to any positive value.

A %y%l<REASON>%x in all cases must be given to use this command.  The bank account or credit in pocket of a user %r%l%fMUST NOT%x be altered unless you have %m%l%ugood reason%x (I.e:  User has obtained credit by unfair means.)

This is important, because improper use of this command (I.e:  Injecting excessive money into the system or taking it out) could ruin the entire monetary system and make it worthless.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bank%>%x', '%g%l%<pay%>%x' and '%g%l%<transfer%>%x'.

