%TOPIC @desc
%TOPIC @describe
%TOPIC descriptions
%TOPIC objectdescriptions
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@desc%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@desc <ARRAY>[<ELEMENT>] [= <TEXT>]
        @desc <OBJECT> [= <DESCRIPTION>]%]%x

This command sets the description of %y%l<OBJECT>%x to %y%l<DESCRIPTION>%x.  If %y%l<DESCRIPTION>%x isn't specified, %y%l<OBJECT>%x's description will be cleared.

You see the description of the %y%l<OBJECT>%x when you (Or others) '%g%l%(look%)%x' at it.

The description of an exit is only seen when the exit is set %y%l%(OPAQUE%)%x (See '%g%l%<opaque flag%>%x'.)

The description of a fuse is the value it counts down from (To zero.)

The description of a compound command is the commands (On separate lines) that the compound command will execute.

%PAGE
'%g%l@desc%x' can also be used to set the description (Or contents if you like) of dynamic array elements, e.g:  '%g%l@desc myarray[2] = some text%x' will set the description of the %c%l2nd%x element of '%y%lmyarray%x' to '%y%lsome text%x' and '%g%l@desc myarray[test] = indexed element 'test'%x' will set the description of the element with the index name '%y%ltest%x' of '%y%lmyarray%x' to '%y%lindexed element 'test'%x'.

You can set the description of more than one dynamic array element at once by using a range, e.g:  '%g%l@desc myarray[4..7] = some more text%x' will set the description of elements %c%l4%x, %c%l5%x, %c%l6%x and %c%l7%x of '%y%lmyarray%x' to '%y%lsome more text%x'.

If the element(s) being described do not exist, they'll be created (Building Quota used by each new element:  %c%l1%x.)  You can add new elements to the end of a dynamic array using the '%y%lEND%x' keyword, e.g:  '%g%l@desc myarray[END] = a new element%x' will add a new element to the end of the dynamic array '%y%lmyarray%x' and set its description to '%y%la new element%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@odesc%>%x', '%g%l%<@succ%>%x', '%g%l%<@fail%>%x' and '%g%l%<@drop%>%x'.

