%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@reload [local|generic]tutorial <TOPIC>
        @reload disclaimer|termcap|titles|map
        @reload [local|generic]help <TOPIC>%]%x

The '%g%l@reload%x' command can only be used by %m%lDeities%x and the %m%lSupreme Being%x.  It's used to reload the %c%ltitle screens%x, %c%ldisclaimer%x, %c%ltermcap%x (Database of terminal definitions) or any %c%lhelp topics%x/%c%ltutorials%x which have had changes made to them without needing to shutdown and restart %@%m.

%@%m features an %y%lOn-Line %(Help%)%x and %y%l%(Tutorials%)%x system, with both %c%lgeneric%x and %c%llocal%x help topics/tutorials.  %c%lGeneric%x help topics and tutorials are officially distributed with the %y%lTCZ source code%x (See '%g%l%<tcz%>%x' and '%g%l%<gpl%>%x') and %r%l%ushould not be modified%x.  If you wish to modify generic topics, please copy them to %c%llocal%x help/tutorials and make the required changes.

%PAGE
'%g%l@reload [local|generic]help <TOPIC>%x' attempts to reload the specified %c%lhelp topic%x from either %c%llocal%x or %c%lgeneric%x help (Or both, if just '%g%lhelp%x' is specified.)  %y%l<TOPIC>%x may contain %(wildcards%) ('%y%l*%x' and '%y%l?%x'  -  See '%g%l%<wildcards%>%x') to reload multiple topics in one go.  '%g%l@reload [local|generic]tutorial <TOPIC>%x' will reload %c%ltutorials%x from either %c%llocal%x or %c%lgeneric%x tutorials (Or both, if just '%g%ltutorial%x' is specified.)

The other forms reload the %c%l%(disclaimer%)%x (See '%g%l%<disclaimer%>%x'), %c%lterminal definition database%x, %c%l%(title screens%)%x (See '%g%l%<titles%>%x') and %c%l%@%m %(map%)%x (See '%g%l%<map%>%x') respectively, allowing them to be updated when changes are made without shutting down and then restarting %@%m.
<-SEPARATOR->
