%TOPIC @key
%TOPIC keys
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@key%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@key <OBJECT> [= <KEY>]%]%x

Sets (Or resets, if %y%l<KEY>%x isn't specified) the key required to lock/unlock (Using the '%g%l%(lock%)%x' and '%g%l%(unlock%)%x' commands (See '%g%l%<lock%>%x' and '%g%l%<unlock%>%x')) the container or vehicle %y%l<OBJECT>%x.

%y%l<KEY>%x is specified in the same format as used for the '%g%l%(@lock%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@lock%>%x' for full details.)


%c%l%$Example:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@thing%) Old oak chest = A large, old oak chest.
%(@thing%) Rusty key = An old rusty key, labelled 'Oak chest'.
%(@set%) old oak chest = openable
@key old oak chest = rusty key%]%x

(In order to lock/unlock the chest, you must be holding the '%c%lRusty key%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@lock%>%x', '%g%l%<lock%>%x', '%g%l%<unlock%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?key%>%x'.

