%TOPIC link
%TOPIC @link
%TOPIC linking
%TOPIC linkingthings
%TOPIC linkingobjects
%TOPIC settingyourhome
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@link%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@link <OBJECT> = <HOME OBJECT>
        @link <EXIT> = <DESTINATION>%]%x

The first form ('%g%l@link <OBJECT> = <HOME OBJECT>%x') is used to set the home of a character or thing, or set the drop-to of a room.  You can set your home (Which is the room/container you return to when you type '%g%l%(home%)%x') by typing '%g%l@link me = #<ROOM ID>%x'.

If a thing has it's %y%l%(STICKY%)%x flag set, it will return to its home when dropped.  The drop-to of a room is the location where all objects dropped in the room will be teleported to (If the room has its %y%l%(STICKY%)%x flag set, the drop-to will be delayed until there are no connected characters in the room.)

%PAGE
The second form ('%g%l@link <EXIT> = <DESTINATION>%x') is used to set the destination of an exit, which must be a room or container.  If you're a Builder or above, you can link exits which don't belong to you (In doing this, you take over the ownership and Building Quota used by it.)

You can unlink an exit or remove the drop-to of a room by using the '%g%l%(@unlink%)%x' command.

%9%3%c%lExamples:  %x'%g%l@link me = #12345%x', '%g%l@link mything = #12345%x', '%g%l@link here = #12345%x', '%g%l@link myexit = #12345%x', etc.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@unlink%>%x', '%g%l%<home%>%x', '%g%l%<sticky flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?destination%>%x'.

