%TOPIC @monitor
%TOPIC watchingusers
%TOPIC watchingproblemusers
%TOPIC monitoringabusiveusers
%TOPIC monitoringproblemusers
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@monitor%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@monitor <NAME> = commands|output|both = <REASON>
        @monitor <NAME> = off%]%x

This command allows %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above to monitor an abusive/problem user to obtain evidence and take appropriate action against them.

When monitored, every command the user types will be logged to the '%c%lMonitor%x' log file (See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.)  When the parameter '%y%lcommands%x' or '%y%lboth%x' is specified, every command typed by the user will also be relayed to the member of Admin monitoring them.

If the parameter '%y%loutput%x' or '%y%lboth%x' is specified, all output (As seen by the monitored user, on their screen) will be relayed to the member of Admin monitoring them.  %c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xRelayed output appears %m%lEXACTLY%x how it does on the monitored user's screen, so don't be surprised if you suddenly start saying things, sending pages, etc. (That is the monitored user speaking, paging, etc., %r%lNOT%x you.)

You can stop a monitor on a user by typing '%g%l@monitor <NAME> = off%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@boot%>%x' and '%g%l%<@ban%>%x'.

