%TOPIC @name
%TOPIC names
%TOPIC @namelower
%TOPIC objectnames
%TOPIC namingthings
%TOPIC namingobjects
%TOPIC @namelowercase
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@name%x' and '%w%l@namelower%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@namelower <OBJECT> = <NAME>
        @name <OBJECT> = <NAME>%]%x

Changes the name of %y%l<OBJECT>%x to %y%l<NAME>%x.  You must either control %y%l<OBJECT>%x or be of a higher level than its owner to change its name.

You can use '%g%l@name%x' to change your name by typing '%g%l@name me = <NAME>%x'.

'%g%l@namelower%x' allows an object with its article set (See '%g%l%<articles%>%x') to be given a lower-case name, allowing an object to be called '%y%lA television%x' instead of '%y%lA Television%x' for example, if it had the %y%l%(CONSONANT%)%x article.

'%g%l@namelower%x' cannot be used to change the name of a character.

%PAGE
%8%c%lNOTE:  %xIf you're changing your own name or that of another character, the name you give them must be %y%l4 or more characters long%x (Unless you're an %g%lElder Wizard/%gDruid%x or above, who can give a character any name.)

       %8When you change your name, you can't change it again for another %y%l15 minutes%x.  You must also wait for %y%l15 minutes%x after connecting before changing your name.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@desc%>%x' and '%g%l%<articles%>%x'.

