%TOPIC @prefix
%TOPIC @prefixes
%TOPIC @nameprefixes
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@prefix%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@prefix <NAME> = <PREFIX>%]%x

This command can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

Sets the name prefix of the character %y%l<NAME>%x to %y%l<PREFIX>%x.  The name prefix of a character is added in front of their name, e.g:  '%g%l@prefix me = Warrior%x' would add '%g%lWarrior%x' to the front of your name, i.e:  '%g%lWarrior Fred Bloggs%x'.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xA name prefix mustn't contain %c%lembedded NEWLINE's%x, and also mustn't be longer than %c%l40 characters%x.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@suffix%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?prefix%>%x'.

