%TOPIC @dob
%TOPIC @profile
%TOPIC birthdays
%TOPIC @birthday
%TOPIC dateofbirth
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@profile%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@profile [<NAME> =] <FIELD> [<SETTING>]
        @profile reset [yes]%]%x

Every character on %@%n has a profile.  You can use your profile to set detailed information about yourself, which other users can view (By using the '%g%l%(profile%)%x' command  -  See '%g%l%<profile%>%x') to find out more about you.

The '%g%l@profile%x' command is used to set/reset the various fields available on your profile.  %y%l<FIELD>%x is the field to set, from the list on the next page (I.e:  '%y%lrealname%x' will set your %c%lreal name%x, '%y%lhobbies%x' will set your %c%lhobbies%x, etc.)  %y%l<SETTING>%x is the new setting for the field (If this is omitted, the field will be reset), e.g:  '%g%l@profile realname Fred Bloggs%x', '%g%l@profile country England%x', '%g%l@profile eyes brown%x', etc.

%PAGE
%y%l<FIELD>%x can be one of the following:

%y%lAchievements%x, %y%lbirthday%x, %y%lcity%x, %y%lcomments%x, %y%lcountry%x, %y%ldislikes%x, %y%ldrinks%x, %y%lemail%x, %y%leyes%x, %y%lfoods%x, %y%lgender%x, %y%lhair%x, %y%lheight%x, %y%lhobbies%x, %y%linterests%x, %y%llikes%x, %y%lmiscellaneous%x, %y%lmusic%x, %y%lnationality%x, %y%loccupation%x, %y%lother%x, %y%lpicture%x, %y%lqualifications%x, %y%lrealname%x, %y%lsex%x, %y%lsexuality%x, %y%lsports%x, %y%lstatusirl%x, %y%lstatusivl%x, %y%lweight%x, %y%lwww%x.

You can reset all the fields on your profile in one go by typing '%g%l@profile reset [yes]%x'.  %c%lNOTE:  %xAll fields on your profile will be reset %r%lPERMANENTLY%x  -  You will not be able to retrieve them once they have been reset.

If %y%l<NAME>%x is specified, and you're an %c%lWizard/%cDruid%x or above, %y%l<FIELD>%x on the character %y%l<NAME>%x's profile will be set/reset.

%PAGE
%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xYou don't need to set %y%lALL%x of the fields available on your profile  -  Just set the ones which are relevant to you.

              %9%6%y%lHeight%x can be set in either %c%lMETRES/CENTIMETRES%x (E.g:  %y%l1m 96cm%x) or %c%lFEET/INCHES%x (E.g:  %y%l5' 8"%x)

              %9%6%y%lWeight%x can be set in either %c%lKILOGRAMS/GRAMS%x (E.g:  %y%l75Kg 100g%x or %c%lPOUNDS/OUNCES%x (E.g:  %y%l158lbs 3oz%x)

              %9%6%y%lBirthday%x is in %c%lDAY%x, %c%lMONTH%x, %c%lYEAR%x format, i.e:  '%y%l28/11/1994%x', '%y%l28th November 1994%x', etc.

              %9%6%y%lPicture%x is the URL of a picture you have of yourself on the World Wide Web.  If this field is set, users connecting using a World Wide Web browser will see your picture on your profile, and your picture will also appear in the %@%m user picture gallery.  E.g:

              %9%6%y%lhttp://www.wibble.wobble.com/~fred/me.jpg%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<profile%>%x', '%g%l%<scan%>%x', '%g%l%<@?profile%>%x' and '%g%l%<html%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @sanity
%TOPIC integrity
%TOPIC sanitychecks
%TOPIC databasesanity
%TOPIC integritychecking
%TOPIC databasecorruption
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@sanity%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@sanity checklists|fixlists [= yes]
        @sanity general [= yes]%]%x

'%g%l@sanity%x' is used to perform integrity checks on the database, to check for (And optionally attempt to correct) possible corruption.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xA general sanity check is always performed automatically when %@%m starts up, and a full sanity check ('%y%lfixlists%x') is also performed if %@%m was not shutdown 'cleanly' (I.e:  Using the '%g%l%(@shutdown%)%x' command  -  See '%g%l%<@shutdown%>%x'.)  Because of this, manual use of the '%g%l@sanity%x' command should be unnecessary.

'%g%l@sanity checklists%x' (Which can only be used by %g%lElder Wizards/%gDruids%x and above) checks for corrupted linked lists attached to objects and '%g%l@sanity fixlists%x' (Which can only be used by %m%lDeities%x and the %m%lSupreme Being%x) attempts to fix any corruption.

%PAGE
'%g%l@sanity general%x' performs a general sanity check on the database.  This will check for and fix simple problems, such as objects with invalid owners, etc.  This check is also performed automatically on start-up, and could cause lag (For this reason, the second parameter '%y%lyes%x' must be given.)

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xBoth '%g%l@sanity checklists%x' and '%g%l@sanity fixlists%x' can be extremely CPU intensive and can take several minutes to complete (Depending on the size of the database, and server CPU power)  -  I.e:  %@%m could come to a complete halt for everyone using it until the command completes, so it should only ever be used in an %r%l%uabsolute emergency%x.  For these reasons, the second parameter '%y%lyes%x' must be given to use them.

%PAGE

%c%l%$Obsolete '%w%l%$@sanity%c%l%$' options:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xSome '%g%l@sanity%x' options have been be removed, having been replaced with suitable alternatives.  These are listed below:


%[%c%l%$Command:%x              %c%l%$Replacement:%x        %c%l%$Users ranked by:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~              ~~~~~~~~~~~~        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%g%l@sanity checkquotas   %(@rank%) quotaexcess   %xExceeded Building Quota limits.
%g%l@sanity quotalimits   %(@rank%) quotalimits   %xBuilding Quota limits.
%cN/A                   %g%l%(@rank%) quota         %xBuilding Quota in use.
%g%l@sanity credit        %(@rank%) credit        %xCredit in pocket.
%cN/A                   %g%l%(@rank%) balance       %xBank balance.
%g%l@sanity score         %(@rank%) score         %xScore.%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@admin%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @site
%TOPIC @sites
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@site%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@site set <IP ADDRESS> = [!]<FLAG> [[!]<FLAG>] [...] [= <REASON>]
        @site [max]connections <IP ADDRESS> = <LIMIT> = <REASON>
        @site address <IP ADDRESS> [=] <NEW IP ADDRESS>
        @site list [<PAGE NO>] [<IP ADDRESS>|<DESC>]
        @site desc <IP ADDRESS> [=] <DESCRIPTION>
        @site add <IP ADDRESS> [=] <DESCRIPTION>
        @site delete <IP ADDRESS>
        @site [view] <IP ADDRESS>
        @site stats%]%x

The '%g%l@site%x' command (Which can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above) is used to view, list, add, modify or delete Internet sites from the database of registered Internet sites.

The database of registered Internet sites holds details of Internet sites (A meaningful description and number of characters connected/created from site), allows flags to be set/reset on particular sites (To implement create bans, site bans, etc.) and allows the number of connections (Simultaneously) from sites to be restricted.

%PAGE
For further details on the '%g%l@site%x' command and its usage, please see the help screens for each '%g%l@site%x' sub-command, as listed in the table below...

%[%c%lType in:             Description:
%c=============================================================================
%g%l%(help @site view%)      %xHow to view details of a registered Internet site.
%g%l%(help @site list%)      %xHow to list registered Internet sites.
%g%l%(help @site add%)       %xHow to add a new Internet site.
%g%l%(help @site set%)       %xHow to set flags on an Internet site.
%g%l%(help @site desc%)      %xHow to change the description of an Internet site.
%g%l%(help @site address%)   %xHow to change the IP address of an Internet site.
%g%l%(help @site maxc%)      %xHow to restrict maximum connections allowed from a site.
%g%l%(help @site delete%)    %xHow to delete an Internet site.
%g%l%(help @site stats%)     %xHow to view the Internet site DB statistics.
%c=============================================================================%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<sites%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?lastsite%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @siteviewsites
%TOPIC @sitesviewsites
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@site view%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@site [view] <IP ADDRESS>%]%x

This form of '%g%l%(@site%)%x' displays full details of the Internet site specified (Including number of characters connected, created and presently 'on-line' from site.)

%c%lExamples:  %x'%g%l@site view %@%a%x', '%g%l@site 193.72.92.234%x', etc.%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Type '%g%l%<@site list%>%x' for help on the next '%g%l%(@site%)%x' command...

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @sitelistsites
%TOPIC @siteslistsites
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@site list%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@site list [<PAGE>] [<IP ADDR>|<DESC>] [= [!][<FLAG>][[!]<FLAG>][...]]%]%x

This form of '%g%l%(@site%)%x' lists Internet sites in the database of registered Internet sites (Ordered by IP address.)  Sites matching a particular IP address can be listed by specifying the IP address and (Optionally) using a '%y%l*%x' in place of any of the numbers in it, e.g:  '%g%l@site list 193.133.51.*%x' will list all sites with an IP address beginning '%y%l193.133.51%x'.

You can also list all sites with a description which matches the wildcard specification you give, e.g:  '%g%l@site list *leeds*%x' will list every site with the text '%y%lleeds%x' in its description.

%PAGE
You can list sites which only have particular Internet site flags set (Or not set), e.g:  '%g%l@site list = banned%x' will list all Internet sites which have been banned, '%g%l@site list = !create%x' will list all Internet sites which have been banned from creating new characters.  Multiple Internet site flags may be specified, e.g:  '%g%l@site list = create guests%x' lists all Internet sites with either the %y%lCREATE%x or %y%lGUESTS%x site flag(s) set.  Please see '%g%l%<@site set%>%x' for details of Internet site flags and what they do.

By default, if more than a page of Internet sites are found, the first page of sites will be displayed.  If %y%l<PAGE>%x is specified, that page of sites will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%l@sites list 1%x', '%g%l@sites list 2%x', '%g%l@sites list 2 %@%a%x', etc.
<-SEPARATOR->
Type '%g%l%<@site add%>%x' for help on the next '%g%l%(@site%)%x' command...

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @siteadd
%TOPIC @siteaddsite
%TOPIC @sitesaddsite
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@site add%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@site add <IP ADDRESS> [=] <DESCRIPTION>%]%x

This form of '%g%l%(@site%)%x' adds a new Internet site to the database of registered Internet sites.  Please %c%lDO NOT%x add details of any sites other than universities, companies, Internet providers, BBS's, etc. (I.e:  Do not add details of someone's home computer (Even if it does have a fixed address), unless connections/character creation from their machine need to be banned.)

%9%6%y%l<IP ADDRESS>  %xThis is the Internet IP address of the Internet site.  This %c%lMUST%x be specified in numeric form (E.g:  '%y%ln.n.n.n%x'.)  If the site you're adding is a university, company or Internet provider, the chances are that they have a Class B address, which means you should specify the address as ('%y%ln.n.n.*%x'  -  I.e:  Replace last number of address with a '%y%l*%x'.)  If the site is a BBS, the chances are that they only have one Internet address in the form of '%y%ln.n.n.n%x'.  Example IP addresses are:  '%c%l%@%a%x', '%c%l193.133.51.*%x', '%c%l194.72.92.*%x', etc.

%PAGE
%9%7%y%l<DESCRIPTION>%x  This is a short, meaningful description of what the Internet site is.  This should be in the form of '%y%l<UNIVERSITY/COMPANY/PROVIDER/BBS>, <TOWN/CITY>, <STATE/PROVINCE/COUNTY>, <COUNTRY>%x'  Please begin the names of places with a capital letter and %c%lDO NOT%x use abbreviations (I.e:  '%y%luni%x' for '%y%luniversity%x', '%y%lTVU%x' for '%y%lThames Valley University%x', etc.)  Example descriptions:  '%c%lThe University of Leeds, England%x', '%c%lCurrent Technologies Corporation, Mission Hills, California, USA%x', '%c%lDemon Internet (Internet provider), UK%x', etc.

%c%l%$Examples:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l@site add 198.175.4.* = Air Force Academy, Colorado, USA
@site add 129.10.1.* = The University of Leeds, England
@site add 158.152.*.* = Demon Internet (Internet Provider), UK%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Type '%g%l%<@site set%>%x' for help on the next '%g%l%(@site%)%x' command...

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @siteset
%TOPIC @sitesetsiteflags
%TOPIC @sitessetsiteflags
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@site set%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@site set <IP ADDRESS> = [!]<FLAG> [[!]<FLAG>] [...] [= <REASON>]%]%x

This form of '%g%l%(@site%)%x' is used to set or reset site flags on an Internet site.  These flags allow connections/character creation/Admin connections from particular sites to be banned, site addresses to be looked up on the Domain Name Server and site details made readonly.

When resetting the %y%lCREATE%x site flag or setting the %y%lBAN/UNCONDITIONAL%x site flags, you will need to give a reason for doing so.


%c%l%$The following flags may be set/reset on Internet sites...%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%y%lADMIN          %g%l(Elder Wizards/%gDruids %g%land above only)  %xWhen this flag is reset
               on an Internet site, %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above will
               no-longer be able to connect from it.  %c%lBy default, every new
               Internet site has this flag.%]

%PAGE
%[%y%lBAN            %g%l(Elder Wizards/%gDruids %g%land above only)  %xWhen this flag is set on
               an Internet site, users from the site will not be able to
               connect %c%lOR%x create characters.  However, %y%lApprentice
               Wizards/%yDruids%x and above will still be able to connect (Unless
               the %y%lADMIN%x site flag is also reset on the site.)

%y%lCREATE         (Apprentice Wizards/%yDruids %y%land above)  %xWhen this flag is reset
               on an Internet site, users from the site will no-longer be able
               to create new characters (At the login screen.)  %c%lBy default,
               every new Internet site has this flag.%]

%PAGE
%[%y%lDNS            %c%l(Wizards/%cDruids %c%land above only)  %xWhen this flag is set on an
               Internet site, the name of the site will be looked up on the
               Domain Name Server and displayed in the host list, etc.  (E.g:
               '%y%l%@%s%x' instead of '%y%l%@%a%x'.)

               %r%l%fTHIS FLAG SHOULD BE USED WITH CARE:  %xSome Internet site
               addresses do not resolve easily (If at all), and could cause
               %@%m to 'lock up' for anything between 1 and 30 minutes.

%y%lGUESTS         (Apprentice Wizards/%yDruids %y%land above)  %xWhen this flag is reset
               on an Internet site, Guest characters will no-longer be able to
               connect from the site.  %c%lBy default, every new Internet site has
               this flag.%]

%PAGE
%[%y%lNODNS          %c%l(Wizards/%cDruids %c%land above only)  %xWhen this flag is set on an
               Internet site, the name of the site %c%lWILL NOT%x be looked up on
               the Domain Name Server.  This flag should be set on all site
               addresses which are known not to resolve properly.%]

%y%lREADONLY       %g%l(Elder Wizards/%gDruids %g%land above only)  %xWhen this flag is set on
               an Internet site, the details and flags of the site can't be
               modified, and the site can't be deleted.%]

%PAGE
%[%y%lUNCONDITIONAL  %g%l(Elder Wizards/%gDruids %g%land above only)  %xIf this site flag is set
               on a site along with the %y%lBAN%x site flag, the ban becomes
               unconditional and all connections from the site will be
               %c%lcompletely%x blocked (They wont even get as far as the login
               screen (Instead, the site ban message will be displayed and the
               connection closed.))  If set on a site which has had the
               maximum number of connections allowed (Simultaneously) from it
               restricted (See '%g%l%<@site maxc%>%x'), further connections will be
               completely blocked when the maximum number of users allowed
               (Simultaneously) are connected.%]

%PAGE

%c%l%$Examples:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l@site set 198.234.52.* = !create = Because of the continuous stream of
    abusive users/bogus characters being created from this site.

%g%l@site set 198.124.31.* = ban = Due to all users connecting from this site
    doing nothing else other than harassing and abusing other users (Even after
    the CREATE site flag was removed from this site.)%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Type '%g%l%<@site desc%>%x' for help on the next '%g%l%(@site%)%x' command...

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @sitedescsite
%TOPIC @sitesdescsite
