%TITLE Help on '%w%l@site desc%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@site desc <IP ADDRESS> [=] <DESCRIPTION>%]%x

This form of '%g%l%(@site%)%x' allows the description of an Internet site to be changed (If it's incorrect.)  The new description should be in the form of '%y%l<UNIVERSITY/COMPANY/PROVIDER/BBS>, <TOWN/CITY>, <STATE/PROVINCE/COUNTY>, <COUNTRY>%x', the names of places should all begin with a capital letter and abbreviations (Such as '%y%luni%x' for '%y%luniversity%x', etc.) %c%lmust not%x be used.

%[%c%lExample:  %g%l@site desc 193.61.80.* = Nene College, Northampton, England%]%x

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xSome universities/companies with Class B (Or even Class C) Internet addresses lease a few of their available addresses to other (Smaller) universities/colleges/companies.  This means that if someone connects from one of these places, their address will match the address of the providing company (If this is the case, you should add an individual entry for them (In the form of '%y%ln.n.n.n%x'), providing their 'site' isn't their home computer.
<-SEPARATOR->
Type '%g%l%<@site address%>%x' for help on the next '%g%l%(@site%)%x' command...

