%TOPIC osuccess
%TOPIC @osuccess
%TOPIC othersuccessmessage
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@osucc%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@osucc <OBJECT> [= <MESSAGE>]%]%x

This command sets the others success message for the %y%l<OBJECT>%x specified.  You must of course control this object.

An object succeeds when a character manages to satisfy its lock (If it's a room, thing or exit), or if it's a compound command, it succeeds when the last command executed in it succeeds.

If the object succeeds, the others success message is displayed with the character's name in front on the screens of every character in the same room as the character who caused it to succeed.

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xThe character who causes the others success message to be displayed %c%lWILL NOT%x see the others success message.  Instead, they will see the success message (See '%g%l%<@succ%>%x'), if set.

If %y%l<MESSAGE>%x isn't specified, the others success message is cleared.

%PAGE

%c%l%$When is the others success message displayed?
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%9%4%y%lCommand  %c-  %xDisplayed when the compound command finishes executing, and the last command executed succeeded (Not displayed if compound command has its '%g%l%(@csuccess%)%x' branch set (See '%g%l%<@csucc%>%x'.))

%9%4%y%lExit     %c-  %xDisplayed when a character goes through the exit (In the same room as exit.)

%9%4%y%lRoom     %c-  %xDisplayed when the lock of the room is satisfied and a character types '%g%l%(look%)%x' (Underneath the room's description), or if the room has its %y%l%(OPENABLE%)%x flag set (See '%g%l%<openable flag%>%x'), it is displayed when a character successfully enters the room.

%9%4%y%lThing    %c-  %xDisplayed when object is picked up.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@succ%>%x', '%g%l%<@ofail%>%x', '%g%l%<@odrop%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?osucc%>%x'.

