%TOPIC @race
%TOPIC settingyourrace
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@race%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@race [<NAME> =] <RACE>
        @race [me =] <RACE>%]%x

'%g%l@race%x' is used to set your race ('%g%l@race <RACE>%x') or the race of another character ('%g%l@race <NAME> = <RACE>%x'), if you're a %c%lWizard/%cDruid%x or above.

Other characters see what race you are when they '%g%l%(scan%)%x' you.

The maximum length of your race is %c%l50 characters%x.  You can use text colour substitutions in your race, if you wish (See '%g%l%<substitutions%>%x'.)


%c%l%$Examples:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l@race Human
@race Alien%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<scan%>%x', '%g%l%<title%>%x', '%g%l%<@www%>%x', '%g%l%<@desc%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?race%>%x'.

