%TOPIC @rank
%TOPIC sortingusers
%TOPIC rankingusers
%TOPIC sortingcharacters
%TOPIC rankingcharacters
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@rank%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@rank [<PAGE NO>] [<ORDER>] [<DIR>] [= <NAME>|admin|friends|enemies]%]%x

The '%g%l@rank%x' command ranks every user or object in the database by given criteria, using efficient internal sorting algorithms.

%y%l<ORDER>%x is the order of the ranking, which can be one of the following:

%[   %y%lactive        %xRank by %c%ltotal time spent active%x.
   %y%lavgactive     %xRank by %c%laverage time spent active%x.
   %y%lavgidle       %xRank by %c%laverage time spent idling%x.
   %y%lavglogins     %xRank by %c%laverage time between logins%x.
   %y%lavgtotal      %xRank by %c%laverage time connected%x.
   %y%lbalance       %xRank by %c%lbank balance%x.
   %y%lbattles       %xRank by %c%ltotal number of battles fought%x (Won + lost.)
   %y%lcreated       %xRank by %c%lcreation time/date%x.
   %y%lcredit        %xRank by %c%lcredit in pocket%x.
   %y%lcsize         %xRank by %c%lcompressed database memory usage%x (Admin. only.)
   %y%lexpenditure   %xRank by %c%lexpenditure%x.%]

%PAGE
%[   %y%lidle          %xRank by %c%ltotal time spent idling%x.
   %y%lincome        %xRank by %c%lincome%x.
   %y%llasttime      %xRank by %c%llast time connected%x (Like '%g%l%(lastseen%)%x'.)
   %y%llastused      %xRank by %c%ltime/date last used%x.
   %y%llogins        %xRank by %c%ltotal number of logins%x.
   %y%llongest       %xRank by %c%llongest time connected%x (Like '%g%l%(longspod%)%x'.)
   %y%llost          %xRank by %c%lnumber of battles lost%x.
   %y%lperformance   %xRank by %c%lcombat performance%x.
   %y%lprofit        %xRank by %c%lprofit%x.
   %y%lquota         %xRank by %c%lBuilding Quota currently in use%x (Admin. only.)
   %y%lquotaexcess   %xRank by %c%lexceeded Building Quota limits%x (Admin. only.)
   %y%lquotalimits   %xRank by %c%lBuilding Quota limit%x (Admin. only.)
   %y%ltotal         %xRank by %c%ltotal time connected%x (Like '%g%l%(spod%)%x'.)
   %y%lscore         %xRank by %c%lscore%x.
   %9%9%y%lsize          %xRank by %c%ldatabase memory usage%x (%r%l%f%uWARNING:%x  To do this, %@%m must decompress every object in the entire database, which may cause excessive 'lag'.  This option is restricted to %g%lElder Wizards/%gDruids%x and above only.)
   %y%lwon           %xRank by %c%lnumber of battles won%x.%]

%PAGE
%y%l<DIRECTION>%x is the direction of sorting, which can be either '%y%lascending%x' or '%y%ldescending%x'.  If this is omitted, '%y%ldescending%x' is assumed by default.

By default, the first page of users/objects will be displayed.  However, if %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, that page of users/objects will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%l@rank 2 ...%x' to display the %c%l2nd%x page, '%g%l@rank 3 ...%x' to display the %c%l3rd%x, etc.  For example, '%g%l@rank 2 longest%x'.

'%g%l@rank%x' ranks every user/object in the database by default, however you can rank your friends list by typing '%g%l@rank ... = friends%x' or '%g%l@rank ... = enemies%x', and rank current administrators of %@%m by typing '%g%l@rank ... = admin%x'.  For example, '%g%l@rank longest = friends%x'.

You can see the position of an individual user/object by typing '%g%l@rank ... = <NAME>%x', e.g:  '%g%l@rank ... = me%x' will tell you where you are in the list (Out of all of the other characters in the database) and '%g%l@rank ... = fred bloggs%x' will tell you where the user '%y%lFred Bloggs%x' is in the list.  For example, '%g%l@rank longest = me%x'.

%PAGE
You can also list users/objects in a given range of positions by typing '%g%l@rank <FROM>-<TO> ...%x', e.g:  '%g%l@rank 100-150 longest%x' will list users/objects in the positions %y%l100%x to %y%l150%x (Ranked by longest connect time.)


%c%l%$Extra options for '%w%l%$@rank credit%c%l%$', '%w%l%$@rank csize%c%l%$' and '%w%l%$@rank size%c%l%$'...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xExplicit object types can be specified for the following orders of ranking:

%[   %y%lcreated    %c%lCreation time/date%x.
   %y%lcredits    %xAmount of %c%lcredits in location%x, or for a character, their
              total %c%lcredit in pocket%x and %c%lbank balance%x.
   %y%lcsize      %c%lCompressed database memory usage%x (Admin. only.)
   %y%llastused   %c%lTime/date last used%x.
   %y%lsize       %c%lUncompressed database memory usage%x (Admin. only.)%]

%PAGE
You can rank all objects of one or more type(s), by specifying the object type(s) after '%g%lcredits%x', '%g%lcsize%x' or '%g%lsize%x' in a list separated by commas ('%y%l,%x'), e.g:  '%g%l@rank csize,arrays%x' will rank and list all dynamic arrays in the database by compressed memory usage.

Ranking objects is an ideal way to check for individual objects (Especially dynamic arrays) which are using an excessive amount of memory unnecessarily, or locations containing an excessive amount of credits.

Multiple types may be specified, i.e:  '%g%l@rank csize,things,rooms%x'.
%PAGE
%9%9%9%9%1Types can be any of the following:  %y%lalarms%x, %y%lall%x, %y%larrays%x, %y%lcharacters%x, %y%lcommands%x, %y%lexits%x, %y%lfuses%x, %y%lproperties%x, %y%lpuppets%x, %y%lrooms%x, %y%lthings%x, %y%lvariables%x.

When ranking objects in the above manner, %y%l<NAME>%x can be specified to see the position of an individual object in the list.  However, if the object is not in your current location, you will need to specify its %y%l#ID%x number instead of its name.


%c%l%$Extra options for '%w%l%$@rank expenditure%c%l%$', '%w%l%$@rank income%c%l%$' and '%w%l%$@rank profit%c%l%$'...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xWhen ranking characters by %c%lexpenditure%x, %c%lincome%x or %c%lprofit%x, you can rank by average per %c%lday%x, %c%lweek%x or %c%lmonth%x instead of total for the quarter.  To do this, simply follow '%y%lexpenditure%x', '%y%lincome%x' or '%y%lprofit%x' by '%y%l/day%x', '%y%l/week%x' or '%y%l/month%x' to rank characters by average expenditure, income or profit per day, week or month respectively.

%PAGE
%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xOnly %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above can rank characters by their Building Quota in use ('%y%lquota%x') or Building Quota limit ('%y%lquotalimit%x'.)

              %9%6Ranking users by Building Quota in use/Building Quota limit is provided to aid administrators with managing and maintaining Building Quota limits and usage.

              %9%6Administrators are excluded from '%g%l@rank quotalimit%x' (Unless '%g%l@rank quotalimit = admin%x' is used), because their Building Quota limit is unlimited.

              %9%6Puppets are excluded from '%y%lactive%x', '%y%lavgactive%x', '%y%lavgidle%x', '%y%lavglogins%x', '%y%lavgtotal%x', '%y%lidle%x', '%y%llogins%x', '%y%llongest%x', '%y%lscore%x' and '%y%ltotal%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<spod%>%x', '%g%l%<longspod%>%x', '%g%l%<lastseen%>%x' and '%g%l%<friends%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC execution
%TOPIC recursion
%TOPIC @execution
%TOPIC @recursion
%TOPIC @executionlimit
%TOPIC @recursionlimit
%TOPIC recursivecommands
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@execution%x' (Or '%w%l@executionlimit%x')
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@executionlimit <LIMIT>
        @execution <LIMIT>%]%x

Sets the execution time limit (In seconds) for a compound command.  The execution time limit is the maximum execution time allowed for the compound command and any other compound commands called from within it (The default execution time limit is %c%l3 seconds%x.)  If the execution time limit is exceeded, execution of the current compound command will be terminated.

%PAGE

%c%l%$The maximum execution time limits are as follows:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%xMortal                      3 seconds
%y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid     %x5 seconds
%c%lWizard/%cDruid                %x5 seconds
%g%lElder Wizard/%gDruid          %x10 seconds
%m%lDeity/the Supreme Being     %x60 seconds%]%x


However, a compound command should never need an execution time limit of more than %c%l3 seconds%x (Doing so will cause unexceptable lag.)  If it needs more than this, the compound command will need to be rewritten to make it more efficient.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@command%>%x', '%g%l%<@?execution%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?executed%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @rem
%TOPIC @remote
%TOPIC remotecommandexecution
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@remote%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@remote <LOCATION> = <COMMAND>%]%x

'%g%l@remote%x' acts as if you were in %y%l<LOCATION>%x, and executed the command %y%l<COMMAND>%x.

%y%l<LOCATION>%x must be owned by yourself or your puppet (Unless you are a %c%lWizard%x/%cDruid%x or above, who can %g%l@remote%x to any location unless it is set %y%lPRIVATE%x and owned by a character of an equal or higher rank.)

Of course, you don't move at all  -  You just see the result(s) of the command.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@force%>%x'.

