%TOPIC @sc
%TOPIC @score
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@score%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@score <NAME> = <AMOUNT>%]%x

This command can only be used by %c%lWizards/%cDruids%x and above.

Increases/decreases the character %y%l<NAME>%x's score by %y%l<AMOUNT>%x points.  Score points are usually earned by completing adventures, puzzles and winning battles against other characters in combat areas.

To see the high scores on %@%m, simply type '%g%l%(@rank%) score%x' (See '%g%l%<@rank%>%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@rank%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?score%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC @set
%TOPIC settingflags
%TOPIC changingflags
%TOPIC removingflags
%TITLE Help on '%w%l@set%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = [!]<FLAG> [[!]<FLAG>] [...] [= <REASON>]%]%x

'%g%l@set%x' is used to set/reset one or more flags on an object or character.

To set a flag on an object, simply type '%g%l@set <OBJECT> = <FLAG>%x', e.g:  '%g%l@set myobject = sticky%x'.  To reset a flag, simply type '%g%l@set <OBJECT> = !<FLAG>%x' ('%y%l!%x' means '%y%lnot%x'.)  You can set/reset more than one flag on an object in one go by specifying multiple flag names separated by spaces, e.g:  '%g%l@set here = haven !abode !yell%x'.

When you look at an object you own/control, flags are displayed as letters following the ID number of it (E.g:  '%y%lThe Maelstrom(#3227 RAHy)%x'.)

%PAGE
The first flag (After the ID) (%y%lR%x) tells you what type the object is, e.g:  %y%lR%x = %c%lRoom%x.  This flag (Which is an %c%lobject type flag%x) can't be changed  -  Any other flags following this flag can (%y%lAHy%x), by using '%g%l@set%x'.

The setting/resetting of important/privilege flags is logged to the '%c%lFlags%x' (See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.)


%c%l%$The object type flags are:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%y%l%(Alarm%)%x (A), %y%l%(Compound Command%)%x (C), %y%l%(Dynamic Array%)%x (D), %y%l%(Exit%)%x (E), %y%l%(Fuse%)%x (F), %y%l%(Player%)%x (%y%l%(Character%)%x) (P), %y%l%(Property%)%x (p), %y%l%(Puppet%)%x (p) (On character), %y%l%(Room%)%x (R), %y%l%(Thing%)%x (T), %y%l%(Variable%)%x (V).
%PAGE

%c%l%$The flags that you can set/reset are:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%[%y%l%(Abode%)%c         (%c%lA%c)   %y%l%(Abort%)%c         (%c%la%c)   %y%l%(Ansi%)%c          (%c%la%c)   %y%l%(Apprentice%)%c    (%c%lA%c)
%y%l%(Ashcan%)%c        (%c%l!%c)   %y%l%(Assistant%)%c     (%c%lx%c)   %y%l%(BBS%)%c           (%c%lb%c)   %y%l%(BBS-Inform%)%c
%y%l%(Boot%)%c                %y%l%(Builder%)%c       (%c%lB%c)   %y%l%(Censored%)%c      (%c%l^%c)   %y%l%(Combat%)%c        (%c%lc%c)
%y%l%(Consonant%)%c   ('%w%lA%c')   %y%l%(Dark%)%c          (%c%lD%c)   %y%l%(Deity%)%c         (%c%lD%c)   %y%l%(Druid%)%c
%y%l%(Elder%)%c         (%c%lE%c)   %y%l%(Engaged%)%c       (%c%le%c)   %y%l%(Experienced%)%c   (%c%lX%c)   %y%l%(Expiry%)%c        (%c%lx%c)
