%TOPIC abode
%TOPIC abodeflag
%TOPIC linkingrooms
%TOPIC lodestonerooms
%TITLE Help on the %w%lABODE%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = ABODE
        @set <OBJECT> = !ABODE%]%x

When set on a room, the %y%lABODE%x flag allows other characters to see the %y%l#<ID>%x number of the room, set their home to it (By typing '%g%l%(@link%) me = #<ID>%x') or teleport to it (By typing '%g%l%(@tel%) #<ID>%x'.)

%y%lABODE%x is an ideal way of letting friends or the general public into your area (I.e:  By advertising the %y%l#<ID>%x number of it.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@tel%>%x', '%g%l%<@link%>%x', '%g%l%<home%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC abortflag
%TOPIC abortfuses
%TITLE Help on the %w%lABORT%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <FUSE> = ABORT
        @set <FUSE> = !ABORT%]%x

This flag can only be set/reset by %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruids%x and above on fuses.

When set on a fuse, the %y%lABORT%x flag will prevent the command which triggered the fuse from being executed.  For example, if a fuse with its %y%lABORT%x flag set is placed on an object, then when a character attempts to pick up or drop the object, the fuse will be executed, but the object will remain where it is (Because the '%g%l%(take%)%x' or '%g%l%(drop%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<take%>%x' and '%g%l%<drop%>%x') typed by the user will be aborted.)

The '%g%l%(@continue%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@continue%>%x') can be used within the compound command executed by the fuse with its %y%lABORT%x flag set to optionally prevent the effects of the %y%lABORT%x flag (I.e:  Allow the execution of the command which triggered the fuse.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@fuse%>%x', '%g%l%<@continue%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC ashcanflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lASHCAN%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = ASHCAN
        @set <OBJECT> = !ASHCAN%]%x

The %y%lASHCAN%x flag is used to mark objects for automatic destruction after their last usage date exceeds %c%l1 month%x.  Objects with their %y%lASHCAN%x flag set can be saved from automatic destruction by resetting their %y%lASHCAN%x flag.

The %y%lASHCAN%x flag is also set on any object/character which couldn't be destroyed by automatic object/character maintenance for some reason (I.e:  A Builder who has objects locked to them, an object used in the lock of another object, etc.)

%PAGE
%8%c%lNOTE:  %xIf you no-longer need an object, you should destroy it by using the '%g%l%(@destroy%)%x' command, as this will remove the object from the database immediately and reimburse the Building Quota used by it, so you can use it to build something else.

       %8You can recover accidentally destroyed objects by using the '%g%l%(@undestroy%)%x' command, however objects destroyed by automatic object maintenance cannot be recovered.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@destroy%>%x', '%g%l%<@undestroy%>%x', '%g%l%<@destall%>%x', '%g%l%<@maintenance%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC bbsflag
%TOPIC flagbbs
%TITLE Help on the %w%lBBS%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set *<NAME> = BBS
        @set *<NAME> = !BBS%]%x

This flag can only be set/reset by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

If a character's %y%lBBS%x flag is removed, they will no-longer be able to add new messages to %@%n BBS, reply to messages, delete messages, etc.  However, they will be able to still browse the BBS and read messages on it.

If a user is abusing %@%n BBS, removing their %y%lBBS%x flag will prevent them from continuing to do so.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs-inform flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC bbsinformflag
%TOPIC bbsnotifyflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lBBS-INFORM%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set *<NAME> = BBS-INFORM
        @set *<NAME> = !BBS-INFORM%]%x

This flag can only be set/reset on characters.

If you set your %y%lBBS-INFORM%x flag ('%g%l%(@set%) me = bbs-inform%x'), you will receive messages informing you when other characters add, reply to, modify, etc. messages on %@%n BBS (Similar to the messages you get when you are in the BBS room.)  This is extremely useful if you do all of your BBS browsing remotely using the '%g%l%(bbs%) <BBS COMMAND>%x' command (See '%g%l%<bbs%>%x'.)

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xIf you set your %y%l%(QUIET%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<quiet flag%>%x'), the effects of the %y%lBBS-INFORM%x flag will be overridden (I.e:  You will no-longer be informed until you reset your %y%l%(QUIET%)%x flag.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs%>%x', '%g%l%<quiet flag%>%x', '%g%l%<bbs flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC friendsinformflag
%TOPIC friendsnotifyflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lFRIENDS-INFORM%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set *<NAME> = FRIENDS-INFORM
        @set *<NAME> = !FRIENDS-INFORM%]%x

This flag can only be set/reset on characters.

If you set your %y%lFRIENDS-INFORM%x flag ('%g%l%(@set%) me = friends-inform%x'), you will receive messages informing you when other characters add you to or remove you from their friends list (See '%g%l%<fadd%>%x' and '%g%l%<fremove%>%x'.)  You will also receive messages when they change the friend flags they currently have set on you (See '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.)

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xIf you set your %y%l%(QUIET%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<quiet flag%>%x'), the effects of the %y%lFRIENDS-INFORM%x flag will be overridden (I.e:  You will no-longer be informed until you reset your %y%l%(QUIET%)%x flag.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<friends%>%x', '%g%l%<fadd%>%x', '%g%l%<fremove%>%x', '%g%l%<fset%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC bootflag
%TOPIC builderflag
%TOPIC buildingflag
%TOPIC constructorflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lBUILDER%x and %w%lBOOT%x flags
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set *<NAME> = BUILDER|BOOT
        @set *<NAME> = !BUILDER|!BOOT%]%x

%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xThe %y%lBOOT%x flag is an alias for the %y%lBUILDER%x flag.

The Builder flag may be set/reset on characters by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

Builders have the same privileges as Mortals, except they may build their own locations, objects, compound commands, etc.  However, as a Builder, the amount you can build is limited by your Building Quota limit.  You can find out what your Building Quota limit is, and how much of it is in use at any time by typing '%g%l%(scan%) me%x'.

%PAGE
If you'd like to be a Builder, get in touch with an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above  -  You'll be given a %y%lBUILDER%x flag and will have a Building Quota of %c%l100%x to begin with.  You should use this to experiment with the different types of objects you can make and the various building commands.

If an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above's %y%lBOOT%x (%y%lBUILDER%x) flag is removed, they will no-longer be able to boot users (Using '%g%l%(@boot%)%x'  -  However, they may still use the '%g%l%(@bootdead%)%x' command to boot 'dead'/'locked-up' connections.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<building%>%x', '%g%l%<quota%>%x', '%g%l%<scan%>%x', '%g%l%<@set%>%x', '%g%l%<@boot%>%x' and '%g%l%<@bootdead%>%x'.

