%TOPIC computercontrol
%TOPIC nonplayingcharacters
%TITLE Help the %w%lBEING%x flag
%[%c%l%8USAGE:  %g%l@set *<NAME> = BEING
        @set *<NAME> = !BEING%]%x

The %y%lBEING%x flag may be set on characters by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

A character with their %y%lBEING%x flag set will automatically be excluded from the '%g%l%(admin%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<adminlist%>%x'.)

This is useful for excluding users who are not true 'real' administrators (Although they have the appropriate rank), for example, an inactive %c%lWizard%x character who owns a global area and its associated commands, or an Admin-ranked 'puppet' used by an administrator for building purposes.

The %y%lBEING%x flag is also reserved for future use for virtual computer-controlled characters (Also referred to as  'monsters', 'robots', 'bots' and 'non-playing characters' (NPC's.))
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<adminlist%>%x' and '%g%l%<flags%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC censorflag
%TOPIC censoredflag
%TOPIC censorshipflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lCENSORED%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = CENSORED
        @set <OBJECT> = !CENSORED%]%x

This flag can be set on characters, rooms, things and compound commands.

The %y%lCENSORED%x flag controls whether bad language can be used within a location or by a particular character.

When rooms or things are set %y%lCENSORED%x, characters within them will not be able to use bad language (Attempts will be censored out with '%c%l*%x's.)  The %y%lCENSORED%x flag is ideal for public locations and talking rooms where you don't want people using bad language.

When characters are set %y%lCENSORED%x (This can only be done by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above), they will not be able to use bad language in %r%lANY%x location, regardless of whether it has its %y%l%(CENSORED%)%x flag set or not.  This is ideal for dealing with offensive/abusive users.

%PAGE
Compound commands default to having their %y%lCENSORED%x flag set.  This results in each command line within the compound command being subject to censorship when executed in a %y%lCENSORED%x location or by a %y%lCENSORED%x character.  This is ideal for communications compound commands, but can have adverse results within other compound commands.

%c%lWizards/%cDruids%x and above can reset the %y%lCENSORED%x flag on a compound command, allowing it to execute without being subject to censorship.  However, the command-line typed by the user to execute the compound command will still be subject to censorship appropriately.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<privileges%>%x', '%g%l%<@?censor%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC combatflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lCOMBAT%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = COMBAT
        @set <OBJECT> = !COMBAT%]%x

This flag can only be set on %c%lrooms%x, %c%lthings%x and %c%lcompound commands%x.

In order to use the combat system building commands (Such as '%g%l%(@damage%)%x', etc.), the following conditions must be met:

%r%l%4*  %xAny compound commands containing '%g%l%(@damage%)%x', '%g%l%(@delay%)%x' or '%g%l%(@heal%)%x' (See '%g%l%<@damage%>%x', '%g%l%<@delay%>%x' and '%g%l%<@heal%>%x') must have their %y%lCOMBAT%x flag set in order for these commands to work.

%y%l%4*  %xThey must be executed in a location which also has its %y%lCOMBAT%x flag set.

%r%l%4*  %xThe location must not have its %y%l%(HAVEN%)%x flag set (See '%g%l%<haven flag%>%x'.)

%PAGE
%y%l%4*  %xThe location and the compound command containing the combat commands must have the same owner.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xThe %y%l%(^friend COMBAT%)%x friend flag can be used to allow combat commands built by other users to be used in your combat areas.  See '%g%l%<combat friend flag%>%x' for further details.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<haven flag%>%x', '%g%l%<combat friend flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<combat%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC retired
%TOPIC retiring
%TOPIC retirement
%TOPIC retiredflag
%TOPIC retireddruids
%TOPIC retiredwizards
%TOPIC retirementflag
%TOPIC retiredadministration
%TOPIC retiredadministrators
%TITLE Help on the %w%lRETIRED%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = RETIRED
        @set <OBJECT> = !RETIRED%]%x

This flag can only be set/reset by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

When set on an administrator, this flag indicates that they have retired from their administative duties.  Both %r%lRetired Wizards%x and %rRetired Druids%x have the same privileges as an %r%lExperienced Builder%x (See '%g%l%<experienced builder%>%x') (The rules for %r%lExperienced Builders%x (See '%g%l%<experienced builder rules%>%x') apply to them.)

A retired administrator may also request to have their %y%lHELP%x flag set (See '%g%l%<help flag%>%x'), which entitles them to giving help and assistance to users (If this is set, the rules for %rAssistants%x (See '%g%l%<assistant rules%>%x') also apply to them.)

%PAGE
Retired administrators have no administrative privileges and cannot use commands or access information restricted to administrators only.

Retired administrators will usually be administrators who have been around for a long time, who can no-longer connect (Usually due to lack of time, IRL commitments or lack of access to the Internet) or connect for a sufficient amount of time to participate in general administrative duties.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<experienced builder%>%x', '%g%l%<assistant%>%x', '%g%l%<rules%>%x', '%g%l%<help flag%>%x', '%g%l%<welcome%>%x', '%g%l%<assist%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC chownokflag
%TOPIC transferableflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lTRANSFERABLE%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = TRANSFERABLE
        @set <OBJECT> = !TRANSFERABLE%]%x

This flag cannot be set/reset on characters or alarms.

When this flag is set on an object, any character can take over the ownership of it (Without needing '%c%lwrite%x' permission to its current owner) by typing '%g%l%(@owner%) <OBJECT> = me%x'.

If you take over the ownership of an object with its %y%lTRANSFERABLE%x flag set and do not wish to let other characters take over the ownership of it from you, you should type '%g%l%(@set%) <OBJECT> = !TRANSFERABLE%x' to remove the flag.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@owner%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC aflag
%TOPIC consonants
%TOPIC consonantflag
%TOPIC consonantarticleflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lCONSONANT%x article flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = CONSONANT
        @set <OBJECT> = !CONSONANT%]%x

This flag can only be set on %c%l%(things%)%x, %c%l%(rooms%)%x, %c%l%(exits%)%x and %c%l%(characters%)%x.

When set on one of the above types of object ('%g%l%(@set%) <OBJECT> = CONSONANT%x'), the object will be given the %c%lconsonant%x article (%y%lA%x), e.g:

%g%l%(@set%) television = CONSONANT          %x(Gives '%y%lA Television%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<vowel flag%>%x', '%g%l%<plural flag%>%x', '%g%l%<articles%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC expiryflag
%TOPIC objectexpiryflag
%TITLE Help on the %w%lEXPIRY%x flag
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@set <OBJECT> = EXPIRY
        @set <OBJECT> = [!]EXPIRY%]%x

This flag can only be set/reset on objects.

By default, an object which has an expiry time set (Using the '%g%l%(@expiry%)%x' command  -  See '%g%l%<@expiry%>%x') will expire and be automatically destroyed when its last usage date exceeds its expiry time (In days.)  This means that if the object is used regularly, it will not expire.

If the %y%lEXPIRY%x flag is set on the object, the expiry time will be based on its creation date instead.  This means that the object will expire after the specified amount of time, regardless of whether its being used or not.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@expiry%>%x', '%g%l%<@destroy%>%x' and '%g%l%<@set%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC females
%TOPIC femaleflag
