%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l@unlink <OBJECT>%]%x

'%g%l@unlink%x' removes the link on the specified %y%l<OBJECT>%x, which can either be an exit or a room.

Unlinking a room removes its drop-to, if set (The location objects go to if dropped in that room.)

Unlinking an exit makes the exit lead nowhere, so you can re-link it (Using '%g%l%(@link%)%x') to another location.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xUnlinked exits can be re-linked by another Builder, making them the new owner.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@link%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?destination%>%x'.

