%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%ltutorial [<SUBJECT>]%]%x

When using the On-Line Help System, you may see '%c[%c%l%uTUTORIAL AVAILABLE%c]%x' at the top of some of the help screens.  This means that there is also an in-depth tutorial available on the same subject/command.  To read the tutorial, simply type '%g%ltutorial <SUBJECT>%x' or '%g%ltutorial <COMMAND>%x' (I.e:  If '%g%lhelp @command%x' has a tutorial available, you can read it by typing '%g%ltutorial @command%x'.)

