%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l%(@set%) *<NAME> = APPRENTICE DRUID     %(@set%) *<NAME> = !APPRENTICE
        %(@set%) *<NAME> = WIZARD DRUID         %(@set%) *<NAME> = !WIZARD
        %(@set%) *<NAME> = ELDER DRUID          %(@set%) *<NAME> = !ELDER%]%x

There are three ranks of %cDruid%x administrators:  %yApprentice Druid%x (%ya%x), %cDruid%x (%cw%x) and %gElder Druid%x (%ge%x).

%cDruids%x are mainly social orientated, and should be approached with non-building related questions and problems, especially where abusive and offensive users are concerned.

Building and coding questions should be refered to %c%lWizard%x administrators (See '%g%l%<wizards%>%x'), unless it is a simple question or problem which can easily be answered or dealt with (I.e:  By pointing user to appropriate help page.)  Even if you do refer a question, you should make an attempt to find out the answer, so you can take the correct action the next time you are asked.

%PAGE
The %yApprentice Druid%x status is for new trainee %cDruid%x administrators, to prepare them for duties as a full %cDruid%x.  A user must achieve %rAssistant%x status (See '%g%l%<assistant%>%x') first as a Mortal before they can be promoted to %yApprentice Druid%x status.  This is to ensure that all new %yApprentice Druids%x have the basic skills required for the rank.

%yApprentice Druid%x privileges are mainly read-only, to minimalise causing accidental damage while learning new skills and getting used to administration.  If an %yApprentice Druid%x has any questions or is unsure about how to handle a particular situation, they should ask an administrator of a higher level, preferably a %cDruid%x or %gElder Druid%x.

%cDruids%x and above have full '%c%lread%x' and '%c%lwrite%x' privileges to all users below their level.

The %gElder Druid%x status is reserved for long standing %cDruids%x who have expert knowledge and interpersonal skills.
%PAGE

