%TOPIC promote
%TOPIC promoting
%TOPIC promotions
%TOPIC gettingpromoted
%TITLE Help on %w%lpromotions%x
Every user on %@%n starts off at %(Mortal%) status.  However, sooner or later, you may wish to progress up through the %(ranks%) (See '%g%l%<ranks%>%x'), and possibly eventually into a position within the administration team (Subject to %c%lsuitability%x and %c%lavailability%x.)  Below are brief details on how to go about obtaining promotion to various statuses, and the basic requirements of each.

%c%l%9%4IMPORTANT:  %xPlease %r%l%f%uDO NOT%x repetively ask current administrators to promote you to the statuses listed below.  Doing so may %m%l%ureduce%x your chances of promotion.  We %c%lcannot%x promote everyone, as there are only a %y%llimited number of positions available%x (With the exception of the %(Builder%) status.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Promotion to Builder status...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xThe Builder status allows you to build your own rooms, areas and locations, which can be explored and enjoyed by yourself, friends and other users.  In order to obtain Builder status, you must first ensure that your %c%lprivate%x E-mail address is set (See '%g%l%<@email%>%x' for details), and is valid (If it's already set, and is invalid, please ask a member of Admin. to change it for you, i.e:  '%g%l%(page%) admin = can someone change my private E-mail address for me, please?%x')

Once your private E-mail address is set, simply ask a member of Admin. to make you a Builder, i.e:  '%g%l%(page%) admin = Can I be a Builder, please?%x'

Before considering applying for Builder status, please ensure you both read and fully understand the rules for Builders (See '%g%l%<builder rules%>%x'.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Promotion to Assistant status...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%rAssistant%x status is awarded to %c%lfriendly%x and %c%lhelpful%x users, who are prepared to spend time helping and assisting users, even though they are not Admin.  In order to obtain this status, you will need to ask a member of Admin. to put you up for a vote (All members of Admin. will vote on your suitability for this status, over a period of a week.)  Before doing this, you will first need to prepare a brief summary of your credentials, complete with references from people you have helped and assisted (Give this information to the member of Admin. you ask, so that they can put it into the votable message in the %y%lAdmin%x area of %y%l%@%n BBS%x (See '%g%l%<bbs%>%x'.))  When voting closes, you will be told the result, and promoted if the vote is in favour.

Before considering applying for %rAssistant%x status, please ensure you both read and fully understand the rules for %rAssistants%x (See '%g%l%<assistant rules%x'.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Promotion to Experienced Builder status...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%r%lExperienced Builder%x status is awarded to advanced Builders, with excellent building and compound command (See '%g%l%<@command%>%x') writing skills and knowledge.  In order to obtain this status, you will need to ask a member of Admin. to put you up for a vote (All members of Admin. will vote on your suitability for this status, over a period of a week.)  Before doing this, you will first need to prepare a brief summary of your knowledge/credentials, complete with examples (And %c%l#ID numbers%x) of your best building work to date (Give this information to the member of Admin. you ask, so that they can put it into the votable message in the %y%lAdmin%x area of %y%l%@%n BBS%x (See '%g%l%<bbs%>%x'.))  When voting closes, you will be told the result, and promoted if the vote is in favour.

Before considering applying for %r%lExperienced Builder%x status, please ensure you both read and fully understand the rules for %r%lExperienced Builders%x (See '%g%l%<experienced builder rules%>%x'.)

%PAGE

%c%l%$Promotion to Apprentice Wizard or Apprentice Druid status (Admin)...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xTo be promoted to an %y%lApprentice Wizard%x you must first achieve promotion to %r%lExperienced Builder%x status.  Likewise, you must achieve promotion to %rAssistant%x status before you can be promoted to %yApprentice Druid%x status.

Every few months, an %c%lAdmin Review%x takes place, where the status of current administrators is reviewed, and new administrators are promoted (If new Admin. are required and sufficient positions are available.)

If new administrators are required, current administrators will vote on suitable %r%lExperienced Builder%x and %rAssistant%x candidates.  Those with votes with %y%l60% majority%x in favour of promotion will be promoted.

%PAGE
The following credentials of each suitable candidate are considered by administrators voting in the Admin Review (In no particular order of importance):

   %4%y%lResponsibility%x, %y%lknowledge%x, %y%lexperience%x, %y%lfairness%x, %y%lmaturity%x, %y%lbuilding skill%x (%y%lApprentice Wizard%x), %y%linterpersonal skills%x, %y%lintegrity%x, %y%ltrustworthiness%x and %y%lstability%x.

Before considering applying for either %y%lApprentice Wizard%x or %yApprentice Druid%x status, please ensure you both read and fully understand the basic guidelines, rules and duties for administrators (See '%g%l%<admin rules%>%x' and '%g%l%<admin duties%>%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<builder%>%x', '%g%l%<assistant%>%x', '%g%l%<experienced%>%x', '%g%l%<apprentices%>%x', '%g%l%<ranks%>%x' and '%g%l%<rules%>%x'.

