%TITLE Help on '%w%lfadd%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lfriend <NAME> [= [!]<FLAG> [[!]<FLAG>] [...]]
        fadd <NAME> [= [!]<FLAG> [[!]<FLAG>] [...]]%]%x

The '%g%lfadd%x' (Or '%g%lfriend%x' if you prefer  -  The choice is yours) command is used to add a friend to your friends list, e.g:  '%g%lfadd fred bloggs%x' will add the user '%y%lFred Bloggs%x' to your friends list.

Optionally, friend flags to set/reset on the new friend can also be specified, i.e:  '%g%lfadd fred bloggs = !%(^friend pagetellfriends%)%x' will make the user '%y%lFred Bloggs%x' your friend and also reset their %y%l%(^friend PAGETELLFRIENDS%)%x friend flag (See '%g%l%<pagetellfriends friend flag%>%x'), so that you will not receive %g%l%(page%)%xs/%g%l%(tell%)%xs from them which they send to their friends.  For full details of the flags you can set/reset, please see '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xThe friend you'd like to add doesn't have to be connected.

       %8Typing '%g%lfriends%x' without any parameters will display the friends user list ('%g%l%(fwho%)%x'  -  See '%g%l%<fwho%>%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<fremove%>%x' and '%g%l%<friends%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC fc
%TOPIC fchat
%TOPIC fchattingchannel
%TOPIC friendschattingchannel
%TITLE Help on '%w%lfchat%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lfchat <MESSAGE>
        fchat on|off%]%x

The '%g%lfchat%x' command is used to speak over the friends chatting channel or turn it on/off.

You can use the friends chatting channel to speak to all your friends at once (Including those not on your friends list, but you're on theirs (Listed in '%g%l%(fwho%)%x' (See '%g%l%<fwho%>%x') with their name in square brackets ('%y%l[]%x'))  -  However, your message wont go to friends who aren't connected or have turned the friends chatting channel off by typing '%g%lfchat off%x' (These people are listed in '%g%l%(fwho%)%x' with their name in '%y%l<>%x's.)

%PAGE
You can stop receiving messages from particular friends over the friends chatting channel by removing their %y%lFCHAT%x friend flag  -  See '%g%l%<fset%>%x' for details on how to do this.

Typing '%g%lfchat off%x' turns the friends chatting channel facility off (So you no-longer get disturbed by messages being sent over it by friends, e.g:  When you want to do some building.)  Typing '%g%lfchat on%x' will turn it back on again.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<chat%>%x' and '%g%l%<friends%>%x'.

