%TOPIC otherfriends
%TITLE Help on '%w%lflist%x' and '%w%lfothers%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lfothers [<PAGE NO>] [<NAME>] [= <FLAG SPEC>]
        flist [<PAGE NO>] [<NAME>] [= <FLAG SPEC>]%]%x
  
The '%g%lflist%x' command is used to list everyone on your friends list, and the '%g%lfothers%x' command is used to list everyone who has you on their friends list.

If %y%l<NAME>%x is specified, only users with names matching or containing the text %y%l<NAME>%x will be listed (I.e:  '%g%lflist fred%x' will list friends who are on your friends list and have the text '%y%lfred%x' in their name (E.g:  '%y%lFred%x', '%y%lFred Bloggs%x', '%y%lFreda%x', '%y%lFrederick%x', '%y%lWilfred%x', etc.))

Admin can list the friends of other characters by specifying the user's full name, prefixed with '%y%l*%x', e.g:  '%g%lflist *fred bloggs%x' to display the user %c%lFred Blogg%x's friends list.  Alternatively, the %y%l#ID%x number of the user can be used.

%PAGE
If %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, that page of users will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%lflist 1%x', '%g%lflist 2%x', '%g%lfothers 1%x', '%g%lfothers 2%x', etc.

If %y%l<FLAG SPEC>%x is specified, only characters with the given flags will be listed  -  These can either be friend flags (E.g:  '%g%lflist = inform%x', '%g%lflist = !pagetell%x', '%g%lflist = enemy !pagetell !link%x', etc.), standard %@%m flags (See '%g%l%<@set%>%x', e.g:  '%g%lflist = %(haven%)%x', '%g%lflist = %(male%)%x', etc.), '%y%ladmin%x' (%y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above), '%y%lmortals%x' or '%y%lall%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<friends%>%x'.

