Allows you to set/reset friend flags on your friends in your friends list.

To set a friend flag on one of your friends, simply type '%g%lfset <NAME> = <FLAG>%x', e.g:  '%g%lfset fred = inform%x'.  To reset a friend flag, simply type '%g%lfset <NAME> = !<FLAG>%x', e.g:  '%g%lfset fred = !pagetell%x'.

You can test whether you have set/reset particular friend flags on a user, or whether they have set/reset them on you, using the '%g%l{%(@?set%)}%x' query command (See '%g%l%<@?set%>%x'.)

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xFor security, efficiency and integrity, %y%l%(^friend READ%)%x, %y%l%(^friend WRITE%)%x, %y%l%(^friend CREATE%)%x and %y%l%(^friend DESTROY%)%x privileges gained via friend flags do not apply within compound commands.  They are only effective when used on the command-line (Outside of a compound command.)
%PAGE

%c%l%$The following friend flags may be set/reset on your friends...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%y%l%(^friend Beep%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Combat%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Commands%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Create%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Destroy%)%x, %r%l%(^friend Enemy%)%x, %m%l%(^friend Exclude%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Fchat%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Inform%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Link%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Mail%)%x, %y%l%(^friend PageTell%)%x, %y%l%(^friend PageTellFriends%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Read%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Sharable%)%x, %y%l%(^friend Visit%)%x and %y%l%(^friend Write%)%x.
<-SEPARATOR->
Further help is available on the above friend flags  -  Simply type '%g%lhelp <FLAG NAME> friend flag%x', where %y%l<FLAG NAME>%x is the name of the flag you want help on, e.g:  '%g%l%<inform friend flag%>%x'.  %c%lAlso, see '%g%l%<friends%>%c%l'.

