%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lfset <NAME> [=] BEEP
        fset <NAME> [=] !BEEP%]%x

When this friend flag is set on one of your friends, your computer/terminal will beep whenever they connect (Providing you're set %y%l%(LISTEN%)%x (See '%g%l%<listen flag%>%x') or you've set their %y%l%(^friend INFORM%)%x (See '%g%l%<inform friend flag%>%x') friend flag.)

If you set your %y%l%(QUIET%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<quiet flag%>%x'), this will usually override the effects of the %y%l%(LISTEN%)%x flag and/or %y%l%(^friend INFORM%)%x friend flag.  You can make it so that you are always informed when a particular user connects (Regardless of %y%l%(QUIET%)%x flag) by setting both their %y%l%(^friend INFORM%)%x and %y%lBEEP%x friend flags.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<inform friend flag%>%x', '%g%l%<listen flag%>%x', '%g%l%<quiet flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.

