Without this friend flag, they %c%lwill not%x be able to create, destroy or modify your compound commands, regardless of permissions given to them via friend flags.

Giving permission to users to create or modify your compound commands is %r%l%u%fEXTREMELY DANGEROUS%x, because this will allow them to modify your compound commands at will to give them full '%c%lread%x' and '%c%lwrite%x' privileges to your objects %r%l%uAND%x your character.

%PAGE
%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xFor security, efficiency and integrity, %y%l%(^friend READ%)%x, %y%l%(^friend WRITE%)%x, %y%l%(^friend CREATE%)%x and %y%l%(^friend DESTROY%)%x privileges gained via friend flags do not apply within compound commands.  They are only effective when used on the command-line (Outside of a compound command.)

