        fset <NAME> [=] !ENEMY%]%x

When this friend flag is set on one of your friends, it makes them an %r%lenemy%x of yours.  On its own, this friend flag has very little effect, apart from changing '%g%l(Friend)%x' to '%r%l(Enemy)%x', etc.

If you ever get abused or harassed by another user, and there's no Admin around at the time to sort the problem out, you can use friend flags to your advantage, e.g:  Simply add them to your friends list ('%g%l%(fadd%) <NAME>%x'  -  See '%g%l%<fadd%>%x') and then type '%g%l%(fset%) <NAME> = enemy !%(fchat%) !%(link%) !%(mail%) !%(pagetell%)%x' (See '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.)  This will make it very difficult for this user to continue abusing/harassing you (Unless you stay in the same room as them.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<emergency%>%x', '%g%l%<complain%>%x', '%g%l%<fadd%>%x', '%g%l%<fchat friend flag%>%x', '%g%l%<link friend flag%>%x', '%g%l%<mail friend flag%>%x', '%g%l%<pagetell friend flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.

