Displays a list of all your friends who are currently connected in columns (Similar to the '%g%l%(swho%)%x' (See '%g%l%<swho%>%x') command.)

Any names displayed in square brackets ('%y%l[]%x') are people who have you in their friends list, but you don't have them in yours.  Any name displayed in '%y%l<>%x's is a friend (Either in your friends list or you're in theirs) who has turned off the friends chatting channel (See '%g%l%<fchat%>%x'), have removed your %y%lFCHAT%x friend flag (See '%g%l%<fset%>%x') in their friends list, or you've removed theirs (These characters wont receive messages sent by you over '%g%l%(fchat%)%x', and you wont receive messages from them.)  Any names displayed in '%y%l{}%x's are people who are your enemies.

%PAGE
If %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, the list of users will be split up into pages and the page number specified will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%lfwho 1%x', '%g%lfwho 2%x', etc.

If %y%l<NAME>%x is specified, just that one character is listed.  If one or more flags (Separated by spaces) are specified instead of %y%l<NAME>%x, only characters with those flags are listed, e.g:  '%g%lfwho admin%x', '%g%lfwho mortals%x', '%g%lfwho haven quiet%x', etc.

Some characters in the list may have a symbol to the left of their name  -  See '%g%l%<swho%>%x' for details of their meaning.

