%TOPIC wildcards
%TOPIC wildcardcharacters
%TITLE Help on %w%lwildcards%x
Wildcards may be used with '%g%l%(@find%)%x', '%g%l%(@with%)%x', '%g%l%(@site list%)%x' and '%g%l%(@reload%)%x', as well as any compound commands which make use of the '%g%l{%(@?wildcard%)}%x' query.  They allow you to be more specific about what you'd like found, e.g:  '%g%l%(@find%) computer%x' will only find objects with the %c%lEXACT%x name '%y%lcomputer%x', whereas '%g%l%(@find%) *computer*%x' will find all objects with the string '%y%lcomputer%x' in their name.  There are two wildcard characters used in %@%n  -  These are '%y%l*%x' and '%y%l?%x'...

The '%y%l*%x' wildcard represents %c%lANY%x text at that point, providing the text to the left and/or right of the '%y%l*%x' is matched, e.g:  '%y%l*%x' on it's own will match %c%lANY%x text, '%y%l*the*%x' will only match text which has the letters '%y%lthe%x' in it (In that order), '%y%lan*%x' will only match text which %c%lBEGINS%x with the letters '%y%lan%x' and '%y%l*er%x' will only match text which %c%lENDS%x with the letters '%y%ler%x'.

%PAGE
You can use more than one '%y%l*%x' in a wildcard specification if you like, e.g:  '%y%l*the*and*%x' will only match text which has the letters '%y%lthe%x' in it %c%lFOLLOWED%x by the letters '%y%land%x'.

The '%y%l?%x' wildcard represents %c%lANY%x single character at that point, e.g:  '%y%lroom?%x' will match with '%y%lroom1%x', '%y%lroom6%x', '%y%lrooma%x', '%y%lroomf%x', etc.  %c%lPLEASE NOTE:%x  '%y%l?%x' %c%lCANNOT%x represent a blank character, e.g:  '%y%lroom?%x' %c%lWILL NOT%x match with '%y%lroom%x'.

If no wildcards are used, only text which %c%lEXACTLY%x matches the wildcard specification will be matched, e.g:  '%y%lthis%x' will %c%lONLY%x match to the %c%lEXACT%x text '%y%lthis%x'.

%PAGE
The table below shows several example wildcard specifications, and what they match with from the list of words:  %y%lan%x, %y%land%x, %y%lAndrew%x, %y%lant%x, %y%lanother%x, %y%lanswer%x, %y%lexact%x, %y%lflatoutrunning%x, %y%lgamer%x, %y%llongrun%x, %y%lMatthew%x, %y%lpanther%x, %y%lprogrammer%x, %y%lran%x, %y%lrun%x, %y%lrunner%x, %y%lroom1%x, %y%lroom6%x, %y%lrooma%x, %y%lroomf%x, %y%lthe%x, %y%lthere%x, %y%lthesis%x, %y%luser%x...


%[%c%lWildcard spec:  Matches with (From above list of words)...
%c=============================================================================
%g%lexact           %y%lexact
%g%l*the*           %y%lanother%w, %y%lMatthew%w, %y%lpanther%w, %y%lthe%w, %y%lthere%w, %y%lthesis
%g%lan*             %y%lan%w, %y%land%w, %y%lAndrew%w, %y%lant%w, %y%lanother%w, %y%lanswer
%g%l*er             %y%lanother%w, %y%lanswer%w, %y%lgamer%w, %y%lpanther%w, %y%lprogrammer%w, %y%lrunner%w, %y%luser
%g%l*a*e*           %y%lAndrew%w, %y%lanother%w, %y%lanswer%w, %y%lgamer%w, %y%lMatthew%w, %y%lpanther%w, %y%lprogrammer
%g%lroom?           %y%lroom1%w, %y%lroom6%w, %y%lrooma%w, %y%lroomf
%g%lr?n             %y%lran%w, %y%lrun
%g%l*r?n*           %y%lflatoutrunning%w, %y%llongrun%w, %y%lran%w, %y%lrun%w, %y%lrunner
%c============================================================================%]

%PAGE
%8%c%lHINT:  %xWhen performing searches with '%g%l%(@find%)%x' (Which uses wildcards), you can search for all occurrences of a given word or piece of text using '%y%l*<WORD>*%x' or '%y%l*<TEXT>*%x', e.g:  To find rooms with the word '%y%lroom%x' in their name, you could type '%g%l%(@find%) room name = *room*%x'.  Similarly, you could find objects (Things) with the word '%y%lthe%x' in their description using '%g%l%(@find%) thing desc = *the*%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@find%>%x', '%g%l%<@with%>%x', '%g%l%<@?wildcard%>%x', '%g%l%<@site list%>%x' and '%g%l%<@reload%>%x'.

