%TOPIC speaking
%TOPIC communication
%TOPIC communicating
%TOPIC conversations
%TITLE How to chat to other users of %@%n
There are several ways of chatting/communicating with other users on %@%n  -  These are:

%[%g%l%("%)<MESSAGE>%x   Makes you say "%y%l<MESSAGE>%x" to everyone in the same room as you.
%g%l%(?%)<QUESTION>%x  Makes you ask "%y%l<QUESTION>%x".
%g%l%(+%)<THOUGHT>%x   Makes you think  %y%l. o O ( %w%l<THOUGHT>%y%l )
%g%l%(:%)<MESSAGE>%x   Shows your name, with %y%l<MESSAGE>%x after it.  Used for actions.
%g%l%(converse%)%x     '%c%l%(converse%)%x' mode (See '%g%l%<converse%>%x' before using.)

%g%l%(yell%) <MESSAGE>%x  Yells %y%l<MESSAGE>%x to everyone in the same area as you.

%g%l%(whisper%) <NAME> [=] <MESSAGE>%x  Secretly whispers %y%l<MESSAGE>%x to the character
                              %y%l<NAME>%x.

%g%l%(tell%) <NAME> [=] <MESSAGE>%x     Tells %y%l<MESSAGE>%x to character %y%l<NAME>%x.

%g%l%(page%) <NAME> [=] <MESSAGE>%x     Pages %y%l<MESSAGE>%x to character %y%l<NAME>%x.%]%x

You can use %g%l%('%)%x or %g%l%(`%)%x instead of %g%l%("%)%x if you prefer, when speaking.

