%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lemaillist [<PAGE NO>] [<NAME>|<FLAGS>] [= public|private|<NUMBER>]
        email [<PAGE NO>] [<NAME>|<FLAGS>] [= public|private|<NUMBER>]%]%x

The '%g%lemaillist%x' command (Which can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above) displays a list of connected characters and their %c%lprivate%x E-mail addresses (If set.)

By default, the %c%lprivate%x (%c%l2nd%x) E-mail address of each connected character is listed.  By specifying '%y%lpublic%x' for the second parameter (I.e:  '%g%lemaillist = public%x'), you can list all connected characters, along with their %c%l1st public%x E-mail address (If set.)  Likewise, specifying a number between %y%l3%x and %y%l5%x will list all connected characters with their appropriate %c%lpublic%x E-mail address.

%PAGE
