%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lbug <BUG REPORT>
        comment <COMMENT>
        complain <COMPLAINT>
        suggest <SUGGESTION>%]%x

The above commands are used to report bugs, make comments, complaints or suggestions.  When used, all administrators (%y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above) who are not set %y%l%(QUIET%)%x (See '%g%l%<quiet flag%>%x') are informed, and an entry is made in the appropriate log file ('%y%lBugs%x', '%y%lComments%x', '%y%lComplaints%x' and '%y%lSuggestions%x' log files  -  See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.)

%PAGE
'%g%lbug%x' is primarily used to report bugs in the 'hard' code (TCZ source code  -  See '%g%l%<tcz%>%x' and '%g%l%<gpl%>%x'), but can also be used to report bugs in 'soft' code (Compound commands (See '%g%l%<@command%>%x') created and written by Builders and above (See '%g%l%<builder%>%x') as a last resort.  With 'soft' code bugs, you should attempt to contact the creator of the defective compound command(s) so that they can resolve the problem(s) (Type '%g%l%(ex%) <COMMAND NAME>%x' (See '%g%l%<ex%>%x') to find out who owns a particular compound command.)  Bug reports are logged to the '%y%lBugs%x' log file.

'%g%lcomment%x' is used to make comments about %@%m, its administrators, builders and users (I.e:  Those who should perhaps be promoted in the near future), and anything else related which the administrators may wish to know about.  Comments are logged to the '%y%lComments%x' log file.

%PAGE
'%g%lcomplain%x' is used to make complaints of any nature, so that Admin. can deal with and resolve them as quickly as possible.  I.e:  If you are being harassed, abused or offended by another user, please use '%g%lcomplain%x' to complain to Admin. so that they can be stopped.  Complaints are logged to the '%y%lComplaints%x' log file.

'%g%lsuggest%x' is used to make a suggestion for improvement to %@%m and its database.  Such suggestions can include improvements to %@%m itself and its 'hard' code, 'soft' coded compound commands and areas on %@%m, on-line help pages and tutorials, etc.  Suggestions are logged to the '%y%lSuggestions%x' log file.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %x'%g%lcomplain%x' replaces the '%g%lgripe%x' command, which is now obsolete.
       %8'%g%lgripe%x' is now an alias for the '%g%lcomplain%x' command.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<emergency%>%x', '%g%l%<bug fixes%>%x' and '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.

