%TITLE Help on '%w%lhome%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lhome homeroom
        home <#ID>
        home here
        home room
        home%]%x

Typing '%g%lhome%x' on its own with no parameters will send you back to your home location.

Typing '%g%l%(homeroom%)%x', '%g%lhome room%x' or '%g%lhome%x' (If your home room is your current home, or '%g%lhome%x' twice if not) will take you to your home room (Every character is given a home room when they are first created  -  See '%g%l%<@homeroom%>%x'.)

Typing '%g%lhome home%x' or '%g%lhome homeroom%x' will set your home location to your home room, so typing '%g%lhome%x' will always take you there.

You can set your home to any room which either belongs to you or has its %y%l%(ABODE%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<abode flag%>%x') set (I.e:  You can see it's #ID number when you type '%g%l%(look%)%x' while in the room.)

%PAGE
To set your home, simply type '%g%lhome here%x' while you are in the room you wish to make your home.  Alternatively, if you know the room's #ID number, simply type '%g%lhome <#ID>%x', where %y%l<#ID>%x is the #ID number of number, e.g:  '%g%lhome #12345%x'.

%c%l%8NOTE:  %xYou can also set your home using the '%g%l%(@link%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@link%>%x'), but the above method is far easier.


%y%l%$*HOME*%c%l%$ in csuccess/cfailure of compound commands
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xIf the csuccess/cfailure branch of a compound command is set to '%y%lhome%x', %@%m will continue searching up the area-tree for another compound command with the same name as the compound command currently being executed and execute it.

Setting the csuccess/cfailure branch of '%g%l%(.enter%)%x', '%g%l%(.leave%)%x', '%g%l%(.login%)%x' and '%g%l%(.logout%)%x' compound commands to '%y%lhome%x' allows further '%g%l%(.enter%)%x', '%g%l%(.leave%)%x', etc. compound commands up the area-tree to be executed.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<homeroom%>%x', '%g%l%<@link%>%x', '%g%l%<@csucc%>%x', '%g%l%<@cfail%>%x', '%g%l%<.enter%>%x', '%g%l%<.leave%>%x', '%g%l%<.login%>%x' and '%g%l%<.logout%>%x'.

