'%g%lkick%x' allows you to kick an offensive character out of one of your rooms into the %y%lJunk Pile%x (%c%l#0%x.)  If the kicked character's home is set to one of your rooms, their home will be reset to the %y%lJunk Pile%x (%c%l#0%x) so they can't return too easily.  When you kick someone, you should give a %y%l<REASON>%x, e.g:  '%g%lkick fred = for being offensive%x'.

'%g%ljunk%x' allows you to junk an object (Even if it's locked against you) that belongs to someone else that's been left lying around on your property to the %y%lJunk Pile%x (%c%l#0%x.)

%c%l%9%6PLEASE NOTE:  %xIn order to allow %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x to remove unwanted objects from public locations, %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x may junk %c%lMORTAL%x owned objects (%c%lWizards/%cDruids%x and above can do this too of course, with their %c%lread/write%x privileges.)
