%TOPIC uselessobjects
%TITLE Help on %w%ljunked objects%x...
When an object is junked using the '%g%l%(junk%)%x' (See '%g%l%<junk%>%x') command, it is sent to a special location known as the junk pile, which is room %y%l#0%x (%c%lROOMZERO%x) in the database.

Objects in this location (With the exception of characters) are treated as being no-longer needed or wanted by their owner or anyone else, and they will usually be automatically destroyed after a period of %c%l1 month%x, if they are not claimed by their owner or somebody else.

You can easily check to see whether any of your objects have been junked by typing '%g%l%(@list%) junked all%x'.  If any objects are listed, you may wish to recover some or all of them before they are automatically destroyed.

To recover an object which has been junked, simply type '%g%l%(@tel%) <OBJECT> = <LOCATION>%x' (See '%g%l%<@tel%>%x'), where %y%l<OBJECT>%x is the #ID number of the junked object, and %y%l<LOCATION>%x is the #ID of the location you would like to teleport it to (You can specify '%y%lme%x' or '%y%lhere%x' as %y%l<LOCATION>%x to teleport the object to yourself or your current location respectively.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<junk%>%x', '%g%l%<ashcan flag%>%x', '%g%l%<@list%>%x', '%g%l%<@tel%>%x', '%g%l%<@destroy%>%x', '%g%l%<@expiry%>%x', '%g%l%<@maintenance%>%x' and '%g%l%<@admin%>%x'.

