For Admin, '%g%llast%x' displays a list of all connected characters who are of a lower level, along with the command they last typed and executed.

For Mortals, '%g%llast%x' only displays your own last command, and those of your puppet(s), if connected.

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %x'%g%llast%x' %c%lCAN NOT%x be used to secretly snoop on your private conversations.  All spoken text (Including pages, tells and talking on chatting channels) is %c%l%ucensored%x.  You can always see your own last command, and those of your puppet(s).

If %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, the list of users will be split up into pages and the page number specified will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%llast 1%x', '%g%llast 2%x', etc.

%PAGE
If %y%l<NAME>%x is specified, just that one character is listed.  If one or more flags (Separated by spaces) are specified instead of %y%l<NAME>%x, only characters with those flags are listed, e.g:  '%g%llast admin%x', '%g%llast haven quiet%x', etc.
