%TITLE Help on '%w%llastseen%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%llastseen [<PAGE NO>] [<NAME>|friends|admin|enemies]%]%x

Ranks and lists every user in the database by how long ago they last connected to %@%m.  You can also use this command to find out how long ago a particular user connected ('%g%llastseen <NAME>%x') and when your friends last connected ('%g%llastseen friends%x'.)

By default, the first page of users (I.e:  Those who last connected most recently) will be displayed.  However, if %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, that page of users will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%llastseen 2%x' to display the %c%l2nd%x page, '%g%llastseen 3%x' to display the %c%l3rd%x, etc.

%PAGE
'%g%llastseen%x' ranks every user in the database by default, however you can rank your friends list by typing '%g%llastseen friends%x' or '%g%llastseen enemies%x', and rank current administrators of %@%m by typing '%g%llastseen admin%x'.

You can see when a particular user last connected by typing '%g%llastseen <NAME>%x', e.g:  '%g%llastseen fred bloggs%x' will tell you when the user '%y%lFred Bloggs%x' last connected, and how long ago that was.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xEach time '%g%llastseen%x' is used, every user in the database will be ranked using efficient internal sorting algorithms.  This means that the list is always fully up-to-date.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<spod%>%x', '%g%l%<longspod%>%x', '%g%l%<@rank%>%x', '%g%l%<friends%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?lastconnected%>%x'.

