The '%g%lsession%x' command allows you to set the current session, give your comment on it and list everyone else's comments.

To set the current session, simply type '%g%lsession title <TITLE>%x', where %y%l<TITLE>%x is the title of session (Up to %c%l155 characters%x in length.)  The session may only be changed once every %c%l15 minutes%x (However, if you make a mistake when setting the session title, you may correct it up to %c%l1 minute%x after you've set it.)

Once the session has been set, you can leave your comment on it by typing '%g%lsession comment <COMMENT>%x' (Up to %c%l55 characters%x in length.)  You can reset your session comment by typing '%g%lsession comment%x'.

%PAGE
