%TOPIC longspod
%TOPIC longestspod
%TITLE Help on '%w%llongspod%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%llongspod [<PAGE NO>] [<NAME>|friends|admin|enemies]%]%x

Ranks and lists every user in the database (Except puppets) by their longest connect time (The longest amount of time they've spent in one go connected to %@%m without disconnecting.)

By default, the first page of users (I.e:  Those with the highest longest connect time) will be displayed.  However, if %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, that page of users will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%llongspod 2%x' to display the %c%l2nd%x page, '%g%llongspod 3%x' to display the %c%l3rd%x, etc.

'%g%llongspod%x' ranks every user in the database by default, however you can rank your friends list by typing '%g%llongspod friends%x' or '%g%llongspod enemies%x', and rank current administrators of %@%m by typing '%g%llongspod admin%x'.

%PAGE
You can see the position of an individual user by typing '%g%llongspod <NAME>%x', e.g:  '%g%llongspod me%x' will tell you where you are in the list (Out of all of the other characters in the database) and '%g%llongspod fred bloggs%x' will tell you where the user '%y%lFred Bloggs%x' is in the list.

You can also list users in a given range of positions by typing '%g%llongspod <FROM>-<TO>%x', e.g:  '%g%llongspod 100-150%x' will list users in the positions %y%l100%x to %y%l150%x.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xEach time '%g%llongspod%x' is used, every user in the database will be ranked using efficient internal sorting algorithms.  This means that the list is always fully up-to-date.

       %8Puppets are excluded from the list of users.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, '%g%l%<spod%>%x', '%g%l%<lastseen%>%x', '%g%l%<@rank%>%x', '%g%l%<friends%>%x' and '%g%l%<@?longesttime%>%x'.

