%TOPIC majority
%TOPIC majorityfactor
%TOPIC majorityfactorvotes
%TITLE Help on votes subject to the '%w%lmajority factor%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%l[%(bbs%)] %(^bbs vote%) <NUMBER> [=] majority|normal%]%x

Using the '%g%l%(^bbs vote%) <NUMBER> majority%x' BBS command (See '%g%l%<bbs vote%>%x'), the votes of a message on the BBS can be made subject to the '%c%lmajority factor%x', which weights the votes on the message depending on the rank of each voter.  The 'majority factor' is a percentage in favour, which is worked out by dividing the total score of votes in each direction (%y%lFor%x, %y%lagainst%x and %y%labstain%x) and dividing them into the total score for every single vote cast on the message.


%c%l%$The vote weighting is as follows...
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%b%lMoron%c:  %w%l0%c, %w%lMortal/Builder%c:  %w%l1%c, %r%lExperienced Builder/%rAssistant%c:  %w%l2%c, %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%c:  %w%l3%c, %c%lWizard/%cDruid%c:  %w%l4%c, %g%lElder Wizard/%gDruid%c:  %w%l5%c, %m%lDeity/The Supreme Being%c:  %w%l6%c.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<bbs vote%>%x' and '%g%l%<bbscmds%>%x'.

