The '%g%lmodules%x' command displays a complete list of source code modules.

Typing '%g%lmodules%x' without a name of a module will display a complete list of all modules.  The first page of modules will be displayed.  You can display the other pages using '%g%lmodules <PAGE NO>%x', e.g:  '%g%lmodules 2%x'.

If you are interested in a particular module, you can type '%g%lmodule <NAME>%x' to view full information (Including authors) about the module.  For example, '%g%lmodule tcz.c%x' will display full information about the module '%y%ltcz.c%x'.

The '%g%lmodules%x' command ensures that authors of TCZ source code (See '%g%l%<tcz%>%x' and '%g%l%<gpl%>%x') modules are given credit and acknowledgement where due.  It also allows users to find out who was responsible for their favourite parts of TCZ.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<authors%>%x', '%g%l%<version info%>%x', '%g%l%<bug fixes%>%x', '%g%l%<acknowledgements%>%x', '%g%l%<tcz%>%x' and '%g%l%<version%>%x'.

