%TOPIC recallingtells
%TITLE Help on '%w%lrecall%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lrecall <NUMBER>
        recall list
        recall last%]%x

The '%g%lrecall%x' command allows you to recall the last 8 messages sent to you via '%g%l%(page%)%x' or '%g%l%(tell%)%x'.

Typing '%g%lrecall%x' on its own (Without any parameters) will recall the last message sent to you (Along with the time, date and who it was from.)

'%g%lrecall list%x' will list the names of the senders of the last 8 messages, along with the time and date.  You can see the actual message by typing '%g%lrecall <NUMBER>%x', where %y%l<NUMBER>%x is the number of the message, e.g:  '%g%lrecall 1%x'.

You can reply to the last message you received by typing '%g%l%(reply%) <MESSAGE>%x' (See '%g%l%<reply%>%x') or reply to the message %y%l<NUMBER>%x in the list by typing '%g%l%(page%) <NUMBER> <MESSAGE>%x' or '%g%l%(tell%) <NUMBER> <MESSAGE>%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x', '%g%l%<reply%>%x' and '%g%l%<repeat%>%x'.

