%TITLE Help on '%w%lrepeat%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lrepeat <NAME>[,<NAME>][,<NAME>...]%]%x

Repeats (Re-sends) the last message you sent via '%g%l%(page%)%x' or '%g%l%(tell%)%x', sending it to another character or group of characters.

This command is ideal when you accidentally send a message to the wrong person, allowing you to send it to the correct person without having to retype the message all over again.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x', '%g%l%<recall%>%x' and '%g%l%<reply%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC reply
%TOPIC replying
%TITLE Help on '%w%lreply%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lreply <MESSAGE>%]%x

Replies to the sender of the last message you received via '%g%l%(page%)%x' or '%g%l%(tell%)%x'.

If you accidentally send a reply to the wrong person when using this command (I.e:  Someone else sends you a message while you're typing your reply), you can re-send your reply to the correct person by typing '%g%l%(repeat%) <NAME>%x' (See '%g%l%<repeat%>%x'), where %y%l<NAME>%x is the name of the person.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x', '%g%l%<recall%>%x' and '%g%l%<repeat%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC ride
%TOPIC riding
%TOPIC ridingvehicles
%TITLE Help on '%w%lride%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lride <VEHICLE> = <DIRECTION>%]%x

The '%g%lride%x' command is used to ride a vehicle which can't be entered and driven (Using the '%g%l%(enter%)%x' and '%g%l%(drive%)%x' commands (See '%g%l%<ride%>%x' and '%g%l%<drive%>%x')), such as a %c%lmotorcycle%x, %c%lhorse%x, %c%lbicycle%x, etc.

%y%l<VEHICLE>%x is the name of the vehicle, which must be in the same location as you.  %y%l<DIRECTION>%x is the name of the %c%l%(exit%)%x to ride it through, the %c%l#ID number%x of an %y%l%(ABODE%)%x room (See '%g%l%<abode flag%>%x') or the name of a %c%lconnected character%x, e.g:  '%g%ldrive east%x'.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xA vehicle can only be ridden into locations which have their %y%l%(TRANSPORT%)%x flag set (See '%g%l%<transport flag%>%x'.)  A vehicle can't be ridden through an exit which doesn't have its %y%l%(TRANSPORT%)%x flag set.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<drive%>%x', '%g%l%<transport%>%x', '%g%l%<transport flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<abode flag%>%x'.

