%TOPIC .page
%TOPIC .pagecommand
%TOPIC .pagecompoundcommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.page%x' compound command
If you have a compound command on you called '%y%l.page%x', it will be executed when someone successfully pages a message to you.  Within the '%y%l.page%x' compound command, %y%l$1%x holds the name of the person who paged you, and %y%l$2%x holds their message.


%c%l%$Example:
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@command%) .page = |%(page%) $1 = :acknowledges your message and thanks you for
    paging %%o.%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<recall%>%x', '%g%l%<.tell%>%x' and '%g%l%<.message%>%x'.

