%TOPIC .profile
%TOPIC .profilecommand
%TOPIC .profilecompoundcommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.profile%x' compound command
If you have a compound command on you called '%y%l.profile%x', it will be executed whenever someone views your profile (Providing you have set one.)  Within the '%y%l.profile%x' compound command, %y%l$1%x holds the name of the person who viewed your profile.  Example:


%c%l%$Example:
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@command%) .profile = %(@echo%) %%m%%l[%%w%%l$1 %%m%%lviewed your profile.]%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<profile%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC .scan
%TOPIC .scancommand
%TOPIC .scancompoundcommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.scan%x' compound command
If you have a compound command on you called '%y%l.scan%x', it will be executed whenever someone scans you.  Within the '%y%l.scan%x' compound command, %y%l$1%x holds the name of the person who scanned you.


%c%l%$Example:
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@command%) .scan = %(@echo%) %%r%%l[%%w%%l$1 %%r%%lscanned you.]%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<scan%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC .tell
%TOPIC .tellcommand
%TOPIC .tellcompoundcommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.tell%x' compound command
If you have a compound command on you called '%y%l.tell%x', it will be executed when someone successfully tells a message to you.  Within the '%y%l.tell%x' compound command, %y%l$1%x holds the name of the person who told the message to you, and %y%l$2%x holds their message.


%c%l%$Example:
%~%c~~~~~~~~
%[%g%l%(@command%) .tell = |%(tell%) $1 = :acknowledges your message and thanks you for contacting %%o.%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<tell%>%x', '%g%l%<recall%>%x', '%g%l%<.page%>%x' and '%g%l%<.message%>%x'.

