%TOPIC privileges
%TITLE Help on '%w%lprivileges%x' (Or '%w%lprivs%x')
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lprivileges [<NAME>]%]%x

Lists your privileges in the room you're currently in (Or %y%l<NAME>%x's privileges in the room they're currently in, if %y%l<NAME>%x is specified and you're an %y%lApprentice Wizard/%yDruid%x or above.)

You can use this command to find out what you can and can't do in the room you're currently in (E.g:  Whether you can %c%ltalk%x, %c%lyell%x (A localised version of '%g%l%(shout%)%x' for Mortals), %c%lfight%x and use %c%lbad language%x (Even though you shouldn't anyway.))

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xYou can %y%lALWAYS%x yell in your own rooms, regardless of %g%l%(YELL%)%x flag settings (I.e:  You shouldn't use '%g%lprivileges%x' to see if a flag is set on a particular object  -  You should use '%g%l%(settings%) <OBJECT>%x' instead.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<scan%>%x', '%g%l%<profile%>%x', '%g%l%<examine%>%x', '%g%l%<settings%>%x' and '%g%l%<yell%>%x'.

