%TUTORIAL
%TITLE Help on '%w%lscan%x' (Or '%w%lfinger%x')
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lfinger[full|brief] [<NAME>] [= secret]
        scan[full|brief] [<NAME>] [= secret]
        x[f|b] [<NAME>] [= secret]%]%x

Displays information about the character %y%l<NAME>%x (Or yourself, if %y%l<NAME>%x isn't specified), such as their description, time they last connected and how long ago that was, race, score, credit, current location, etc.

Two formats of '%g%lscan%x' are available (%c%lBrief%x and %c%lfull%x.)  '%g%lscan%x', '%g%lfinger%x' and '%g%lx%x' display the %c%lbrief format%x on a %y%lTelnet%x connection and the %c%lfull format%x on a %y%lWorld Wide Web Interface%x connection.

'%g%lscanfull%x', '%g%lfingerfull%x' and '%g%lxf%x' display the %c%lfull format%x, and '%g%lscanbrief%x', '%g%lfingerbrief%x' and '%g%lxb%x' display the brief format.

%PAGE
Both the brief and full format of '%g%lscan%x' show similar information, but the full format goes into more detail, showing average idle/active times, creation date, total number of logins, etc. (This results in more screen output.)

If the second parameter ('%y%l= secret%x') is specified, the scanned user's '%y%l.scan%x' compound command (If they have one (See '%g%l%<.scan%>%x')) will not be executed.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%+scan%>%x', '%g%l%<profile%>%x', '%g%l%<look%>%x', '%g%l%<inventory%>%x', '%g%l%<examine%>%x', '%g%l%<secret flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<.scan%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

