%TOPIC visit
%TOPIC goplayer
%TOPIC gocharacter
%TOPIC visitplayer
%TOPIC visitcharacter
%TITLE Help on '%w%lvisit%x' (Or '%w%lgo%x')
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lvisit <NAME>
        go <NAME>%]%x

The '%g%lvisit%x' (Or '%g%lgo%x') command takes you to the location of the character %y%l<NAME>%x, providing their location has its %y%l%(ABODE%)%x and %y%l%(VISIT%)%x flags (See '%g%l%<abode flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<visit flag%>%x') set or they have set the %y%l%(^friend VISIT%)%x friend flag (See '%g%l%<visit friend flag%>%x') on you in their friends list (See '%g%l%<friends%>%x'.)  E.g:  '%g%lgo fred bloggs%x'.

If you have set the %y%l%(^friend VISIT%)%x friend flag on any of your friends, you can temporarily disable its effect by setting your %y%l%(PRIVATE%)%x flag ('%g%l%(@set%) me = private%x'  -  See '%g%l%<private flag%>%x')  -  Having done this, you can allow your friends to visit you again whenever they like by simply resetting your %y%lPRIVATE%x flag ('%g%l%(@set%) me = !private%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<to%>%x', '%g%l%<summon%>%x', '%g%l%<warp%>%x', '%g%l%<@tel%>%x', '%g%l%<abode flag%>%x', '%g%l%<visit flag%>%x', '%g%l%<private flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<fset%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC unlock
%TOPIC unlockingexits
%TOPIC unlockingvehicles
%TOPIC unlockingcontainers
%TITLE Help on '%w%lunlock%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lunlock <OBJECT>%]%x

The '%g%lunlock%x' command unlocks the %c%lcontainer%x, %c%lvehicle%x or %c%lexit %y%l<OBJECT>%x, so that it can be opened and closed (Using the '%g%l%(open%)%x' and '%g%l%(close%)%x' commands (See '%g%l%<open%>%x' and '%g%l%<close%>%x'.))

A container or vehicle can only be unlocked if its %c%llock key%x ('%g%l%(@key%)%x'  -  See '%g%l%<@key%>%x') is satisfied.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<lock%>%x', '%g%l%<open%>%x', '%g%l%<close%>%x', '%g%l%<@key%>%x', '%g%l%<@lock%>%x' and '%g%l%<containers%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC wake
%TOPIC sleep
%TOPIC asleep
%TOPIC waking
%TOPIC wakeup
%TOPIC sleeping
%TITLE Help on '%w%lwake%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lwake <NAME>%]%x

The '%g%lwake%x' command is used to 'wake up' and get the attention of another user (Especially someone who's currently idle.)  It sends a wake up message to the character %y%l<NAME>%x along with an attention grabbing beep and the time you tried to wake them.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<idle%>%x' and '%g%l%<page%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC warn
%TOPIC warnings
%TOPIC warningusers
%TOPIC officialwarnings
%TITLE Help on '%w%lwarn%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lwarn <NAME> = <WARNING>%]%x

This command can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above.

Issues an official warning to the character %y%l<NAME>%x.  This command should be used to warn characters who are breaking the rules of the game, being abusive, harassing other users, etc.

Official warnings are logged to the '%c%lWarn%x' log file (See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<moron flag%>%x', '%g%l%<@boot%>%x', '%g%l%<@ban%>%x' and '%g%l%<@site%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC warp
%TOPIC bounce
%TITLE Help on '%w%lwarp%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lwarp [<NAME>]%]%x

Teleports you to a random %y%l%(ABODE%)%x (See '%g%l%<abode flag%>%x') location in %@%m  -  This is a great way of exploring the virtual world and discovering new areas (Especially those built by Builders, which are seldomly linked up to the rest of the virtual world or advertised on the %y%l%@%n BBS%x.)

If %y%l<NAME>%x is specified, you'll be teleported to one of the character %y%l<NAME>%x's %y%l%(ABODE%)%x locations at random (A great way for finding the %y%l%(ABODE%)%x rooms of a user without remembering the #ID numbers.)

%9%6%c%lPLEASE NOTE:  %xLocations which have their %y%l%(WARP%)%x flag (See '%g%l%<warp flag%>%x') reset (The default for things) will be excluded from the '%g%lwarp%x' command.  This is ideal if you have an %y%l%(ABODE%)%x location which you don't want other users to teleport to at random via the '%g%lwarp%x' command.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<go%>%x', '%g%l%<to%>%x', '%g%l%<@tel%>%x', '%g%l%<abode flag%>%x' and '%g%l%<warp flag%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC welcome
%TOPIC welcoming
%TOPIC welcomingusers
%TITLE Help on '%w%lwelcome%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lwelcome list [<PAGE NO>]
        welcome [<NAME>]%]%x

This command can only be used by %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above, and %r%lExperienced Builders/%rAssistants%x (Providing there are %c%l3%x or less %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above connected.)

The '%g%lwelcome%x' command is used to welcome new users to %@%n, and offer them your help, should they need it.

Typing '%g%lwelcome list%x' will display a list of new users who need welcoming  -  You can welcome one of these users by typing '%g%lwelcome <NAME>%x', or welcome the first user in the list by typing '%g%lwelcome%x' on its own.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %r%lExpererienced Builders/%rAssistants%x above can welcome users who have been connected for over %c%l2 minutes%x without being welcomed, or when there are %c%l3%x or less %y%lApprentice Wizards/%yDruids%x and above connected.

%PAGE
If %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, the list of users who need welcoming will be split up into pages and the page number specified will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%lwelcome list 1%x', '%g%lwelcome list 2%x', etc.

Usage of the '%g%lwelcome%x' command is logged to the '%c%lWelcome%x' log file (See '%g%l%<@log%>%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<assist%>%x', '%g%l%<@log%>%x' and '%g%l%<admin%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC where
%TOPIC whereis
%TOPIC wherelist
%TITLE Help on '%w%lwhere%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lwhere [<PAGE NO>] [<FLAGS>]
        where *<NAME>%]%x

The first form ('%g%lwhere [<PAGE NO>] [<FLAGS>]%x') displays a full list of all characters connected to %@%n and where they currently are (I.e:  The name of the room/container they're currently in.)

If %y%l<PAGE NO>%x is specified, the list of users will be split up into pages and the page number specified will be displayed, e.g:  '%g%lwhere 1%x', '%g%lwhere 2%x', etc.

If one or more flags (Separated by spaces) are specified, only characters with those flags are listed, e.g:  '%g%lwhere admin%x', '%g%lwhere mortals%x', '%g%lwhere haven quiet%x', etc.

The second form ('%g%lwhere *<NAME>%x') tells you where the character %y%l<NAME>%x presently is (Regardless of whether they are connected or not.)  If they're connected and in a room with other users, the users they're with are listed too.  (%c%lNOTE:  %xYou don't have to put a '%y%l*%x' in front of %y%l<NAME>%x  -  However, if you don't, the chances are that the name you give may match to a %@%m flag.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<secret flag%>%x', '%g%l%<who%>%x' and '%g%l%<swho%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC secrets
%TOPIC whisper
%TOPIC whispering
%TOPIC secretmessages
%TITLE Help on '%w%lwhisper%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lwhisper <NAME> [=] <MESSAGE>%]%x

Whispers %y%l<MESSAGE>%x to the character %y%l<NAME>%x, providing they're in the same room as you.  Only the recipient will receive the message  -  However, everyone else in the room will see a message along the lines of:

%w%lFred Bloggs %c%lwhispers something to %w%lJoe Bloggs%c%l.%x

If %b%lMorons%x try to whisper, everyone in the room overhears what they say.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<page%>%x' and '%g%l%<tell%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC yell
%TOPIC scream
%TOPIC yelling
%TOPIC screaming
%TITLE Help on '%w%lyell%x'
%[%c%lUSAGE:  %g%lyell <MESSAGE>%]%x

'%g%lyell%x' is a localised version of '%g%l%(shout%)%x' that allows Mortals to yell messages to everyone listed on '%g%l%(lwho%)%x' (Local user list) who are in a room with its %y%l%(YELL%)%x flag set.

Only characters with a %y%l%(YELL%)%x flag may yell messages (Everyone starts off with a %y%l%(YELL%)%x flag  -  You only lose it if you abuse it!)  You can yell in your own rooms regardless of whether you have a %y%l%(YELL%)%x flag or not.  Morons can't yell anywhere.  You can find out if you can yell in a room by simply typing '%g%l%(privileges%)%x'.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<lwho%>%x', '%g%l%<privileges%>%x' and '%g%l%<yell flag%>%x'.

