%TOPIC actioncompoundcommands
%TITLE Help on %w%lAction Compound Commands%x
%@%m features a number of special action compound commands which are executed when certain actions are performed on an object (For example, picking it up, looking at it, dropping it, etc.)

Each of these compound commands is prefixed with a '%g%l.%x', usually followed by a name which is appropriate for the command it is related to (E.g:  '%g%l.look%x' and '%g%l.looked%x' for the '%g%l%(look%)%x' command.)

To use action compound commands, simply create them and attach them to the required object (Using '%g%l%(drop%)%x' or '%g%l%(@tel%)%x'.)

The functionality of some action compound commands can also be replicated with fuses (See '%g%l%<@fuse%>%x'), but action compound commands can save you time, effort and Quota to achieve the same effect.

%PAGE

%[%c%l%$Parameters for most action compound commands:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%g%l%6$1   %xThe name of the character involking the action compound command.
%g%l%6$2   %xThe affected object.
%g%l%6$3   %xFor '%g%l.drive%x' and '%g%l.driven%x', the vehicle's destination.
     For '%g%l.give%x' and '%g%l.given%x', the recipient of the object.%]%x


%[%c%l%$Key:
%~%c~~~
%y%l* %c= %xAny object.
%y%lC %c= %x%(Character%)
%y%lE %c= %x%(Exit%)
%y%lR %c= %x%(Room%)
%y%lT %c= %x%(Thing%)%]

%PAGE
%m%lA complete list of available action commands is given below...%x


%[%c%l%$Command:%x    %c%l%$@command:%x      %c%l%$Executed:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~    ~~~~~~~~~      ~~~~~~~~~
%g%l%(close%)       .close     %y%lET  %xBefore container/exit is closed.
%g%l%(close%)       .closed    %y%lET  %xAfter container/exit is closed.
%g%l%(drop%)%c/%g%l%(throw%)  .drop      %y%lT   %xBefore object is dropped.
%g%l%(drop%)%c/%g%l%(throw%)  .dropped   %y%lT   %xAfter object is dropped.
%g%l%(drive%)%c/%g%l%(ride%)  .drive     %y%lT   %xBefore vehicle is driven/ridden.
%g%l%(drive%)%c/%g%l%(ride%)  .driven    %y%lT   %xAfter vehicle has been driven/ridden.
            %g%l.exit      %y%lE   %xBefore going through an exit.
            %g%l.exited    %y%lE   %xAfter going through an exit.
%g%l%(give%)        .give      %y%lT   %xBefore object is given to someone else.
%g%l%(give%)        .given     %y%lT   %xAfter object has been given to someone else.
%g%l%(junk%)        .junk      %y%lT   %xBefore object is junked.
%g%l%(junk%)        .junked    %y%lT   %xAfter object is junked.%]%x

%PAGE

%[%c%l%$Command:%x    %c%l%$@command:%x      %c%l%$Executed:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~    ~~~~~~~~~       ~~~~~~~~~
%g%l%(lock%)        .lock      %y%lET  %xBefore container/exit is locked.
%g%l%(lock%)        .locked    %y%lET  %xAfter container/exit is locked.
%g%l%(look%)        .look      %y%l*   %xBefore object is looked at.
%g%l%(look%)        .lookdesc  %y%l*   %xAfter object's description is looked at.
%g%l%(look%)        .looked    %y%l*   %xAfter object is looked at.
%g%l%(open%)        .open      %y%lET  %xBefore container/exit is opened.
%g%l%(open%)        .opened    %y%lET  %xAfter container/exit is opened.
%g%l%(get%)%c/%g%l%(take%)    .take      %y%lT   %xBefore object is picked up.
%g%l%(get%)%c/%g%l%(take%)    .taken     %y%lT   %xAfter object is picked up.
%g%l%(unlock%)      .unlock    %y%lET  %xBefore container/exit is unlocked.
%g%l%(unlock%)      .unlocked  %y%lET  %xAfter container/exit is unlocked.%]%x

%PAGE

%c%l%$Restrictions:
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xWhen action compound commands execute, they will run under the ID of their owner, unless the %y%l%(WIZARD%)%x flag is set (See '%g%l%<wizard flag%>%x') or the action compound command is owned by Admin.

The action compound command will also disallow writing to the character executing the compound command (For example, you can't change their description)  Again, the %y%l%(WIZARD%)%x flag or admin ownership removes this restriction.

These restrictions are for security and to prevent abuse of action compound commands. 

%c%l%8NOTE:%x  '%g%l.lookdesc%x' follows the rules for '%g%l%(.scan%)%x' and '%g%l%(.profile%)%x' when attached to a character (It executes under the ID of the character looked at.)  Also, '%g%l.lookdesc%x' is executed when a character is scanned (Ideal for creating customised descriptions.)
%PAGE
%c%l%8NOTE:  %xAction compound commands (And other compound commands starting with '%g%l.%x') cannot be directly executed from the command-line by typing their name.  However, they can be executed by #ID or directly by name from within another compound command.

%c%l%8HINT:  %xTo save Quota, try combining multiple action compound commands on the same object into one, by naming just one compound command with all the names you require, separated by '%g%l;%x', e.g:  '%g%l.look;.lookdesc;.looked%x'.  You can then use the '%g%l{%(@?cmdname%)%g%l}%x' query command (See '%g%l%<@?cmdname%>%x') to test which action compound command has been invoked.


%c%l%$Other Action Compound Commands
%~%c~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%xThe following is a list of other available action compound commands (Not subject to above restrictions)  -  See individual help pages for more information on these...

%PAGE

%[%c%l%$Command:%x  %c%l%$@command:%x       %c%l%$Executed:%x
%~%c~~~~~~~~  ~~~~~~~~~       ~~~~~~~~~
%g%l%(enter%)     %(.enter%)     %y%lRT   %xContainer or area is entered.
%g%l          %(.entercmd%)  %y%lC    %xCharacter enters a room.
%g%l%(leave%)     %(.leave%)     %y%lRT   %xContainer or area is exited.
%g%l          %(.leavecmd%)  %y%lC    %xCharacter leaves a room.
%g%l          %(.login%)     %y%lCRT  %xCharacter connects.
%g%l          %(.reconnect%) %y%lCRT  %xCharacter reconnects.
%g%l%(QUIT%)      %(.logout%)    %y%lCRT  %xCharacter disconnects.
%g%l%(page%)      %(.page%)      %y%lC    %x'%g%l%(page%)%x' message is sent to character.
%g%l%(profile%)   %(.profile%)   %y%lC    %xProfile of character is viewed.
%g%l%(tell%)      %(.tell%)      %y%lC    %x'%g%l%(tell%)%x' message is sent to character.
%g%l%(scan%)      %(.scan%)      %y%lC    %xCharacter is scanned.
%g%l%(use%)       %(.use%)       %y%l*    %xObject is used with the '%g%l%(use%)%x' command.%]%x
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<@command%>%x', '%g%l%<@teleport%>%x' '%g%l%<@fuse%>%x' and '%g%l%<advanced%>%x'.

