%TOPIC .enter
%TOPIC .entercommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.enter%x' compound command
%8%c%lNOTE:  %xA '%g%l.enter%x' compound command attached to you has no effect (See '%g%l%<.entercmd%>%x'.)

A '%g%l.enter%x' compound command in a room or container executes when a character enters that room or any of the rooms within it.

If the csuccess/cfailure branch of a '%g%l.enter%x' compound command is set to '%y%lHOME%x', %@%m will continue searching up the area-tree for another '%g%l.enter%x' compound command and execute it.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.leave%>%x', '%g%l%<.entercmd%>%x', '%g%l%<.leavecmd%>%x', '%g%l%<.login%>%x', '%g%l%<.logout%>%x' and '%g%l%<.action%>%x'

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC .leave
%TOPIC .leavecommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.leave%x' compound command
%8%c%lNOTE:  %xA '%g%l.leave%x' compound command attached to you has no effect (See '%g%l%<.leavecmd%>%x'.)

A '%g%l.leave%x' compound command in a room or container executes when a character leaves that room or any of the rooms within it (As long as their destination room isn't a room within the room the '%g%l.leave%x' is in.)

If the csuccess/cfailure branch of a '%g%l.leave%x' compound command is set to '%y%lHOME%x', %@%m will continue searching up the area-tree for another '%g%l.leave%x' compound command and execute it.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.enter%>%x', '%g%l%<.leavecmd%>%x', '%g%l%<.entercmd%>%x', '%g%l%<.login%>%x', '%g%l%<.logout%>%x' and '%g%l%<.action%>%x'

