%TOPIC .entercmd
%TOPIC .entermsg
%TOPIC entrymessages
%TOPIC .entermessages
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.entercmd%x' compound command
If you have a compound command on you called '%y%l.entercmd%x', it will be executed whenever you move to a new location (In the destination room), allowing you to create a custom entry message for your character, e.g:

%[%g%l%(@command%) .entercmd = %(@oemote%) wanders into the room and greets everyone.%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.leavecmd%>%x', '%g%l%<.enter%>%x', '%g%l%<.leave%>%x' and '%g%l%<.action%>%x'

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC .leavecmd
%TOPIC .leavemsg
%TOPIC .leavemessages
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.leavecmd%x' compound command
If you have a compound command on you called '%y%l.leavecmd%x', it will be executed whenever you move to a new location (In the room you left), allowing you to create a custom leave message for your character, e.g:

%[%g%l%(@command%) .leavecmd = %(@oemote%) waves to everyone and leaves the room.%]
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.entercmd%>%x', '%g%l%<.enter%>%x', '%g%l%<.leave%>%x' and '%g%l%<.action%>%x'

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC .login
%TOPIC .logincommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.login%x' compound command
A '%g%l.login%x' compound command attached to you executes when you connect to %@%n (Useful for setting your preferences (Word-wrap, prompt, etc.))

A '%g%l.login%x' compound command in a room or container executes when a character connects to %@%n and is in that room or any of the rooms within it.

If the csuccess/cfailure branch of a '%g%l.login%x' compound command is set to '%y%lHOME%x', %@%m will continue searching up the area-tree for another '%g%l.login%x' compound command and execute it.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.reconnect%>%x', '%g%l%<.logout%>%x', '%g%l%<.enter%>%x', '%g%l%<.leave%>%x' and '%g%l%<.action%>%x'

