%TOPIC .logout
%TOPIC .logoutcommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.logout%x' compound command
A '%g%l.logout%x' compound command attached to you executes when you disconnect from %@%n.

A '%g%l.logout%x' compound command in a room or container executes when a character disconnects from %@%n in that room or any of the rooms within it.

If the csuccess/cfailure branch of a '%g%l.logout%x' compound command is set to '%y%lHOME%x', %@%m will continue searching up the area-tree for another '%g%l.logout%x' compound command and execute it.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.login%>%x', '%g%l%<.reconnect%>%x', '%g%l%<.enter%>%x', '%g%l%<.leave%>%x' and '%g%l%<.action%>%x'

