%TOPIC .message
%TOPIC .messagevariable
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.message%x' variable
The '%g%l.message%x' variable is used to set alternative messages when someone pages/tells a message to you when you are set %y%l%(HAVEN%)%x, not connected, idle or have reset their %y%lPAGETELL%x/%y%lMAIL%x/%y%lLINK%x friend flag(s).

To create a '%y%l.message%x' variable, simply type '%g%l%(@var%) .message%x'.  You can then set the messages as follows...

%9%9%9%4%g%l%(@succ%) .message = <TIME>%x       Sets the time you have to be idle for (In secs) before your idle message ('%g%l%(@osucc%)%x' of '%g%l.message%x') is displayed.

%9%9%9%4%g%l%(@osucc%) .message = <MESSAGE>%x   Displayed when someone tries to page/tell a message to you and you've been idle for the amount of time (Or longer) specified in the '%g%l%(@succ%)%x' of your '%g%l.message%x' (In secs.)

%9%9%9%4%g%l%(@fail%) .message = <MESSAGE>%x    Displayed when someone tries to page/tell a message to you and you're set %y%l%(HAVEN%)%x.

%PAGE
%9%9%9%4%g%l%(@ofail%) .message = <MESSAGE>%x   Displayed when someone tries to page/tell a message to you and you're not connected.

%9%9%9%4%g%l%(@drop%) .message = <MESSAGE>%x    Displayed when someone tries to page/tell a message to you and you've removed their %y%lPAGETELL%x friend flag (E.g:  '%g%l%(fset%) <NAME> = !pagetell%x'.)

%9%9%9%4%g%l%(@odrop%) .message = <MESSAGE>%x   Displayed when someone tries to send mail to you and you've removed their %y%lMAIL%x friend flag (E.g:  '%g%l%(fset%) <NAME> = !mail%x'.)

%9%9%9%4%g%l%(@desc%) .message = <MESSAGE>%x    Displayed when someone tries to '%g%l%(@link%)%x' or '%g%l%(@tel%)%x' themselves to one of your (%y%l%(ABODE%)%x) rooms and you've removed their %y%lLINK%x friend flag (E.g:  '%g%l%(fset%) <NAME> = !link%x'.)
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<page%>%x', '%g%l%<tell%>%x', '%g%l%<fset%>%x' and '%g%l%<@lock%>%x'.

