%TOPIC .startup
%TOPIC .initialise
%TOPIC .startupcommand
%TOPIC .initialisecommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.startup%x' compound command
This command (When owned by %m%lRoot%x and placed in %y%l#4%x) is executed when %@%n is %c%l(re)started%x.

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xThe '%g%l.startup%x' compound command has a maximum execution time limit of %c%l1 minute%x (This can be increased or decreased if necessary using '%g%l%(@executionlimit%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@executionlimit%>%x'.))
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.shutdown%>%x', '%g%l%<.login%>%x', '%g%l%<.logout%>%x', '%g%l%<.enter%>%x' and '%g%l%<.leave%>%x'.

%COMMENT --------------------------------------------------------------------->

%TOPIC .shutdown
%TOPIC .shutdowncommand
%TITLE Help on the '%w%l.shutdown%x' compound command
This command (When owned by %m%lRoot%x and placed in %y%l#4%x) is executed when %@%n is shutdown using the '%g%l%(@shutdown%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@shutdown%>%x'.)

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xThe '%g%l.shutdown%x' compound command has a maximum execution time limit of %c%l1 minute%x (This can be increased or decreased if necessary using '%g%l%(@executionlimit%)%x' command (See '%g%l%<@executionlimit%>%x'.))

%8%c%lNOTE:  %xThe '%g%l.shutdown%x' command %r%lWILL NOT%x be executed if %@%n crashes and/or starts an emergency database dump.  It is only executed before %c%lnormal shutdown%x.
<-SEPARATOR->
Also, see '%g%l%<.startup%>%x', '%g%l%<.login%>%x', '%g%l%<.logout%>%x', '%g%l%<.enter%>%x' and '%g%l%<.leave%>%x'.

